Name: Axitinib
Information: Axitinib is a multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFRβ and c-Kit with IC50 of 0.1 nM, 0.2 nM, 0.1-0.3 nM, 1.6 nM and 1.7 nM in Porcine aorta endothelial cells, respectively.

Name: Roxadustat (FG-4592)
Information: Roxadustat (FG-4592) is an HIF-α prolyl hydroxylase inhibitor in a cell-free assay, stabilizes HIF-2 and induces EPO production. Phase 3.

Name: Selumetinib (AZD6244)
Information: Selumetinib (AZD6244) is a potent, highly selective MEK inhibitor with IC50 of 14 nM for MEK1 and Kd value of 530 nM for MEK2. It  also inhibits ERK1/2 phosphorylation with IC50 of 10 nM, no inhibition to p38α, MKK6, EGFR, ErbB2, ERK2, B-Raf, etc. Phase 3.

Name: Nintedanib (BIBF 1120)
Information: Nintedanib (BIBF 1120) is a potent triple angiokinase inhibitor for VEGFR1/2/3, FGFR1/2/3 and PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 34 nM/13 nM/13 nM, 69 nM/37 nM/108 nM and 59 nM/65 nM in cell-free assays. Phase 3.

Name: Afatinib (BIBW2992)
Information: Afatinib (BIBW2992) inhibits EGFR/ErbB irreversibly in vitro with IC50 of 0.5, 0.4, 10, 14, 1 nM for EGFRwt, EGFR L858R , EGFR L858R/T790M ErbB2 (HER2) and ErbB4 (HER4), respectively.

Name: Bortezomib (PS-341)
Information: Bortezomib (PS-341) is a potent 20S proteasome inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM. It exhibits favorable selectivity towards tumor cells over normal cells.

Name: Bosutinib (SKI-606)
Information: Bosutinib (SKI-606) is a novel, dual Src/Abl inhibitor with IC50 of 1.2 nM and 1 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Dasatinib
Information: Dasatinib is a novel, potent and multi-targeted inhibitor that targets Abl, Src and c-Kit, with IC50 of <1 nM, 0.8 nM and 79 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Ridaforolimus (Deforolimus, MK-8669)
Information: Ridaforolimus (Deforolimus, MK-8669) is a selective mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 nM in HT-1080 cell line while not classified as a prodrug, mTOR inhibition and FKBP12 binding is similar to rapamycin. Phase 3.

Name: Gefitinib (ZD1839)
Information: Gefitinib (ZD-1839) is an EGFR inhibitor for Tyr1173, Tyr992, Tyr1173 and Tyr992 in the NR6wtEGFR and NR6W cells with IC50 of 37 nM, 37nM, 26 nM and 57 nM, respectively.

Name: Imatinib Mesylate (STI571)
Information: Imatinib Mesylate (STI571) is an orally bioavailability mesylate salt of Imatinib, which is a multi-target inhibitor of v-Abl, c-Kit and PDGFR with IC50 of 0.6 μM, 0.1 μM and 0.1 μM in cell-free or cell-based assays, respectively.

Name: Lapatinib (GW-572016) Ditosylate
Information: Lapatinib (GW-572016) Ditosylate is a potent EGFR and ErbB2 inhibitor with IC50 of 10.8 and 9.2 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Lenalidomide (CC-5013)
Information: Lenalidomide (CC-5013) is a TNF-α secretion inhibitor with IC50 of 13 nM in PBMCs.

Name: Panobinostat (LBH589)
Information: Panobinostat (LBH589) is a novel broad-spectrum HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 5 nM in a cell-free assay. Phase 3.

Name: Nilotinib (AMN-107)
Information: Nilotinib (AMN-107) is a selective Bcr-Abl inhibitor with IC50 less than 30 nM in Murine myeloid progenitor cells.

Name: Pazopanib HCl (GW786034 HCl)
Information: Pazopanib HCl (GW786034 HCl) is a novel multi-target inhibitor of VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFR, FGFR, c-Kit and c-Fms with IC50 of 10 nM, 30 nM, 47 nM, 84 nM, 74 nM, 140 nM and 146 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Rapamycin (Sirolimus)
Information: Rapamycin (Sirolimus) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of ~0.1 nM HEK293 cells.

Name: Sorafenib Tosylate
Information: Sorafenib Tosylate is a multikinase inhibitor of Raf-1, B-Raf and VEGFR-2 with IC50 of 6 nM, 22 nM and 90 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Sunitinib Malate
Information: Sunitinib Malate is a multi-targeted RTK inhibitor targeting VEGFR2 (Flk-1) and PDGFRβ with IC50 of 80 nM and 2 nM in cell-free assays, and also inhibits c-Kit.

Name: Temsirolimus (CCI-779, NSC 683864)
Information: Temsirolimus (CCI-779, NSC 683864) is a specific mTOR inhibitor with IC50 of 1.76 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Vorinostat (SAHA, MK0683)
Information: Vorinostat (suberoylanilide hydroxamic acid, SAHA) is an HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of ~10 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Entinostat (MS-275)
Information: Entinostat (MS-275) strongly inhibits HDAC1 and HDAC3 with IC50 of 0.51 μM and 1.7 μM in cell-free assays, compared with HDACs 4, 6, 8, and 10. Phase 3.

Name: Enzastaurin (LY317615)
Information: Enzastaurin (LY317615) is a potent PKCβ selective inhibitor with IC50 of 6 nM in cell-free assays, 6- to 20-fold selectivity against PKCα, PKCγ and PKCε. Phase 3.

Name: Olaparib (AZD2281, Ku-0059436)
Information: Olaparib (AZD2281, KU0059436) is a selective inhibitor of PARP1/2 with IC50 of 5 nM/1 nM in cell-free assays, 300-times less effective against tankyrase-1.

Name: Masitinib (AB1010)
Information: Masitinib is a novel inhibitor for Kit and PDGFRα/β with IC50 of 200 nM and 540 nM/800 nM, weak inhibition to ABL and c-Fms. Phase 3.

Name: Crizotinib (PF-02341066)
Information: Crizotinib (PF-02341066) is a potent inhibitor of c-Met and ALK with IC50 of 11 nM and 24 nM in cell-based assays, respectively.

Name: Vismodegib (GDC-0449)
Information: Vismodegib (GDC-0449) is a potent, novel and specific hedgehog inhibitor with IC50 of 3 nM and also inhibits P-gp with IC50 of 3.0 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Belinostat (PXD101)
Information: Belinostat (PXD101) is a novel HDAC inhibitor with IC50 of 27 nM in a cell-free assay, with activity demonstrated in cisplatin-resistant tumors.

Name: Rucaparib (AG-014699,PF-01367338) phosphate
Information: Rucaparib (AG-014699, PF-01367338) is an inhibitor of PARP with Ki of 1.4 nM for PARP1 in a cell-free assay, also showing binding affinity to eight other PARP domains. Phase 3.

Name: Cabozantinib (XL184, BMS-907351)
Information: Cabozantinib (XL184, BMS-907351) is a potent VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.035 nM and also inhibits c-Met, Ret, Kit, Flt-1/3/4, Tie2, and AXL with IC50 of 1.3 nM, 4 nM, 4.6 nM, 12 nM/11.3 nM/6 nM, 14.3 nM and 7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Everolimus (RAD001)
Information: Everolimus (RAD001) is an mTOR inhibitor of FKBP12 with IC50 of 1.6-2.4 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Malotilate
Information: Malotilate, diisopropyl 1,3-dithiol-2-ylidenemalonate, is a drug used for the treatment of liver cirrhosis.

Name: Ivacaftor (VX-770)
Information: Ivacaftor (VX-770) is a selective potentiator of CFTR targeting G551D-CFTR and F508del-CFTR with EC50 of 100 nM and 25 nM in fisher rat thyroid cells, respectively.

Name: Docetaxel
Information: Docetaxel, an analog of paclitaxel, is an inhibitor of depolymerisation of microtubules by binding to stabilized microtubules.

Name: Paclitaxel
Information: Paclitaxel is a microtubule polymer stabilizer with IC50 of 0.1 pM in human endothelial cells.

Name: Capecitabine
Information: Capecitabine is a tumor-selective fluoropyrimidine carbamate, which achieves higher intratumoral 5-FU level with lower toxicity than 5-FU.

Name: PA-824
Information: PA-824 is an anti-tuberculosis drug for tuberculosis with MIC less than 2.8 μM.Phase 2.

Name: Lenvatinib (E7080)
Information: Lenvatinib (E7080) is a multi-target inhibitor, mostly for VEGFR2(KDR)/VEGFR3(Flt-4) with IC50 of 4 nM/5.2 nM, less potent against VEGFR1/Flt-1, ~10-fold more selective for VEGFR2/3 against FGFR1, PDGFRα/β in cell-free assays. Phase 3.

Name: Valproic acid sodium salt (Sodium valproate)
Information: Valproic acid sodium salt (Sodium valproate) is a HDAC inhibitor by selectively inducing proteasomal degradation of HDAC2, used in the treatment of epilepsy, bipolar disorder and prevention of migraine headaches.

Name: Regorafenib (BAY 73-4506)
Information: Regorafenib (BAY 73-4506) is a multi-target inhibitor for VEGFR1, VEGFR2, VEGFR3, PDGFRβ, Kit, RET and Raf-1 with IC50 of 13 nM/4.2 nM/46 nM, 22 nM, 7 nM, 1.5 nM and 2.5 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Danoprevir (ITMN-191)
Information: Danoprevir(ITMN-191) is a peptidomimetic inhibitor of the NS3/4A protease of hepatitis C virus (HCV) with IC50 of 0.2-3.5 nM, inhibition effect for HCV genotypes 1A/1B/4/5/6 is ~10-fold higher than 2B/3A. Phase 2.

Name: Ritonavir
Information: Ritonavir is a Cytochrome P450 3A and Protease Inhibitor Also inhibits Cytochrome P450 2D6, P-Glycoprotein and induces Cytochrome P450 2C19, Cytochrome P450 1A2, Cytochrome P450 2C9, Cytochrome P450 2B6 and UDP Glucuronosyltransferases.

Name: Anastrozole
Information: Anastrozole is a third-generation nonsteroidal selective aromatase inhibitor. It may offer greater selectivity compared with other aromatase inhibitors, being without any intrinsic endocrine effects and with no apparent effect on the synthesis of adrenal steroids.

Name: Aprepitant
Information: Aprepitant is a potent and selective neurokinin-1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.1 nM.

Name: Bicalutamide
Information: Bicalutamide is an androgen receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 0.16 μM in LNCaP/AR(cs)cell line.

Name: Fulvestrant
Information: Fulvestrant is an estrogen receptor (ER) antagonist with IC50 of 0.94 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Raltitrexed
Information: Raltitrexed is a thymidylate synthase inhibitor with an IC50 of 9 nM for the inhibition of L1210 cell growth.

Name: Thalidomide
Information: Thalidomide was introduced as a sedative drug, immunomodulatory agent and also is investigated for treating symptoms of many cancers. Thalidomide inhibits an E3 ubiquitin ligase, which is a CRBN-DDB1-Cul4A complex.

Name: Exemestane
Information: Exemestane is an aromatase inhibitor, inhibits human placental and rat ovarian aromatase with IC50 of 30 nM and 40 nM, respectively.

Name: Finasteride
Information: Finasteride is a potent, reversible inhibitor of the rat type 1 5 alpha-reductase with Ki of 10.2 nM, used in the treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and male pattern baldness (MPB).

Name: Cladribine
Pharmacopoeia: USP42-NF37;BP2019;EP9.2;All compounds are not protected by patents
Information: Cladribine is an adenosine deaminase inhibitor for U266, RPMI8226, and MM1.S cells with IC50 of approximately 2.43 μM, 0.75 μM, and 0.18 μM, respectively.

Name: Decitabine
Information: Decitabine is a DNA methyltransferase inhibitor, incorporating into DNA and resulting in hypomethylation of DNA and intra-S-phase arrest of DNA replication. It is used to treat myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS).

Name: Dutasteride
Information: Dutasteride is a dual 5-α reductase inhibitor that inhibits conversion of testosterone to dihydrotestosterone (DHT).

Name: Melatonin
Information: Melatonin is a MT receptor agonist, used as a dietary supplement.

Name: Bisoprolol fumarate
Information: Bisoprolol fumarate is a selective type β1 adrenergic receptor blocker.

Name: Tivozanib (AV-951)
Information: Tivozanib (AV-951) is a potent and selective VEGFR inhibitor for VEGFR1/2/3 with IC50 of 30 nM/6.5 nM/15 nM, and also inhibits PDGFR and c-Kit, low activity observed against FGFR-1, Flt3, c-Met, EGFR and IGF-1R. Phase 3.

Name: Doxorubicin (Adriamycin) HCl
Information: Doxorubicin (Adriamycin) HCl is an antibiotic agent that inhibits DNA topoisomerase II and induces DNA damage and apoptosis in tumor cells.

Name: Fluorouracil (5-Fluoracil, 5-FU)
Information: Fluorouracil (5-Fluoracil, 5-FU) is a DNA/RNA synthesis inhibitor, which interrupts nucleotide synthetic by inhibiting thymidylate synthase (TS) in tumor cells.

Name: Methotrexate
Information: Methotrexate (MTX), analog of folic acid, is a nonspecific inhibitor of the dihydrofolate reductase(DHFR) of bacteria and cancerous cells as well as normal cells. It forms an inactive ternary complex with DHFR and NADPH.

Name: Bendamustine HCl
Information: Bendamustine HCL is a DNA-damaging agent with IC50 of 50 μM in cell-free assay.

Name: Nelarabine
Information: Nelarabine is a purine nucleoside analog and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 from 0.067-2.15 μM in tumor cells.

Name: Bleomycin sulfate
Information: Bleomycin Sulfate is a glycopeptide antibiotic and an anticancer agent for squamous cell carcinomas (SCC) with IC50 of 4 nM in UT-SCC-19A cells.

Name: Clofarabine
Information: Clofarabine inhibits the enzymatic activities of ribonucleotide reductase (IC50 = 65 nM) and DNA polymerase.

Name: Dacarbazine
Information: Dacarbazine is a triazene derivative with antineoplastic activity. Dacarbazine alkylates and cross-links DNA during all phases of the cell cycle, resulting in disruption of DNA function, cell cycle arrest, and apoptosis used in the treatment of various cancers.

Name: Dexrazoxane HCl (ICRF-187, ADR-529)
Information: Dexrazoxane HCl (ICRF-187, ADR-529) is an intracellular iron chelator, which decreases the formation of superoxide radicals, used as a cardioprotective agent also an inhibitor of topoisomerase II

Name: Epirubicin HCl
Information: Epirubicin HCl, a semisynthetic L-arabino derivative of doxorubicin, is an antineoplastic agent by inhibiting Topoisomerase.

Name: Etoposide
Information: Etoposide is a semisynthetic derivative of podophyllotoxin, which inhibits DNA synthesis via topoisomerase II  inhibition activity.

Name: Raloxifene HCl
Information: Raloxifene is an estrogen antagonist, which inhibits human cytosolic aldehyde oxidase-catalyzed phthalazine oxidation activity with IC50 of 5.7 nM.

Name: Fludarabine Phosphate
Information: Fludarabine Phosphate is an analogue of adenosine and deoxyadenosine, which is able to compete with dATP for incorporation into DNA and inhibit DNA synthesis.

Name: Topotecan HCl
Information: Topotecan HCl is a topoisomerase I inhibitor for MCF-7 Luc cells and DU-145 Luc cells with IC50 of 13 nM and 2 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: 2-Methoxyestradiol (2-MeOE2)
Information: 2-Methoxyestradiol (2-MeOE2) depolymerizes microtubules and blocks HIF-1α nuclear accumulation and HIF-transcriptional activity. Phase 2.

Name: Letrozole
Information: Letrozole is a third generation inhibitor of aromatase with IC50 of 0.07-20 nM in cell-free assays.It has no effect on the plasma levels of 17α-OH progesterone, thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH), luteinizing hormone (LH), follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), or androstenedione and does not affect normal urine electrolyte excretion or thyroid function in clinical studies.

Name: Temozolomide
Information: Temozolomide is a monofunctional SN-1 alkylating agent that can modify nitrogen atoms in the DNA ring and the extracyclic oxygen group, chemically converted to MTIC and degrades to methyldiazonium cation, which transfers methyl groups to DNA at physiologic pH. A DNA damage inducer in L-1210 and L-1210/BCNU cells.

Name: Tamoxifen
Information: Tamoxifen is an antagonist of the estrogen receptor in breast tissue.

Name: Vincristine sulfate
Information: Vincristine sulfate is an inhibitor of polymerization of microtubules by binding to tubulin with IC50 of 32 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Agomelatine
Information: Agomelatine is classified as a norepinephrine-dopamine disinhibitor (NDDI) due to its antagonism of the 5-HT2C receptor.

Name: Latrepirdine 2HCl
Information: Latrepirdine is an orally active,and neuroactive antagonist of multiple drug targets, including histamine receptors, GluR, and 5-HT receptors, used as an antihistamine drug.

Name: Leflunomide
Information: Leflunomide is a pyrimidine synthesis inhibitor belonging to the DMARD, used as an immunosuppressant agent.

Name: Enzalutamide (MDV3100)
Information: Enzalutamide (MDV3100) is an androgen-receptor (AR) antagonist with IC50 of 36 nM in LNCaP cells.

Name: Dienogest
Information: Dienogest is an orally active synthetic progesterone, used for contraception and the treatment of endometriosis.

Name: Entecavir Hydrate
Information: Entecavir, a new deoxyguanine nucleoside analogue, is a selective inhibitor of the replication of the hepatitis B virus (HBV).

Name: Nepafenac
Information: Nepafenac is a prodrug of amfenac that acts as an inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 activity, used in the treatment of pain and inflammation associated with cataract surgery.

Name: Rufinamide
Information: Rufinamide is a voltage-gated sodium channel blocker, used an anticonvulsant medication.

Name: Posaconazole
Information: Posaconazole is an inhibitor primarily of CYP3A4, but it does not inhibit the activity of other CYP enzymes Also an inhibitor of sterol C14ɑ demethylase inhibitor with IC50 of 0.25 μM. Posaconazole has a median terminal elimination half-life of 15-35 hours.

Name: Prasugrel
Information: Prasugrel is a thienopyridine ADP receptor (P2Y12) antagonist, used for the reduction of thrombotic cardiovascular events.

Name: Ramelteon
Information: Ramelteon is a novel melatonin receptor agonist for human MT1 and MT2 receptors and chick forebrain melatonin receptors with Ki of 14 pM, 112 pM and 23.1 pM, respectively.

Name: Cinacalcet HCl
Information: Cinacalcet HCl represents a new class of compounds for the treatment of hyperparathyroidism.

Name: Celecoxib
Information: Celecoxib is a selective COX-2 inhibitor with IC50 of 40 nM in Sf9 cells.

Name: Vemurafenib (PLX4032, RG7204)
Information: Vemurafenib (PLX4032, RG7204) is a novel and potent inhibitor of B-RafV600E with IC50 of 31 nM in cell-free assay. 10-fold selective for B-RafV600E over wild-type B-Raf in enzymatic assays and the cellular selectivity can exceed 100-fold.

Name: Acarbose
Information: Acarbose is an inhibitor of intestinal alpha-glucosidase, used to treat type 2 diabetes mellitus.

Name: Adapalene
Information: Adapalene is a dual RAR and RXR agonist, used in the treatment of acne.

Name: Altretamine
Information: Altretamine is an anti-neoplastic agent.

Name: Amisulpride
Information: Amisulpride is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat psychosis in schizophrenia and episodes of mania in bipolar disorder.

Name: Aniracetam
Information: Aniracetam is a nootropics and neuroprotective drug.

Name: Artemisinin
Information: Artemisinin is a sesquiterpene endoperoxide which is a potent antimalarial agent.

Name: Asenapine maleate
Information: Asenapine maleate is a high-affinity antagonist of serotonin, norepinephrine, dopamine and histamine receptors, used for the treatment of schizophrenia and acute mania associated with?bipolar disorder.

Name: Benazepril HCl
Information: Benazepril HCl is a novel angiotensin I converting enzyme inhibitor, used primarily in treatment of hypertension.

Name: Budesonide
Information: Budesonide is a glucocorticoid steroid for the treatment of asthma, non-infectious rhinitis.

Name: Bumetanide
Information: Bumetanide (Bumex) is a loop diuretic of the sulfamyl category to treat heart failure.

Name: Carmofur
Information: Carmofur is a highly potent acid ceramidase inhibitor, used in the treatment of breast and colorectal cancer.

Name: Cetirizine DiHCl
Information: Cetirizine DiHCl is an antihistamine.

Name: Cilnidipine
Information: Cilnidipine is a unique L-type and N-type calcium channel blocker, used for high blood pressure treatment.

Name: Cilostazol
Information: Cilostazol is a potent cyclic nucleotide phosphodiesterase type 3 (PDE3) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.2 μM and inhibitor of adenosine uptake.

Name: Floxuridine
Information: Floxuridine is an antineoplastic antimetabolite, used in the treatment of colon carcinoma and colorectal cancer that has metastasized to the liver.

Name: Tegafur (FT-207, NSC 148958)
Information: Tegafur (FT-207, NSC 148958) is a substance being used in the treatment of some types of cancer.

Name: Ifosfamide
Information: Ifosfamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent used in the treatment of cancer.

Name: Megestrol Acetate
Information: Megestrol acetate is a synthetic progestogen, used to treat breast cancer and loss of appetite.

Name: Mercaptopurine (6-MP)
Information: Mercaptopurine is a widely used antileukemic agent and immunosuppressive drug that inhibits de novo purine synthesis through incorporation of thiopurine methyltransferase metabolites into DNA and RNA.

Name: Streptozotocin (STZ)
Information: Streptozotocin is a glucosamine-nitrosourea derivative, which is a methylating, carcinogenic, antibiotic and diabetes inducing agent.

Name: Costunolide
Information: Costunolide, a natural sesquiterpene compound with multiple biological activities inhibits FPTase with IC50 of 20 μM, also inhibits telomerase with IC50 of 65-90 μM.

Name: Dexamethasone (DHAP)
Information: Dexamethasone (DHAP) is a potent synthetic member of the glucocorticoid class of steroid drugs, and an interleukin receptor modulator  that has anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant effects.

Name: Doxazosin Mesylate
Information: Doxazosin, a quinazoline-derivative, selectively antagonizes postsynaptic α1-adrenergic receptors, used in the treatment of high blood pressure and urinary retention associated with benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: Edaravone
Information: Edaravone is a novel potent free radical scavenger that has been clinically used to reduce the neuronal damage following ischemic stroke.

Name: Etodolac
Information: Etodolac is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) and a COX inhibitor, used for the treatment of inflammation and pain.

Name: Felbamate
Information: Felbamate (Felbatol) is an anticonvulsant drug used in the treatment of epilepsy NMDAR antagonist.

Name: Fluconazole
Information: Fluconazole is a fungal lanosterol 14 alpha-demethylase inhibitor, which thereby prevents the formation of ergosterol,used in the treatment and prevention of superficial and systemic fungal infections.

Name: Flumazenil
Information: Flumazenil is a competitive GABAA receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of benzodiazepine overdoses.

Name: Fluoxetine HCl
Information: Fluoxetine is a selective serotonin-reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) at the neuronal membrane, used in the treatment of depression.

Name: Flupirtine maleate
Information: Flupirtine maleate is the salt form of Flupirtine, which is a centrally acting non-opioid analgesia, is a selective neuronal potassium channel opener that also has NMDA receptor antagonist properties.

Name: Fluvoxamine maleate
Information: Fluvoxamine Maleate is a selective serotonin (5-HT) reuptake inhibitor (SSRI), used in the treatment of obsessive-compulsive disorder.

Name: Gatifloxacin
Information: Gatifloxacin is an antibiotic of the fourth-generation fluoroquinolone family, and inhibits the bacterial enzymes DNA gyrase and topoisomerase IV.

Name: Genistein
Information: Genistein, a phytoestrogen found in soy products, is a highly specific inhibitor of protein tyrosine kinase (PTK)  which blocks the mitogenic effect mediated by EGF on NIH-3T3 cells with IC50 of 12μM or by insulin with IC50 of 19 μM.

Name: Glimepiride
Information: Glimepiride is a potent Kir6.2/SUR inhibitor with IC50 of 3.0 nM, 5.4 nM, and 7.3 nM for SUR1, SUR2A and SUR2B, used in the treatment of type 2 diabetes mellitus.

Name: Ivermectin
Information: Ivermectin is a glutamate-gated chloride channel (GluCls) activator, used as a broad-spectrum antiparasitic drug.

Name: Lansoprazole
Information: Lansoprazole is a proton-pump inhibitor (PPI) which prevents the stomach from producing gastric acid.

Name: Levetiracetam
Information: Levetiracetam is an anticonvulsant medication used to treat epilepsy.

Name: Lidocaine
Information: Lidocaine is a selective inverse peripheral histamine H1-receptor agonist with an IC50 of >32 μM.

Name: Loratadine
Information: Loratadine is a histamine H1 receptor antagonist, used to treat allergies. Also acts as a selective inhibitor of B(0)AT2 with IC50 of 4 μM.

Name: Losartan Potassium (DuP 753)
Information: Losartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist, competes with the binding of angiotensin II to AT1 receptors with IC50 of 20 nM.

Name: Amonafide
Information: Amonafide produces protein-associated DNA-strand breaks through a topoisomerase II-mediated reaction, but does not produce topoisomerase I-mediated DNA cleavage. Phase 3.

Name: Acitretin
Information: Acitretin is a second generation retinoid used for psoriasis.

Name: Daptomycin
Information: Daptomycin is a novel antibiotic with rapid in vitro bactericidal activity against gram-positive organisms.

Name: Doripenem Hydrate
Information: Doripenem Hydrate is an ultra-broad-spectrum injectable antibiotic, used to treat complicated intra-abdominal infections and complicated urinary tract infections.

Name: Gestodene
Information: Gestodene is a progestogen hormonal contraceptive.

Name: Drospirenone
Information: Drospirenone is a synthetic progestin that is an analog to spironolactone.

Name: Ruxolitinib (INCB018424)
Information: Ruxolitinib (INCB018424) is the first potent, selective, JAK1/2 inhibitor to enter the clinic with IC50 of 3.3 nM/2.8 nM in cell-free assays, >130-fold selectivity for JAK1/2 versus JAK3.

Name: Isotretinoin
Information: It was developed to be used as a chemotherapy medication for the treatment of brain cancer, pancreatic cancer and more.

Name: Lopinavir
Information: Lopinavir is a potent HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 1.3 pM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Meropenem
Information: Meropenem is an ultra-broad spectrum injectable antibiotic.

Name: Mianserin HCl
Information: Mianserin is an potent antagonist of H1 histamine receptor and 5-HT serotonin receptors, used for the treatment of depression.

Name: Mosapride Citrate
Information: Mosapride Citrate is a gastroprokinetic agent that acts as a selective 5HT4 agonist.

Name: Nafamostat Mesylate
Information: Nafamostat mesilate is a synthetic serine protease inhibitor, used as an anticoagulant during hemodialysis.

Name: Naftopidil DiHCl
Information: Naftopidil DiHCl is a selective 5-HT1A and α1-adrenergic receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.1 μM and 0.2 μM, respectively.

Name: Omeprazole
Information: Omeprazole is a proton pump inhibitor, used to treat dyspepsia, peptic ulcer disease, gastroesophageal reflux disease, laryngopharyngeal reflux, and Zollinger–Ellison syndrome.

Name: Ondansetron HCl
Information: Ondansetron is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist, used to prevent nausea and vomiting caused by cancer chemotherapy, and radiation therapy.

Name: Oxcarbazepine
Information: Oxcarbazepine inhibits the binding of [3H]BTX to sodium channels with IC50 of 160 μM and also inhibits the influx of 22Na+ into rat brain synaptosomes with IC50 about 100 μM.

Name: Pirarubicin
Information: Pirarubicin is an anthracycline antibiotic, and also a DNA/RNA synthesis inhibitor by intercalating into DNA and interacts with topoisomerase II, used as an antineoplastic agent.

Name: Pizotifen Malate
Information: Pizotifen Malate is a benzocycloheptane based agent used for recurrent migraine headaches.

Name: Resveratrol
Information: Resveratrol has a wide spectrum of targets including cyclooxygenases(i.e. COX, IC50=1.1 μM), lipooxygenases（LOX, IC50=2.7 μM）, kinases, sirtuins and other proteins. It has anti-cancer, anti-inflammatory, blood-sugar-lowering and other beneficial cardiovascular effects.

Name: Rocuronium Bromide
Information: Rocuronium Bromide is a competitive AchR antagonist, used in modern anaesthesia.

Name: Stavudine (d4T)
Information: Stavudine (d4T) is a nucleoside analog reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NARTI) active against HIV.

Name: Tenofovir Disoproxil Fumarate
Information: Tenofovir Disoproxil Fumarate belongs to a class of antiretroviral drugs, it inhibits the activity of HIV reverse transcriptase by competing with the natural substrate deoxyadenosine 5’-triphosphate and, after incorporation into DNA, by DNA chain termination.

Name: Tenofovir
Information: Tenofovir blocks reverse transcriptase and hepatitis B virus infections.

Name: Tigecycline
Information: Tigecycline is bacteriostatic and is a protein synthesis inhibitor by binding to the 30S ribosomal subunit of bacteria and thereby blocking entry of Aminoacyl-tRNA into the A site of the ribosome during prokaryotic translation.

Name: Trilostane
Information: Trilostane is an inhibitor of 3β-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase used in the treatment of Cushing’s syndrome.

Name: Vecuronium Bromide
Information: Vecuronium is a non-depolarizing neuromuscular blocking agent, used for skeletal muscle relaxation during surgery.

Name: Bimatoprost
Information: Bimatoprost is a prostaglandin analog used topically (as eye drops) to control the progression of glaucoma and in the management of ocular hypertension.

Name: Linezolid
Information: Linezolid is a synthetic antibiotic used for the treatment of serious infections.

Name: Alfuzosin HCl
Information: Alfuzosin HCl  is an alpha1 receptor antagonist used to treat benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH).

Name: Clopidogrel
Information: Clopidogrel is an oral, thienopyridine class antiplatelet agent.

Name: Ranolazine 2HCl
Information: Ranolazine 2HCl is a calcium uptake inhibitor via the sodium/calcium channal, used to treat chronic angina.

Name: Repaglinide
Information: Repaglinide is a potassium channel blocker, which lowers blood glucose by stimulating the release of insulin from the pancreas, used the treatment of type II diabetes.

Name: Rolipram
Information: The PDE4 selective inhibitor, rolipram, inhibited immunopurified PDE4B and PDE4D activities similarly, with IC50 values of approx. 130 nM and 240 nM respectively an anti-inflammatory agent.

Name: Sildenafil Citrate
Information: Sildenafil Citrate, a selective inhibitor of cyclic guanosine monophosphate (cGMP)-specific phosphodiesterase type 5 (PDE5), is a well-tolerated and highly effective treatment for erectile dysfunction.

Name: Sumatriptan Succinate
Information: Sumatriptan Succinate is a triptan sulfa drug containing a sulfonamide group for the treatment of migraine headaches.

Name: Tamsulosin hydrochloride
Information: Tamsulosin (Flomax) hydrochloride is an antagonist of alpha1A adrenoceptors in the prostate.

Name: Tizanidine HCl
Information: Tizanidine HCl is an α2-adrenergic receptor agonist and inhibits neurotransmitter release from CNS noradrenergic neurons.

Name: Topiramate
Information: Topiramate is a mutil-targeted inhibitor, including voltage-gated sodium channel and calcium channel, AMPA/kainate receptor and carbonic anhydrase, used to treat epilepsy.

Name: Tranilast
Information: Tranilast?is an antiallergic drug by inhibiting lipid mediator and cytokine release from inflammatory cells, used for the treatment of allergic disorders such as asthma, allergic rhinitis and atopic dermatitis.

Name: Venlafaxine HCl
Information: Venlafaxine HCl is an arylalkanolamine serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI), used to treat major depressive disorder (MDD), generalised anxiety disorder (GAD), panic disorder and social phobia.

Name: Voriconazole
Information: Voriconazole is a new triazole derivative similar to fluconazole and itraconazole that acts by inhibiting fungal cytochrome P-450-dependent, 14-alpha-sterol demethylase-mediated synthesis of ergosterol.

Name: Zileuton
Information: Zileuton is an orally active inhibitor of 5-lipoxygenase, and thus inhibits leukotrienes (LTB4, LTC4, LTD4, and LTE4) formation, used to decrease the symptoms of asthma.

Name: Ziprasidone HCl
Information: Ziprasidone HCl is a novel and potent dopamine and serotonin (5-HT) receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of schizophrenia and bipolar disorder.

Name: Zonisamide
Information: Zonisamide is a voltage-dependent sodium channel and T-type calcium channel blocker, used as an antiepileptic drug.

Name: Tipifarnib
Information: Tipifarnib (R115777) is a potent and specific farnesyltransferase (FTase) inhibitor with IC50 of 0.6 nM, its anti-proliferative effects are most prominent in H-ras or N-ras mutant cells. Phase 3.

Name: Atazanavir Sulfate
Information: Atazanavir Sulfate is a HIV protease inhibitor with Ki of 2.66 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: VX-745
Information: VX-745 is a potent and selective inhibitor of p38α with IC50 of 10 nM, 22-fold greater selectivity versus p38β and no inhibition to p38γ.

Name: Moxifloxacin HCl
Information: Moxifloxacin is a fourth-generation synthetic fluoroquinolone antibacterial agent.

Name: Calcitriol
Information: Calcitriol is a nonselective vitamin D receptor activator/agonist(VDRA), exhibiting a 10-fold higher vitamin D receptor (VDR) binding affinity(IC50=0.4 nM) than the selective VDRA paricalcitol.

Name: Doxercalciferol
Information: Doxercalciferol is a synthetic vitamin D2 analog, suppressing parathyroid synthesis and secretion, used to treat secondary hyperparathyroidism and metabolic bone disease.

Name: Alfacalcidol
Information: Alfacalcidol is a non-selective VDR activator medication.

Name: Safinamide Mesylate
Information: Safinamide Mesylate is mesylate salt of Safinamide, selectively and reversibly inhibits MAO-B with IC50 of 98 nM, exhibits 5918-fold selectivity against MAO-A. Phase 3.

Name: Daclatasvir (BMS-790052)
Information: Daclatasvir (BMS-790052) is a highly selective inhibitor of HCV NS5A with EC50 of 9-50 pM, for a broad range of HCV replicon genotypes and the JFH-1 genotype 2a infectious virus in cell culture. Phase 3.

Name: Iloperidone
Information: Iloperidone is a dopamine (D2)/serotonin (5-HT2) receptor antagonist, used for the treatment of schizophrenia.

Name: HMN-214
Information: HMN-214 is a prodrug of HMN-176, which alters the cellular spatial orientation of Plk1.

Name: Naratriptan HCl
Information: Naratriptan HCl is a triptan agent that is used for the treatment of migraine headaches.

Name: Ponatinib (AP24534)
Information: Ponatinib (AP24534) is a novel, potent multi-target inhibitor of Abl, PDGFRα, VEGFR2, FGFR1 and Src with IC50 of 0.37 nM, 1.1 nM, 1.5 nM, 2.2 nM and 5.4 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Fludarabine
Information: Fludarabine is a STAT1 activation inhibitor which causes a specific depletion of STAT1 protein (and mRNA) but not of other STATs. Also a DNA synthesis inhibitor in vascular smooth muscle cells.

Name: Pralatrexate
Information: Pralatrexate  is an antifolate, and structurally a folate analog. Its IC50 is < 300 nM in some cell lines.

Name: Cefaclor
Information: Cefaclor is a cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Betamethasone
Information: Betamethasone is a glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties.

Name: Mycophenolate Mofetil
Information: Mycophenolate Mofetil is a non-competitive, selective and reversible inhibitor of inosine monophosphate dehydrogenase I/II with IC50 of 39 nM and 27 nM, respectively.

Name: Dyphylline
Information: Dyphylline is a xanthine derivative with bronchodilator and vasodilator effects.

Name: Aztreonam
Information: Aztreonam is a synthetic monocyclic beta-lactam antibiotic, used to treat Gram-negative aerobic bacteria infection.

Name: Alprostadil
Information: Alprostadil is used as a drug in the treatment of erectile dysfunction and has vasodilatory properties. It is a Prostaglandin Analog and Prostaglandin E1 Agonist.

Name: Lactulose
Information: Lactulose, a disaccharide composed of galactose and fructose, is a stimulator of health-promoting bacterium growth in the gastrointestinal tract, used to treat chronic constipation and hepatic encephalopathy.

Name: Tadalafil
Information: Tadalafil is a PDE-5 inhibitor with IC50 of 1.8 nM in a cell-free assay. Tadalafil is at least 9000 times more selective for PDE5 than most of the other families of PDEs, with the exception of PDE11. It can partial inhibits PDE11

Name: Cyclosporine
Information: Cyclosporine is a calcineurin phosphatase pathway inhibitor, used as an immunosuppressant drug to prevent rejection in organ transplantation.

Name: Natamycin
Information: Natamycin, a natural and versatile anti-fungal agent during fermentation by the bacterium Streptomyces natalensis, commonly found in soil with little to no flavour interference

Name: Quizartinib (AC220)
Information: Quizartinib (AC220) is a second-generation FLT3 inhibitor for Flt3(ITD/WT) with IC50 of 1.1 nM/4.2 nM in MV4-11 and RS411 cells, respectively, 10-fold more selective for Flt3 than KIT, PDGFRα, PDGFRβ, RET, and CSF-1R. Phase 3.

Name: Telaprevir (VX-950)
Information: Telaprevir (VX-950) is an HCV NS3-4A serine protease inhibitor with IC50 of 0.35 μM.

Name: Saxagliptin
Information: Saxagliptin is a selective and reversible DPP4 inhibitor with IC50 of 26 nM.

Name: Febuxostat
Information: Febuxostat is a selective xanthine oxidase inhibitor with Ki of 0.6 nM.

Name: Dapagliflozin
Information: Dapagliflozin is a potent and selective hSGLT2 inhibitor with EC50 of 1.1 nM, exhibiting 1200-fold selectivity over hSGLT1. Phase 4.

Name: Nebivolol HCl
Information: Nebivolol HCl selectively inhibits β1-adrenoceptor with IC50 of 0.8 nM.

Name: Pimobendan
Information: Pimobendan is a selective inhibitor of PDE3 with IC50 of 0.32 μM.

Name: ABT-492(Delafloxacin, RX-3341, WQ-3034)
Information: ABT-492 is a new fluoroquinolone against 155 aerobic and 171 anaerobic pathogens.

Name: VX-809 (Lumacaftor)
Information: VX-809 (Lumacaftor) acts to correct CFTR mutations common in cystic fibrosis by increasing mutant CFTR (F508del-CFTR) maturation,EC50 of 0.1 μM in fisher rat thyroid cells. Phase 3.

Name: Pomalidomide
Information: Pomalidomide inhibits LPS-induced TNF-α release with IC50 of 13 nM in PBMCs.

Name: Tazarotene
Information: Tazarotene is a retinoid prodrug of tazarotenic acid, which is a RAR agonist, used to treat psoriasis, acne, and sun damaged skin.

Name: Fasudil (HA-1077) HCl
Information: Fasudil(HA-1077), a potent and selective inhibitor of Rho kinase, displays less potent inhibiton over PKA, PKG, PKC and MLCK with Ki of 1.6, 1.6, 3.3, and 36 μM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Sulfasalazine
Information: Sulfasalazine is a sulfa derivative of mesalazine, used as an anti-inflammatory agent to treat bowel disease and rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Candesartan
Information: Candesartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.26 nM.

Name: Bestatin
Information: Bestatin is a potent aminopeptidase-B and leukotriene (LT) A4 hydrolase inhibitor, used in the treatment of acute myelocytic leukemia.

Name: Apixaban
Information: Apixaban is a highly selective, reversible inhibitor of Factor Xa with Ki of 0.08 nM and 0.17 nM in human and rabbit, respectively.

Name: Reserpine
Information: Reserpine is an inhibitor of multidrug efflux pumps, used as an antipsychotic and antihypertensive drug.

Name: Furosemide
Information: Furosemide is a potent NKCC2 (Na-K-2Cl symporter) inhibitor, used in the treatment of congestive heart failure and edema.

Name: Olmesartan Medoxomil
Information: Olmesartan Medoxomil (CS-866) is a selective angiotensin II type 1 (AT(1)) receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of high blood pressure.

Name: Cefdinir
Information: Cefdinir is an oral cephalosporin antibiotic, used to treat bacterial infections in many different parts of the body.

Name: Clotrimazole
Information: Clotrimazole alters the permeability of the fungal cell wall by inhibiting the biosynthesis of ergosterol, used in the treatment of fungal infections.

Name: Rizatriptan Benzoate
Information: Rizatriptan Benzoate is an agonist at serotonin 5-HT1B and 5-HT1D receptors, used to treat acute migraine attacks.

Name: Pyridostigmine Bromide
Information: Pyridostigmine Bromide is a parasympathomimetic and a reversible cholinesterase inhibitor.

Name: Methimazole
Information: Methimazole  is an antithyroid medicine.

Name: Metolazone
Information: Metolazone is a diuretic that primarily used to treat congestive heart failure and high blood pressure.

Name: Cefoperazone
Information: Cefoperazone is a cephalosporin antibiotic for inhibition of rMrp2-mediated [3H]E217βG uptake with IC50 of 199 μM.

Name: Silodosin
Information: Silodosin is a highly selective α1A-adrenoceptor antagonist, used in treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: Riluzole
Information: Riluzole is a glutamate release inhibitor with neuroprotective, anticonvulsant, anxiolytic and anesthetic qualities.

Name: Sulfameter
Information: Sulfameter  is a long-acting sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Prilocaine
Information: Prilocaine is a local anesthetic of the amino amide type. It acts on sodium channels on the neuronal cell membrane, limiting the spread of seizure activity and reducing seizure propagation.

Name: Darunavir Ethanolate
Information: Darunavir Ethanolate (DRV) is a nonpeptidic HIV protease inhibitor, used to treat HIV infection.

Name: Prednisone
Information: Prednisone (Adasone) is a synthetic corticosteroid agent that is particularly effective as an immunosuppressant compound.

Name: Acetylcysteine
Information: Acetylcysteine(N-acetyl-l-cysteine) is a ROS(reactive oxygen species) inhibitor that antagonizes the activity of proteasome inhibitors. It is also a tumor necrosis factor production inhibitor, used mainly as a mucolytic, protects against acetaminophen overdose-induced hepatotoxicity by maintaining or restoring hepatic concentrations of glutathione.

Name: Ethinyl Estradiol
Information: Ethinyl Estradiol is an orally bio-active estrogen used in almost all modern formulations of combined oral contraceptive pills.

Name: Naproxen Sodium
Information: Naproxen Sodium is a COX inhibitor for COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 8.7 μM and 5.2 μM, respectively.

Name: Nitazoxanide
Information: Nitazoxanide is a synthetic nitrothiazolyl-salicylamide derivative and an antiprotozoal agent. (IC50 for canine influenza virus ranges from 0.17 to 0.21 μM)

Name: Triamcinolone Acetonide
Information: Triamcinolone acetonide is a synthetic glucocorticoid, used in the symptomatic treatment of inflammation.

Name: Orlistat
Information: Orlistat is a general lipase inhibitor with IC50 of 122 ng/ml for PL from human duodenal juice.

Name: Allopurinol
Information: Allopurinol is a purine analog inhibitor of the enzyme xanthine oxidase, used to treat gout or kidney stones, and to decrease levels of uric acid.

Name: Allopurinol Sodium
Information: Allopurinol Sodium  is a xanthine oxidase inhibitor with an IC50 of 7.82±0.12 μM.

Name: Zafirlukast
Information: Zafirlukast is an oral leukotriene receptor antagonist (LTRA), used to prevent asthma symptoms.

Name: Erythromycin
Information: Erythromycin is a macrolide antibiotic that has an antimicrobial spectrum similar to or slightly wider than that of penicillin (IC50=1.5 μg/ml).

Name: Amphotericin B
Information: Amphotericin B (AmB) is an amphipathic polyene antibiotic which permeabilizes ergosterol-containing membranes.

Name: Ibuprofen
Information: Ibuprofen (Dolgesic) is an anti-inflammatory inhibitor targeting COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 13 μM and 370 μM, respectively.

Name: Amprenavir
Information: Amprenavir is a potent PXR-selective agonist, and an HIV protease inhibitor, used to treat HIV.

Name: Albendazole
Information: Albendazole is a member of the benzimidazole compounds used as a drug indicated for the treatment of a variety of worm infestations.

Name: Chlorothiazide
Information: Chlorothiazide is a diuretic and antihypertensive. (IC50=3.8 mM)

Name: Ursodiol
Information: Ursodiol reduces cholesterol absorption and is used to dissolve (cholesterol) gallstones. (IC50=0.22 μM)

Name: Nitrofural
Information: Nitrofural is a topical anti-infective agent with an IC50 of 22.83 ± 1.2 μM. (Rat LD50 = 590 mg/kg)

Name: Ketoprofen
Information: Ketoprofen is a dual COX1/2 inhibitor, used as a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug to treat arthritis-related inflammatory pains.

Name: Ketorolac
Information: Ketorolac (Ketorolac tromethamine) is a non-selective COX inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 with IC50 of 1.23 μM and 3.50 μM, respectively.

Name: Adenosine
Information: Adenosine is a nucleoside composed of a molecule of adenine attached to a ribose sugar molecule (ribofuranose) moiety via a β-N9-glycosidic bond.

Name: Zolmitriptan
Information: Zolmitriptan is a novel and highly selective 5-HT(1B/1D) receptor agonist, used in the treatment of acute migraines.

Name: Telbivudine
Information: Telbivudine is a potent, and selective HBV reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used to treat HBV infection.

Name: Monobenzone
Information: Monobenzone is a compound used as a topical agent for medical depigmentation. It can specifically block tyrosinase.

Name: Tretinoin
Information: Tretinoin, which is a ligand for both the retinoic acid receptor (RAR) and the retinoid X receptor (RXR), can induce granulocytic differentiation and apoptosis in acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL) cells.

Name: Phenylbutazone
Information: Phenylbutazone is used as a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent for the treatment of chronic pain, including the symptoms of arthritis.

Name: Ezetimibe
Information: Ezetimibe is a potent, selective, cholesterol absorption inhibitor, used to lower cholesterol.

Name: Enalaprilat Dihydrate
Information: Enalaprilat is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor with IC50 of 1.94 nM.

Name: Dofetilide
Information: Dofetilide is a selective potassium channel ((hERG)) blocker, used as a Class III antiarrhythmic drug.

Name: Isradipine
Information: Isradipine is a potent and selective L-type voltage-gated calcium channel blocker, used to treat high blood pressure.

Name: Estrone
Information: Estrone is an estrogenic hormone.

Name: Flucytosine
Information: Flucytosine (5-Fluorocytosine, 5-FC) is an antifungal drug with IC50 of 0.93 μM in C. albicans.

Name: Trichlormethiazide
Information: Trichlormethiazide is a diuretic with properties similar to those of hydrochlorothiazide.

Name: Loteprednol etabonate
Information: Loteprednol etabonate is a potent glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used in treatment of inflammation of the eye due to allergies.

Name: Aminophylline
Information: Aminophylline is a competitive nonselective phosphodiesterase inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.12 mM and also a nonselective adenosine receptor antagonist.

Name: Lubiprostone
Information: Lubiprostone is an activator of ClC-2 chloride channels, used in the management of idiopathic chronic constipation.

Name: Amorolfine HCl
Information: Amorolfine HCl is an antifungal reagent.

Name: Chloramphenicol
Information: Chloramphenicol is a bacteriostatic by inhibiting protein synthesis.

Name: Flurbiprofen
Information: Flurbiprofen is a member of the phenylalkanoic acid derivative family of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs).

Name: Disulfiram
Information: Disulfiram is  a specific inhibitor of aldehyde-dehydrogenase (ALDH1), used for the treatment of chronic alcoholism by producing an acute sensitivity to alcohol.

Name: Mesalamine
Information: Mesalamine is a specific inhibitor of TNFα-induced IKK activity, used to treat inflammatory bowel disease.

Name: Ipratropium Bromide
Information: Ipratropium Bromide is an antagonist of M3 type muscarinic acetylcholine receptors, used for the treatment of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

Name: Sulfanilamide
Information: Sulfanilamide (Sulphanilamide) is a competitive inhibitor for bacterial enzyme dihydropteroate synthetase with IC50 of 320 μM.

Name: Betamethasone Dipropionate
Information: Betamethasone Dipropionate is a glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive abilities.

Name: Meprednisone
Information: Meprednisone is a glucocorticoid and a methylated derivative of prednisone.

Name: Betamethasone Valerate
Information: Betamethasone Valerate is a moderately potent glucocorticoid steroid with anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive properties.

Name: Praziquantel
Information: Praziquantel is an anthelmintic effective against flatworms.

Name: Busulfan
Information: Busulfan is a cell cycle non-specific alkylating antineoplastic agent.

Name: Carbamazepine
Information: Carbamazepine (Carbatrol) is a sodium channel blocker with IC50 of 131 μM in rat brain synaptosomes.

Name: Hydrocortisone
Information: Hydrocortisone is a steroid hormone or glucocorticoid produced by the adrenal gland.

Name: Desonide
Information: Desonide is a low potency topical corticosteroid.

Name: Didanosine
Information: Didanosine is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.49 μM.

Name: Divalproex Sodium
Information: Divalproex Sodium, consisting of a compound of sodium valproate and valproic acid in a 1:1 molar relationship in an enteric coated form, is a HDAC inhibitor, used in the treatment for epilepsy.

Name: Emtricitabine
Information: Emtricitabine (FTC) is a new nucleoside agent that has activity against both human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) and hepatitis B virus. It is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor. Intracellular half-life is 39 h.

Name: Progesterone
Information: Progesterone is an endogenous steroid hormone involved in the menstrual cycle, pregnancy, and embryogenesis of humans and other species. A potent agonist of the nuclear progesterone receptor (nPR) with Kd of 1 nM An agonist of the membrane progesterone receptors(mPRs) An antagonist of the σ1 receptor.

Name: Lamivudine
Information: Lamivudine is a potent nucleoside analog reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used for treatment of chronic HBV and HIV/AIDS. It works by blocking the HIV reverse transcriptase and hepatitis B virus polymerase.

Name: Estradiol
Information: Estradiol, or more precisely, 17β-estradiol, is a human sex hormone and steroid, and the primary female sex hormone.

Name: Deferasirox
Information: Deferasirox is an iron chelator, also a cytochrome P450 3A4 inducer, Cytochrome P450 2C8 inhibitor, and Cytochrome P450 1A2 inhibitor.

Name: Piroxicam
Information: Piroxicam is a non-selective COX inhibitor, used in the treatment of rheumatoid and osteoarthritis.

Name: Gemcitabine
Information: Gemcitabine, a nucleic acid synthesis inhibitor, is a very potent and specific deoxycytidine analogue, used as chemotherapy.

Name: Glipizide
Information: Glipizide is used to treat high blood sugar levels caused by a type of diabetes mellitus called type 2 diabetes.

Name: Glyburide (Glibenclamide)
Information: Glyburide (Glibenclamide) is a known blocker of vascular ATP-sensitive K+ channels (KATP), used in the treatment of type 2 diabetes.

Name: Fomepizole
Information: Fomepizole is a competitive inhibitor of alcohol dehydrogenase, the enzyme that catalyzes the initial steps in the metabolism of ethylene glycol and methanol to their toxic metabolites.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Adefovir Dipivoxil
Information: Adefovir Dipivoxil is a reverse transcriptase inhibitor, used in the treatment of chronic hepatitis B virus (HBV).

Name: Zalcitabine
Information: Zalcitabine is a nucleoside analog HIV reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NARTI).

Name: Azathioprine
Information: Azathioprine is an immunosuppressive drug, inhibiting purine synthesis and GTP-binding protein Rac1 activation, used in the treatment of organ transplantation and autoimmune diseases.

Name: Indomethacin
Information: Indomethacin is a nonselective COX1 and COX2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.1 μg/mL and 5 μg/mL, respectively, used to reduce fever, pain, stiffness, and swelling.

Name: Terbinafine
Information: Terbinafine is used to treat infections caused by a fungus. It works by killing the fungus or preventing its growth.

Name: Levonorgestrel
Information: Levonorgestrel is a female hormone that prevents ovulation.

Name: Gemfibrozil
Information: Gemfibrozil is an activator of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-alpha (PPARα), used for the treatment of hypercholesterolemia and hypertriglyceridemia.

Name: Indapamide
Information: Indapamide is a non-thiazide sulphonamide diuretic compound, generally used in the treatment of hypertension, as well as decompensated cardiac failure.

Name: Mitotane
Information: Mitotane, is an antineoplastic medication used in the treatment of adrenocortical carcinoma.

Name: Methylprednisolone
Information: Methylprednisolone is a synthetic glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used to achieve prompt suppression of inflammation.

Name: Meloxicam
Information: Meloxicam is a selective COX inhibitor, used to relieve pain and fever effects.

Name: Mesna
Information: Mesna, a sulfhydryl compound that is used to reduce the incidence of hemorrhagic cystitis associated with certain chemotherapeutic agents.

Name: Methocarbamol
Information: Methocarbamol is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, used as a central muscle relaxant to treat skeletal muscle spasms.

Name: Prednisolone
Information: Prednisolone is a synthetic glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory and immunomodulating properties.

Name: Telmisartan
Information: Telmisartan  is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist (ARB) used in the management of hypertension.

Name: Thiabendazole
Information: Thiabendazole inhibits the mitochondrial helminth-specific enzyme, fumarate reductase, with anthelminthic property, used as an anthelmintic and fungicide agent. It is a potent inhibitor of  cytochrome P450 1A2 (CYP1A2).

Name: Guaifenesin
Information: Guaifenesin is an expectorant used to relieve chest congestion.

Name: Rifabutin
Information: Rifabutin is a semisynthetic ansamycin antibiotic, used in the treatment of Mycobacterium avium intracellulare (MAI) and tuberculosis.

Name: Nevirapine
Information: Nevirapine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) used to treat HIV-1 infection and AIDS.

Name: NEXIUM (esomeprazole magnesium)
Information: Esomeprazole Magnesium is a proton pump inhibitor to reduce gastric acid secretion.

Name: Nicotinic Acid
Information: Nicotinic Acid is a water-soluble vitamin belonging to the vitamin B family.

Name: Nimodipine
Information: Nimodipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker and an autophagy inhibitor, used in the treatment of high blood pressure.

Name: Nisoldipine
Information: Nisoldipine (Sular) is a calcium channel blocker belonging to the dihydropyridines class, specific for L-type Cav1.2 with IC50 of 10 nM.

Name: Octocrylene
Information: Octocrylene is an organic compound used as an ingredient in sunscreens and cosmetics.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Oxybutynin
Information: Oxybutynin is a competitive antagonist of the M1, M2, and M3 subtypes of the muscarinic acetylcholine receptor, used to relieve urinary and bladder difficulties.

Name: Enoxacin
Information: Enoxacin is an oral broad-spectrum fluoroquinolone antibacterial agent by inhibiting bacterial DNA gyrase and topoisomerase IV, used to treat a wide variety of infections.

Name: Pitavastatin Calcium
Information: Pitavastatin calcium, a novel member of the medication class of statins, is a calcium salt formulation of pitavastatin which is a highly effective HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor.

Name: Rifapentine
Information: Rifapentine is an antibiotic, which inhibits DNA-dependent RNA polymerase activity, used to treat tuberculosis.

Name: Suprofen
Information: Suprofen is a dual COX-1/COX-2 inhibitor, used as a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory analgesic and antipyretic.

Name: Pyrazinamide
Information: Pyrazinamide is an agent used to treat tuberculosis.

Name: Quetiapine Fumarate
Information: Quetiapine Fumarate is an atypical antipsychotic used in the treatment of schizophrenia, bipolar I mania, bipolar II depression, bipolar I depression and shows affinity for various neurotransmitter receptors including serotonin, dopamine, histamine, and adrenergic receptors.

Name: Rifampin
Information: Rifampin is a DNA-dependent RNA polymerase inhibitor, used to treat a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Cefditoren Pivoxil
Information: Cefditoren Pivoxil is a broad-spectrum antibiotic against Gram-negative and Gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Sulfadiazine
Information: Sulfadiazine is a sulfonamide antibiotic.

Name: Chlorprothixene
Information: Chlorprothixene has strong binding affinities to dopamine and histamine receptors, such as D1, D2, D3, D5, H1, 5-HT2, 5-HT6 and 5-HT7, with Ki of 18 nM, 2.96 nM, 4.56 nM, 9 nM, 3.75 nM, 9.4 nM, 3 nM and 5.6 nM, respectively.

Name: Oxytetracycline (Terramycin)
Information: Oxytetracycline is a broad-spectrum tetracycline antibiotic, used to treat infections with bacteria.

Name: Thioguanine
Information: Thioguanine, a purine antimetabolite, inhibits DNMT1 activity through ubiquitin-targeted degradation, used in the treatment of acute lymphoblastic leukemia, autoimmune disorders (e.g., Crohn's disease, rheumatoid arthritis) and organ transplant recipients.

Name: Thiotepa
Information: Thiotepa(Thioplex) is an alkylating agent used to treat cancer.

Name: Toremifene Citrate
Information: Toremifene Citrate is an oral selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM), used in the treatment of advanced breast cancer.

Name: Ethionamide
Information: Ethionamide is an antibiotic used in the treatment of tuberculosis.

Name: Trifluridine
Information: Trifluridine is an anti-herpesvirus antiviral agent by interacting viral DNA replication, used primarily on the eye.

Name: Azacitidine
Information: Azacitidine is a nucleoside analogue of cytidine that specifically inhibits DNA methylation by trapping DNA methyltransferases.

Name: Vidarabine
Information: Vidarabine is an antiviral drug by interfering with the synthesis of viral DNA, used to treat herpes simplex and varicella zoster viruses.

Name: Verteporfin
Information: Verteporfin is a small molecule that inhibits TEAD–YAP association and YAP-induced liver overgrowth.  It is also a potent second-generation photosensitizing agent derived from porphyrin.

Name: Teniposide
Information: Teniposide is a chemotherapeutic medication mainly used in the treatment of childhood acute lymphocytic leukemia (ALL).

Name: Tetrabenazine (Xenazine)
Information: Tetrabenazine(Nitoman, Xenazine) acts primarily as a reversible high-affinity inhibitor of mono-amine uptake into granular vesicles of presynaptic neurons by binding selectively to VMAT-2 Also blocks dopamine D2 receptors, but this affinity is 1,000-fold lower than its affinity for VMAT-2.

Name: Rifaximin

Name: Fenofibrate

Name: Ranolazine

Name: Acetylcholine Chloride

Information: Mestranol is the 3-methyl ether of ethinyl estradiol, which is a potent estrogen receptor agonist and used as oral contraceptives.

Name: Naftopidil
Information: Naftopidil is a selective α1-adrenergic receptor antagonist with Ki of 3.7 nM, 20 nM, and 1.2 nM for α1a, α1b, and α1d, respectively, used for the treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: S- (+)-Rolipram
Information: S-(+)-Rolipram inhibits human monocyte cyclic AMP-specific PDE4 with IC50 of 0.75 μM, has anti-inflammatory and anti-depressant activity in the central nervous system, less potent than its R enantiomer.

Name: Bazedoxifene HCl
Information: Bazedoxifene HCl is a novel, non-steroidal, indole-based estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) binding to both ERα and ERβ with IC50 of  23 nM and 89 nM, respectively.

Name: Atropine sulfate monohydrate
Information: Atropine sulfate monohydrate is a competitive antagonist for the muscarinic acetylcholine receptor, used to decrease the production of saliva and secretions of the airway prior to surgery.

Name: Roflumilast
Information: Roflumilast is a selective inhibitor of PDE4 with IC50 of 0.2-4.3 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Sonidegib (Erismodegib, NVP-LDE225)
Information: Sonidegib (Erismodegib, NVP-LDE225) is a Smoothened (Smo) antagonist, inhibiting Hedgehog (Hh) signaling with IC50 of 1.3 nM (mouse) and 2.5 nM (human) in cell-free assays, respectively. Phase 3.

Name: Dabigatran Etexilate
Information: Dabigatran Etexilate is the prodrug of dabigatran, a potent, nonpeptidic small molecule that specifically and reversibly inhibits both free and clot-bound thrombin by binding to the active site of the thrombin molecule.

Name: Tebipenem Pivoxil
Information: Tebipenem pivoxil is an oral carbapenem antibiotic, use to treat otolaryngologic and respiratory infections.

Name: Bazedoxifene Acetate
Information: Bazedoxifene Acetate is a third generation selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM).

Name: Rosuvastatin Calcium
Information: Rosuvastatin Calcium is a competitive inhibitor of HMG-CoA reductase with IC50 of 11 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Telotristat Etiprate (LX 1606 Hippurate)
Information: Telotristat Etiprate (LX 1606 Hippurate) is an orally bioavailable, tryptophan hydroxylase (TPH) inhibitor with potential antiserotonergic activity. Phase 3.

Name: Dichlorphenamide (Diclofenamide)
Information: Dichlorphenamide is a sulfonamide and a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor of the meta-Disulfamoylbenzene class.

Name: Ixazomib (MLN2238)
Information: MLN2238 inhibits the chymotrypsin-like proteolytic (β5) site of the 20S proteasome with IC50 and Ki of 3.4 nM and 0.93 nM in cell-free assays, respectively, also inhibits the caspase-like (β1) and trypsin-like (β2) proteolytic sites, with IC50 of 31 and 3500 nM. Phase 3.

Name: Ixazomib Citrate (MLN9708)
Information: Ixazomib Citrate (MLN9708) immediately hydrolyzed to MLN2238, the biologically active form, on exposure to aqueous solutions or plasma. MLN2238 inhibits the chymotrypsin-like proteolytic (β5) site of the 20S proteasome with IC50/Ki of 3.4 nM/0.93 nM in cell-free assays, less potent to β1 and little activity to β2. Phase 3.

Name: Phenprocoumon
Information: Phenprocoumon(Marcumar) is a vitamin K reductase with an IC50 of 1 μM

Name: Aliskiren Hemifumarate
Information: Aliskiren hemifumarate is a direct renin inhibitor with IC50 of 1.5 nM.

Name: Formestane
Information: Formestane is a second generation selective aromatase inhibitor with an IC50 of 80 nM.

Name: Irinotecan HCl Trihydrate
Information: Irinotecan prevents DNA from unwinding by inhibition of topoisomerase 1.

Name: Idelalisib (CAL-101, GS-1101)
Information: Idelalisib (CAL-101, GS-1101) is a selective p110δ inhibitor with IC50 of 2.5 nM in cell-free assays shown to have 40- to 300-fold greater selectivity for p110δ than p110α/β/γ, and 400- to 4000-fold more selectivity to p110δ than C2β, hVPS34, DNA-PK and mTOR.

Name: Eltrombopag Olamine
Information: Eltrombopag Olamine is a member of the biarylhydrazone class, which is a nonpeptide agonist of the thrombopoietin receptor (TpoR).

Name: Esomeprazole sodium
Information: Esomeprazole Sodium is a sodium salt of esomeprazole that is a potent proton pump inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.076 mg/kg.

Name: Abiraterone Acetate
Information: Abiraterone Acetate is an acetate salt form of Abiraterone which is a steroidal cytochrome CYP17 inhibitor with IC50 of 72 nM in a cell-free assay.

Name: (-)-Epigallocatechin Gallate
Information: (-)-Epigallocatechin Gallate(EGCG) is the main catechin extraction of green tea that inhibits telomerase and DNA methyltransferase. EGCG blocks the activation of EGF receptors and HER-2 receptors. ECGG inhibits fatty acid synthase and glutamate dehydrogenase activity.

Name: 4-Methylumbelliferone (4-MU)
Information: 4-Methylumbelliferone is a hyaluronic acid (HA) synthesis inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.4 mM.

Name: Esculin
Information: Esculin is a glucoside found in horse chestnuts.

Name: Amygdalin
Information: Amygdalin is a glycoside initially isolated from the seeds of the tree Prunus dulcis, also known as bitter almonds.

Name: Andrographolide
Information: Andrographolide is a labdane diterpenoid that is the main bioactive component of the medicinal plant Andrographis paniculata.

Name: Apigenin
Information: Apigenin is a potent P450 inhibitor for CYP2C9 with Ki of 2 μM.

Name: Arbutin
Information: Arbutin is a tyrosinase inhibitor with an IC50 of 1.09 mM.

Name: Artemether
Information: Artemether is an antimalarial for the treatment of resistant strains of falciparum malaria.

Name: Artesunate
Information: Artesunate is a part of the artemisinin group of agents with an IC50 of < 5 μM for small cell lung carcinoma cell line H69. It is a potential inhibitor of STAT-3 and exhibits selective cytotoxicity of cancer cells over normal cells in vitro A potent inhibitor of EXP1.

Name: Asiatic Acid
Information: Asiatic acid is the aglycone of asiaticoside isolated from the plant Centella asiatica, commonly used in wound healing.

Name: Baicalein
Information: Baicalein is a CYP2C9 and prolyl endopeptidase inhibitor.

Name: Baicalin
Information: Baicalin is a known prolyl endopeptidase inhibitor and affects the GABA receptors.

Name: Bergenin
Information: Bergenin is trihydroxybenzoic acid glycoside and the C-glycoside of 4-O-methyl gallic acid.

Name: Berberine chloride
Information: Berberine chloride is a quaternary ammonium salt from the group of isoquinoline alkaloids.

Name: Caffeic Acid
Information: Caffeic acid is a hydroxycinnamic acid, a naturally occurring organic compound.

Name: Chlorogenic Acid
Information: Chlorogenic acid is a hydroxycinnamic acid and a member of a family of naturally occurring organic compounds.

Name: Cinchonidine
Information: Cinchonidine is an alkaloid used in asymmetric synthesis in organic chemistry.

Name: Cinchonine(LA40221)
Information: Cinchonine is an alkaloid and a stereoisomer and pseudo-enantiomer of cinchonidine.

Name: Colchicine
Information: Colchicine is a microtubule polymerization inhibitor with an IC50 of 3 nM.

Name: Cyclosporin A
Status: FDA, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Pharmacopoeia: Martindale the Extra Pharmacopoei, EP10.2, USP43-NF38, Ph.Int_6th, JP17
Information: Cyclosporin A is an immunosuppressive agent, binds to the cyclophilin and then inhibits calcineurin with IC50 of 7 nM in a cell-free assay, widely used in organ transplantation to prevent rejection.

Name: Cytisine
Information: Cytisine is a nicotinic acetylcholine receptor agonist.

Name: Daidzin
Information: Daidzin, a natural organic compound in the class of phytochemicals known as isoflavones, is a potent and selective inhibitor of human mitochondrial aldehyde dehydrogenase and inhibits ALDH-I selectively (Ki=20 nM) at least 500 times less effective against ALDH-Ⅱ, the cytosolic isozyme (Ki=10 μM).

Name: Dihydroartemisinin (DHA)
Information: Dihydroartemisinin (DHA) is a semi-synthetic derivative of artemisinin and isolated from the traditional Chinese herb Artemisia annua.

Name: DL-Carnitine HCl
Information: DL-Carnitine HCl is a quaternary ammonium compound biosynthesized from the amino acids lysine and methionine.

Name: Emodin
Information: Emodin is a purgative resin, 6-methyl-1,3,8-trihydroxyanthraquinone, from rhubarb, the buckthorn and Japanese Knotweed (Fallopia japonica).

Name: Enoxolone
Information: Enoxolone is a pentacyclic triterpenoid derivative of the beta-amyrin type obtained from the hydrolysis of glycyrrhizic acid, which was obtained from the herb liquorice.

Name: Formononetin
Information: Formononetin is a phytoestrogen from the root of Astragalus membranaceus and an O-methylated isoflavone.

Name: Ferulic Acid
Information: Ferulic Acid is a hydroxycinnamic acid and a type of organic compound found in the Ferula assafoetida L. or Ligusticum chuanxiong.

Name: Glycyrrhizin (Glycyrrhizic Acid)
Information: Glycyrrhizin (Glycyrrhizic Acid) is a direct HMGB1(high mobility group box 1) inhibitor that inhibits HMGB1-dependent inflammatory molecule expression and oxidative stress modulates P38 and P-JNK but not p-ERK signalling Also inhibits 11 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and monoamine oxidase (MAO).

Name: gossypol-Acetic acid
Information: Gossypol Acetate is a polyphenolic aldehyde that permeates cells and acts as an inhibitor for several dehydrogenase enzymes such as lactate dehydrogenase, NAD-linked enzymes.

Name: Gramine
Information: Gramine is a naturally occurring indole alkaloid present in several plant species.

Name: Hesperetin
Information: Hesperetin is a bioflavonoid and, to be more specific, a flavanone.

Name: Hesperidin
Information: Hesperidin is a flavanone glycoside found abundantly in citrus fruits.

Name: Honokiol
Information: Honokiol is the active principle of magnolia extract that inhibits Akt-phosphorylation and promotes ERK1/2 phosphorylation. Phase 3.

Name: Hyodeoxycholic acid (HDCA)
Information: Hyodeoxycholic(HDCA) acid is a secondary bile acid, one of the metabolic byproducts of intestinal bacteria.

Name: Kaempferol
Information: Kaempferol, a natural flavonol, functions as an ERRα and ERRγ inverse agonist. It inhibits topoisomerase I catalyzed DNA religation and may also inhibit the activity of fatty acid synthase.

Name: Kinetin
Information: Kinetin is a type of cytokinin, a class of plant hormone that promotes cell division.

Name: L-(+)-Rhamnose Monohydrate
Information: L(+)-Rhamnose (Rham) is a naturally-occurring deoxy sugar that is found primarily in plants and some bacteria.

Name: Lappaconitine
Information: Lappaconitine (LC) is a natural diterpenoid alkaloid (DTA), acting as a human heart sodium channel blocker and possessing a wide range of biological activities, including anti-arrhythmic, anti-inflammatory, antioxidative, anticancer, epileptiform etc.

Name: Luteolin
Information: Luteolin is a flavonoid found in Terminalia chebula, which is a non-selective phisphodiesterase PDE inhibitor for PDE1-5 with Ki of 15.0 &muM, 6.4 &muM, 13.9 &muM, 11.1 &muM and 9.5 &muM, respectively. Phase 2.

Name: Magnolol
Information: Magnolol is a bioactive lignin found in the bark of the Houpu magnolia (Magnolia officinalis) which shows antifungal properties. It can block TNF-α-induced NF-KB activation.

Name: (+)-Matrine
Information: Matrine((+)-Matrine) is an alkaloid found in plants from the Sophora family, which has a variety of pharmacological effects, including anti-cancer effects, and action as a kappa opioid receptor agonist.

Name: Morin Hydrate
Information: Morin hydrate(Aurantica) is a flavonoid isolated from Maclura pomifera (Osage orange), Maclura tinctoria (old fustic) and from leaves of Psidium guajava (common guava).

Name: Nalidixic acid
Information: Nalidixic acid is a synthetic 1,8-naphthyridine antimicrobial agent with a limited bacteriocidal spectrum. It is an inhibitor of the A subunit of bacterial DNA gyrase.

Name: Naringin
Information: Naringin is a flavanone glycoside, which exerts a variety of pharmacological effects such as antioxidant activity, blood lipid lowering, anticancer activity, and inhibition of cytochrome P450 enzymes.

Name: Neohesperidin Dihydrochalcone (Nhdc)
Information: Neohesperidin dihydrochalcone(Nhdc), sometimes abbreviated to neohesperidin DC or simply NHDC, is an artificial sweetener derived from citrus.

Name: Neohesperidin
Information: Neohesperidin, a flavanone glycoside found in citrus fruits, is an antioxidant agent.

Name: Oleanolic Acid
Information: Oleanolic Acid is a non-toxic, hepatoprotective triterpenoid found in Phytolacca Americana, which exerts antitumor and antiviral properties.

Name: Orotic acid (6-Carboxyuracil)
Information: Orotic acid(6-Carboxyuracil) is a heterocyclic compound and an acid.

Name: Osthole
Information: Osthol is an O-methylated coumarin, which is found in the plants such as Cnidium monnieri, Angelica archangelica and Angelica pubescens.

Name: Oxymatrine
Information: Oxymatrine is a quinolizidine alkaloid extracted from the root of Sophora flavescens with anti-inflammatory, antifibrosis, and antitumor effects, inhibits the iNOS expression and TGF-β/Smad pathway. It is used for the treatment of viral hepatitis, cancer, viral myocarditis, gastrointestinal hemorrhage and skin diseases.

Name: Paeonol
Information: Paeonol (Peonol), a phenolic compound extracted from Chinese herbs Paeonia suffruticosa (moutan cortex) and Cynanchum paniculatum, inhibits MAO with an IC50 of about 50 &muM.

Name: (-)-Parthenolide
Information: (-)-Parthenolide, an inhibitor of the Nuclear Factor-κB Pathway, specifically depletes HDAC1 protein without affecting other class I/II HDACs Also promotes the ubiquitination of MDM2 and activates p53 cellular functions.

Name: Piperine
Information: Piperine (1-Piperoylpiperidine) is the alkaloid responsible for the pungency of black pepper and long pepper, which has also been used in some forms of traditional medicine and as an insecticide.

Name: Puerarin
Information: Puerarin (Kakonein), an isoflavones found in the root of Radix puerariae, is a 5-HT2C receptor and benzodiazepine site antagonist.

Name: Quercetin Dihydrate
Information: Quercetin, a polyphenolic flavonoid found in a wide variety of plant-based foods, such as apples, onions, berries, and red wine, is utilized in many different cultures for their nervous system and anticancer effects.

Name: Rotenone (Barbasco)
Information: Rotenone is a botanical insecticide that is an inhibitor of mitochondrial electron transport.

Name: Rutaecarpine
Information: Rutaecarpine is an indolopyridoquinazolinone alkaloid isolated from Evodia rutaecarpa and related herbs a new class of COX-2 inhibitor.

Name: Rutin
Information: Rutin, a flavonol glycoside found in many plants including buckwheat tobacco forsythia hydrangea viola, etc., which possesses healthy effects for human.

Name: Salicin
Information: Salicin is a phenol β-glycosid produced from willow bark that shows anti-inflammatory effects. It is a natural, non-selective COX-1 and COX-2 inhibitor.

Name: Sclareol
Information: Sclareol, a labdane-type diterpene isolated from clary sage (Salvia sclarea), exerts growth inhibition and cytotoxic activity against a variety of human cancer cell lines.

Name: Silibinin
Information: Silibinin, the main flavonoid extracted from the milk thistle Silybum marianum, displays hepatoprotective properties in acute and chronic liver injury.

Name: Silymarin
Information: Silymarin (Silybin B), a polyphenolic flavonoid extracted from the seeds of Silybum marianum or milk thistle, is used in the prevention and treatment of liver diseases and primary liver cancer.

Name: Sinomenine
Information: Sinomenine, a pure alkaloid extracted from the chinese medical plant Sinomenium acutum, is used for the treatment of rheumatism and arthritis.

Name: Synephrine
Information: Synephrine, a natural protoalkaloid in the extract of bitter orange and other citrus species, is commonly used for weight loss.

Name: Tanshinone I
Information: Tanshinone I, an active principle isolated from Salvia miltiorrhiza (Danshen), is structurally similar to tanshinone IIA and may possess similar cytotoxic effects on tumor cells.

Name: Tanshinone IIA
Information: Tanshinone IIA(Tanshinone B) is the most abundant diterpene quinone in Danshen, Salviae miltiorrhizae Radix, a widely prescribed traditional herbal medicine that is used to treat cardiovascular and inflammatory diseases A natural monoacylglycerol lipase inhibitor.

Name: Taxifolin (Dihydroquercetin)
Information: Taxifolin, type I inhibitor for VEGFR-2 kinase, is a flavonoid in many plants such as Taxus chinensis, Siberian larch, Cedrus deodara and so on.

Name: Troxerutin
Information: Troxerutin, a natural bioflavonoid isolated from Sophora japonica., has been reported to have many benefits and medicinal properties.

Name: Ursolic Acid
Information: Ursolic acid (Malol) is a pentacyclic triterpene acid, used in cosmetics.

Name: Yohimbine HCl
Information: Yohimbine has been used as a mydriatic and in the treatment of impotence. It is also alleged to be an aphrodisiac.

Name: 5-hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP)
Information: 5-Hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP), also known as oxitriptan (INN), is a naturally occurring amino acid and chemical precursor for the treatment of depression.

Name: Aloin
Information: Aloin, a natural anthracycline from Aloe vera, is a tyrosinase inhibitor.

Name: Ammonium Glycyrrhizinate
Information: Ammonium Glycyrrhizinate inhibits growth and cytopathology of several unrelated DNA and RNA viruses.

Name: Butylscopolamine Bromide
Information: Butylscopolamine Bromide, is a peripherally acting antimuscarinic, anticholinergic agent used as an abdominal-specific antispasmodic.

Name: Dioscin
Information: Dioscin is a saponin extracted and isolated from Polygonatum Zanlanscianense Pamp, showing antitumor activities.

Name: Diosmetin
Information: Diosmetin is a bioflavonoid found in spearmint, oregano, and many other plants.

Name: D-Mannitol
Information: D-Mannitol is an osmotic diuretic agent and a weak renal vasodilator.

Name: Evodiamine
Information: Evodiamine (Isoevodiamine), an alkaloid extract from the fruit of Evodiae Fructus exhibits antitumor activities against the human tumor cells. It is shown to inhibit NF-kB activation through suppression of IkB kinase activity.

Name: Gastrodin
Information: Gastrodin, an anti-inflammatory polyphenol extracted from Chinese natural herbal Gastrodia elata Blume., benefits neurodegenerative diseases.

Name: Hematoxylin
Information: Hematoxylin (Hydroxybrazilin) is a compound that forms strongly colored complexes with certain metal ions, notably Fe(III) and Al(III) salts and a kind of stain in histology.

Name: Indirubin
Information: Indirubin is a potent cyclin-dependent kinases and GSK-3β inhibitor with IC50 of about 5 μM and 0.6 μM.

Name: Lappaconite HBr
Information: Lappaconite Hydrobromide is a kind of alkaloid extracted from Aconitum sinomontanum Nakai and has anti-inflammatory effects.

Name: L-carnitine
Information: L-carnitine  is constituent of striated muscle and liver. It is used therapeutically to stimulate gastric and pancreatic secretions and in the treatment of hyperlipoproteinemias.

Name: Naringin Dihydrochalcone
Information: Naringin Dihydrochalcone(Naringin DC) is a new-style sweetening agent and an artificial sweetener derived from naringin and also an inhibitor of CYP enzymes.

Name: Polydatin
Information: Polydatin is a crystal component extracted from the root stem of perennial herbage Polygonum Cuspidatum Sieb.et Zucc.

Name: Quercetin
Information: Quercetin, a natural flavonoid present in vegetables, fruit and wine, is a stimulator of recombinant SIRT1 and also a PI3K inhibitor with IC50 of 2.4-5.4 μM. Phase 4.

Name: Sorbitol
Information: Sorbitol is a sugar alcohol and a sugar substitute.

Name: Salidroside
Information: Salidroside, a phenylpropanoid glycoside isolated from Rhodiola rosea, has been reported to have a broad spectrum of pharmacological properties.

Name: Palmatine chloride
Information: Palmatine hydrochloride (Palmatine chloride (6CI,7CI) Fibrauretin) is a hydrochloride salt of palmatine which is a protoberberine alkaloid.

Name: Sodium Danshensu
Information: Sodium Danshensu is a mono sodium of danshensu, which is a natural phenolic acid of caffeic acid derivatives isolated from Salvia miltiorrhiza.

Name: Tetrandrine
Information: Tetrandrine, a bis-benzylisoquinoline alkaloid derived from Stephania tetrandra, is a calcium channel blocker.

Name: Paeoniflorin
Information: Paeoniflorin is a herbal constituent extracted from the root of Paeonia albiflora Pall.

Name: Geniposide
Information: Geniposide is an iridoid glycoside isolated from the fruit of Gardenia jasminoides Ellis.

Name: Ipriflavone (Osteofix)
Information: Ipriflavone (7-Isopropoxyisoflavon) is used to inhibit bone resorption.

Name: (S)-10-Hydroxycamptothecin
Information: 10-Hydroxycamptothecin is a DNA topoisomerase I inhibitor with potent anti-tumor activity.

Name: Rotundine
Information: Rotundine (L-tetrahydropalmatine, L-THP) is a selective dopamine D1 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 166 nM.

Name: Synephrine HCl
Information: SynephrineHCl (Oxedrine, p-Synephrine) is a sympathomimetic α-adrenergic receptor (AR) agonist.

Name: Guanosine
Information: Guanosine is a purine nucleoside comprising guanine attached to a ribose (ribofuranose) ring via a &beta-N9-glycosidic bond.

Name: Inosine
Information: Inosine is a nucleoside that is formed when hypoxanthine is attached to a ribose ring via a &beta-N9-glycosidic bond.

Name: Tolbutamide
Information: Tolbutamide is an inhibitor of potassium channel, used for type II diabetes.

Name: Levosimendan
