Name: Tanshinone IIA sulfonate (sodium)
Information: Sodium tanshinone IIA sulfonate (STS) is a water-soluble derivative of tanshinone IIA isolated as the main pharmacologically active natural compound from a traditional Chinese herbal medicine, the dried root of Salvia miltiorrhiza Bunge known as Danshen a potent negative allosteric modulator of the human purinergic receptor P2X7.

Name: Palmatine
Information: Palmatine, an isoquinoline alkaloid, has sedative, antidepressant, antioxidative, anti-ulcerative, antacid, anticancer, and anti-metastatic activities.

Name: 5-Hydroxymethylfurfural
Information: 5-Hydroxymethylfurfural (5-HMF) is an important bio-sourced intermediate, formed from carbohydrates such as glucose or fructose and used for production of fuels and chemical intermediates.

Name: Tyrosol
Information: Tyrosol is an antioxidant that is naturally present in several foods such as wines and green tea and is present most abundantly in olives.

Name: Dehydroandrographolide Succinate Potasium Salt
Information: Dehydroandrographolide Succinate (DAS), extracted from herbal medicine Andrographis paniculata (Burm f) Nees, is widely used for the treatment of viral pneumonia and viral upper respiratory tract infections because of its immunostimulatory, anti-infective and anti-inflammatory effect.

Name: Ligustrazine hydrochloride
Information: Tetramethylpyrazine, also known as ligustrazine, is a chemical compound found in natto and in fermented cocoa beans with anti-inflammation, antioxidant, antiplatelet, and antiapoptosis activities.

Name: Sophoricoside
Information: Sophoricoside (SOPH) is an isoflavone isolated from Sophora japonica (Leguminosae) with numerous pharmacological effects, including anti- inflammatory, anti-cancer and immunosuppressive effects.

Name: cis-Anethole
Information: Anethole has two isomers, the cis(Z) isomer being 15-38 times more toxic to animal than the trans(E) isomer. cis-Anethole is found in anise and Only a low level is permitted in flavours.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Ginkgolide C
Information: Ginkgolide C, isolated from Ginkgo biloba leaves, is a flavone reported to have multiple biological functions, from decreased platelet aggregation to ameliorating Alzheimer disease.

Name: Echinacoside
Information: Echinacoside, a natural polyphenolic compound, has various biological activities, such as antioxidative, anti-inflammatory, neuroprotective, hepatoprotective, nitric oxide radical-scavenging and vasodilative actions.

Name: Notoginsenoside R1
Information: Notoginsenoside R1 is the main ingredient with cardiovascular activity in Panax notoginseng. It inhibits TNF-α-induced PAI-1 overexpression via extracellular signal-related kinases (ERK1/2) and phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K)/protein kinase B (PKB) signaling pathways.

Name: Carvacrol
Information: Carvacrol, monoterpenic phenol isomeric with thymol, has diverse activities such as antimicrobial, antitumor, an-timutagenic, antigenotoxic, analgesic, antispasmodic, anti-inflammatory, angiogenic, antiparasitic, antiplatelet, AChE inhibitory, antielastase, insecticidal, antihepatotoxic and hepatoprotective activities.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Succinic acid
Information: Succinic acid is a crystalline organic acid which occurs in living tissue as an intermediate in glucose metabolism.
Synonyms: 1,4-Butandioic Acid; 1,2-Ethanedicarboxylic acid; Amber acid; Asuccin; Butanedioic acid

Name: Palmitic acid
Information: Palmitic acid is the most common saturated fatty acid found in animals, plants and microorganisms with anti-tumor activity.

Name: Helicide
Information: Helicide (4-formylphenyl-O-β-d-allopyranoside), a main active constituent from seeds of the Chinese herb Helicia nilagirica, has been reported to exert a sedative, analgesic and hypnotic effect, and is used clinically to treat neurasthenic syndrome, vascular headaches and trigeminal neuralgia.

Name: Gentisic acid
Information: Gentisic acid, an active metabolite of salicylic acid degradation, has a broad spectrum of biological activity, such as anti-inflammatory, antirheumatic and antioxidant properties.
Synonyms: DHB; 2,5-dihydroxybenzoic acid; 5-Hydroxysalicylic acid; Gentianic acid; Carboxyhydroquinone; Hydroquinonecarboxylic acid

Name: Trigonelline Hydrochloride
Information: Trigonelline, a major alkaloid component of fenugreek, has hypoglycemic, hypolipidemic, neuroprotective, antimigraine, sedative, memory-improving, antibacterial, antiviral, and anti-tumor activities, and also has been shown to reduce diabetic auditory neuropathy and platelet aggregation.
Synonyms: Nicotinic acid N-methylbetaine Hydrochloride, Coffearine Hydrochloride, Coffearine Hydrochloride, Gynesine Hydrochloride

Name: Stevioside
Information: Stevioside is a natural sweetener extracted from leaves of Stevia rebaudiana (Bertoni) Bertoni.

Name: Dehydroandrographolide
Information: Dehydroandrographolide, isolated from Andrographis paniculata (Burm. F.) Nees (Chuan-xin-lian), is a novel TMEM16A inhibitor and possesses multiple pharmacological activities, including anti-inflammation, anti-cancer, anti-bacterial, anti-virus and anti-hepatitis activity.

Name: Imperatorin
Information: Imperatorin, a naturally occurring psoralen-type furanocoumarin, is a potent myorelaxant agent and acts as a calcium antagonist on vascular smooth muscle.

Name: Scutellarin
Information: Scutellarin, the major active principal flavonoids extracted from the Chinese herbal medicines Scutellaria baicalensis and Erigeron breviscapus (Vant.) Hand-Mazz, has many pharmacological effects, such as antioxidant, antitumor, antiviral, and antiinflammatory activities.

Name: Ginsenoside Re
Information: Ginsenoside Re is a major ginsenoside in ginseng and belongs to 20(S)-protopanaxatriol group. It has diverse in vitro and in vivo effects, including vasorelaxant, antioxidant, antihyperlipidemic, and angiogenic actions.
Synonyms: Panaxoside Re, Sanchinoside Re, Chikusetsusaponin Ivc

Name: Harmine hydrochloride
Information: Harmine, a fluorescent harmala alkaloid belonging to the beta-carboline family of compounds, is a highly cell-permeant and competitive inhibitor of ATP binding to the kinase pocket of DYRK1A, with about 60-fold higher IC50 value for DYRK2. It can also inhibit monoamine oxidases (MAOs) and cdc-like kinases (CLKs).

Name: Quercitrin
Information: Quercitrin (3-rhamnosyl quercetin), a glycoside of quercetin, has been found as a main bioactive constituent in T. sinensis leaves and has antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and anti-allergic activities.

Name: Loganin
Information: Loganin is an iridoid glycoside first isolated from the seeds of Strychnos nux-vomica, a member of the Loganiaceae family. It is a non-competitive inhibitor of BACE1 with IC50 of 47.97 μM an also inhibits AChE and BChE with IC50 values of 3.95 μM and 33.02 μM, respectively.

Name: Isoquercitrin
Information: Isoquercitrin, a flavonoid compound with anticancer activity isolated from Bidens bipinnata L, is an inhibitor of Wnt/β-catenin that acts downstream of the β-catenin nuclear translocation.

Name: Madecassoside
Information: Madecassoside is the main active triterpene constituent of Centella asiatica herbs, a traditional Chinese medicine for wound healing and scar management.

Name: Eupatilin
Information: Eupatilin, a major flavonoid from Artemisia plants, possesses various beneficial biological effects including anti-inflammation, anti-tumor, anti-cancer, anti-allergy, and anti-oxidation activity.

Name: Panaxatriol
Information: Panaxatriol is a triterpene sapogenin originally found in species of Panax (ginseng) and exhibits anti-inflammatory, hepatoprotective, anti-arrhythmic, and antioxidative activities.

Name: D-Galactose
Information: D-Galactose is an aldohexose that occurs naturally in the D-form in lactose, cerebrosides, gangliosides, and mucoproteins and is converted enzymatically into D-glucose for metabolism or polysaccharides for storage. It accelerates senescence in invertebrates and mammals and has been used as a model for aging.

Name: Glucosamine sulfate
Information: Glucosamine sulfate is a dietary supplement commonly used in the treatment of osteoarthritis. It is a type of glycosaminoglycan, which is a naturally occurring major component of joint cartilage and joint fluid.

Name: Camphor
Information: Camphor is a bicyclic monoterpene ketone found widely in plants, especially cinnamomum camphora and used topically as a skin antipruritic and as an anti-infective agent.

Name: Tetrahydropalmatine hydrochloride
Information: Tetrahydropalmatine (THP) is an isoquinoline alkaloid found in several different plant species, mainly in the Corydalis genus (Yan Hu Suo), but also in other plants such as Stephania rotunda. It is a potent muscle relaxant.

Name: Allantoin
Information: Allantoin, produced from uric acid, is a major metabolic intermediate in most organisms including animals, plants and bacteria.

Name: Lawsone
Information: Lawsone is a red-orange dye present in the leaves of the henna plant (Lawsonia inermis) as well as in the flower of water hyacinth (Eichhornia crassipes).

Name: Galanthamine
Information: Galantamine is a phenanthrene alkaloid and a reversible, competitive acetylcholinesterase inhibitor with IC50 of 0.35 μM, exhibits 50-fold selectivity against butyryl-cholinesterase. It is studied as a treatment for Alzheimer's disease and other central nervous system disorders.
Synonyms: Nivalin, Razadyne, Razadyne ER, Reminyl, Lycoremine

Name: Harmine
Information: Harmine is an alkaloid of the β-carboline family that regulates PPARγ expression through inhibition of the Wnt signaling pathway. It also selectively binds to MAO-A and reversibly inhibits monoamine oxidase A (MAO-A) but not the variant MAO-B.

Name: D-Pinitol
Information: D-pinitol is a naturally occurring compound derived from soy and has significant pharmacological activitites such as inhibition of the T-helpercell-1 response, antiviral, larvicidal, antiinflammatory, antihyperlipidemic, cardioprotective, inhibition of ovalbumin-induced airway inflammation and antioxidant.

Name: Guaiacol
Information: Guaiacol is a phenolic natural product first isolated from Guaiac resin and the oxidation of lignin. It is a precursor to various flavorants, such as eugenoland vanillin.

Name: Indigo
Information: Indigo dye is an organic compound with a distinctive blue color. It is extracted from the leaves of certain plants or synthetic.

Name: Scopoletin
Information: Scopoletin is the main bioactive constituent of flower buds from Magnolia fargesii with anti-inflammatory, hypouricemic, and antioxidant activities.
Synonyms: Esculetin 6-methyl ether, Gelseminic acid, 6-Methylesculetin, Chrysatropic acid

Name: Protopine
Information: Protopine, an alkaloid present in different plants, has been shown to exhibit a number of activities, such as inhibition of calcium influx through both voltage and receptor-operated channels and inhibition of rabbit blood platelet aggregation. It also possesses anti-cholinergic and anti-histaminic as well as anti-bacterial activities.

Name: Pyrogallol
Information: Pyrogallol, an organic compound belonging to the phenol family, used as a photographic film developer and in the preparation of other chemicals. It is known to be a superoxide anion generator and ROS inducer.

Name: L-Rhamnose monohydrate
Information: L-Rhamnose monohydrate is used as a starting material for the production of furanones. It is an important material involved in the reaction of flavors developed during the preparation of various foods like bread, grilled meats, etc.

Name: Arteether
Information: Arteether is a well-known antimalarial drug which acts by producing free radicals within the malarial parasite.

Name: Isopsoralen
Information: Isopsoralen, also known as angelicin, is a constituent of roots and leaves of angelica with anti-inflammatory activity and regulates LPS-induced inflammation via inhibiting MAPK/NF-κB pathways. It also shows antiviral activity against gammaherpesviruses.

Name: Bornyl acetate
Information: Bornyl acetate, the main volatile constituent in numerous conifer oils and some Chinese traditional herbs, exhibits anti-inflammatory property and it is used as an analgesic.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Synonyms: Isobornyl acetate, Bornyl acetic ether, 2-Camphanol acetate

Name: Sophoridine
Information: Sophoridine, a natural product obtained from medicinal plants, has a variety of pharmacological effects, including anti-cancer and anti-arrhythmia, and affects the immune and central nervous systems.

Name: Hydroxy Camptothecine
Information: 10-Hydroxycamptothecin is a cell-permeable powerful DNA topoisomerase I inhibitor. It has selective inhibitory effect on the phosphorylation of histone H1 and H3, but less effect on other histones.

Name: Hederagenin
Information: Hederagenin is a highly water insoluble triterpenoid compound that can be found in various plants including Hedera helix and Chenopodium quinoa. It exhibits a variety of biological activities, including potent antitumor properties both in vitro and in vivo.
Synonyms: Caulosapogenin, Hederagenol, Hederagenic acid, Astrantiagenin E

Name: Astragaloside IV
Information: Astragaloside IV is a bioactive saponin first isolated from the dried plant roots of the genus Astragalus, which is used in traditional Chinese medicine. It has various effect on the cardiovascular, immune, digestive, and nervous systems.

Name: Bulleyaconi cine A
Information: Bulleyaconitine A (BLA) is an active ingredient of Aconitum bulleyanum plants and classified as an "aconitine-like" alkaloid. It is a potent use-dependent blocker for both Nav1.7 and Nav1.8 Na+ currents.

Name: Catalpol
Information: Catalpol, an iridoid glucoside contained richly in the roots of the small flowering plant species Rehmannia glutinosa Libosch, has been shown to have antioxidation, anti-inflammation, anti-apoptosis and other neuroprotective properties and plays a role in neuroprotection against hypoxic/ischemic injury, AD and PD in both in vivo and in vitro models.

Name: α-Hederin
Information: α-hederin is a water-soluble pentacyclic triterpenoid saponin which has shown hemolytic and apoptotic properties.

Name: Hederacoside C
Information: Hederacoside C (HDC) is one of the active ingredients in Hedera helix leaf extract (Ivy Ex.) and used to treat respiratory disorders.

Name: Lathyrol
Information: Lathyrol is a natural product that is used for cancer treatment.

Name: Ginsenoside Rg1
Information: Ginsenoside Rg1, identified as a protopanaxatriol-type, has pharmacological actions such as neuroprotective and anti-tumor effects on various cancer types.
Synonyms: Ginsenoside A2, Panaxoside A, Panaxoside Rg1, Sanchinoside C1, Sanchinoside Rg1

Name: Ginsenoside Rb1
Information: Ginsenoside Rb1 is a protopanaxadiol that has diverse in vitro and in vivo effects, including neuroprotective, anti-inflammatory, and anti-obesity actions.

Name: (-)-Epicatechin gallate
Information: Epigallocatechin gallate (EGCG), also known as epigallocatechin-3-gallate, is the ester of epigallocatechin and gallic acid, and is a type of catechin with anti-inflammatory effects.

Name: Forsythin
Information: Forsythin (FOR) is an active ingredient extracted from the fruit of the medicinal plant Forsythia suspensa (Thunb.) Vahl and has been shown to have antioxidant, antibacterial and antiinflammatory properties.

Name: Swertiamarin
Information: Swertiamarin is a common secoiridoid found among the members of Gentianaceae with anti-inflammatory, anticancer, hypoglycemic and hypolipidemic activities.

Name: Liquiritin
Information: Liquiritin (LIQ) is a main component among the licorice flavonoids, and possesses anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer abilities.

Name: Nonivamide
Information: Nonivamide is found in herbs and spices. Nonivamide is an alkaloid from Capsicum species Nonivamide is a flavoring ingredient.
Synonyms: Pseudocapsaicin; Pelargonic acid vanillylamide; Nonanoic acid vanillylamide

Name: Valproic acid
Information: Valproic acid is a fatty acid with anticonvulsant properties used in the treatment of epilepsy. It is also a histone deacetylase inhibitor and is under investigation for treatment of HIV and various cancers.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: L-Cycloserine
Information: L-Cycloserine is a potent inhibitor of the sphingolipid pathway via inhibiting 3-ketodihydrosphingosine synthetase. It also inhibits HIV-1 cytopathic effects, replication, and infectivity.

Name: Maltitol
Information: Maltitol is a sugar alcohol (polyol) used as a sugar substitute. It is especially useful in the production of sweets, including sugarless hard candies, chewing gum, chocolates.

Name: Tannic acid
Information: Tannic acid, a polyphenolic compound, is a CXCL12/CXCR4 inhibitor with antiangiogenic, anti-inflammatory and antitumor activity.

Name: Tetramethylpyrazine
Information: Tetramethylpyrazine (ligustrazine, TMP) is a natural compound isolated from Chinese herbal medicine Ligusticum wallichii (Chuan Xiong) with anti-inflammation, antioxidant, antiplatelet, and antiapoptosis activities.

Name: Gamma-Oryzanol
Information: Gamma-oryzanol (GO), a nutriactive phytochemical naturally occurring in crude rice bran oil, is an antioxidant compound used to treat hyperlipidemia, disorders of menopause and to increase the muscle mass.

Name: (+)-Borneol
Information: (+)-Borneol is one of enantiomers of borneol which is a valuable medical material, senior aromatic spice, and chemical material and has been used in food and also folk medicine.

Name: Vanillyl Butyl Ether
Information: Vanillyl butyl ether, an ether of monohydroxybenzoic acid, is added to food products as a flavoring agent. It is also present in cosmetics and personal care products as a fragrance ingredient, oral care agent, hair conditioning agent, and warming or cooling agent.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Nifuratel
Information: Local antiprotozoal and antifungal agent that may also be given orally.

Name: Flavone
Information: Flavone, a class of flavonoids, mainly found in spices and red or purple plant foods with antioxidant, anti-proliferative, anti-tumor, anti-microbial, estrogenic, acetyl cholinesterase, anti-inflammatory activities and are also used in cancer, cardiovascular disease, neurodegenerative disorders etc.

Name: Histamine
Information: Histamine, an organic nitrogenous compound, is involved in local immune responses regulating physiological function in the gut and acting as a neurotransmitter for the brain, spinal cord, and uterus. It is a potent H1 and H2 receptor agonist.

Name: Veratric acid
Information: Veratric acid, a simple benzoic acid derived from plants and fruits, has anti-oxidant, anti-inflammation, and blood pressure-lowering effects.

Name: Vindoline
Information: Vindoline is a chemical precursor to vinblastine and exhibits antimitotic activity by inhibiting microtubule assembly.

Name: Fusidine
Information: Fusidine, isolated from Fusidium coccineum, is a steroidal antibiotic that inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: (+)-Catechin hydrate
Information: Catechins are a plant derived polyphenolic anti-oxidants with phytotoxic properties. (+)-Catechin hydrate is a frequent component of traditional herbal remedies, such as Uncaria rhynchophylla.

Name: Protocatechuic acid
Information: Protocatechuic acid (PCA), a dihydroxybenzoic acid, is a type of widely distributed naturally occurring phenolic acid.

Name: (-)-Borneol
Information: (-)-Borneol, one of enantiomers of borneol, has a camphoraceous and evident woody odor.

Name: Zinc Undecylenate
Information: Zinc Undecylenate is a natural or synthetic fungistatic fatty acid, antifungal Zinc Undecylenate is used topically in creams against fungal infections, eczemas, ringworm, and other cutaneous conditions.

Name: Pyridoxine
Information: Pyridoxine, also known as vitamin B6, is a form of vitamin B6 found commonly in food and used as dietary supplement. It is a cofactor for both glutamic acid decarboxylase and GABA transaminase.

Name: Batyl alcohol
Information: Batyl alcohol, isolated from shark liver oil, is also present in yellow bone marrow of animals and has been described as an inflammatory agent.

Name: Caryophyllene oxide
Information: Caryophyllene oxide, an oxygenated terpenoid existed in many plant essential oil, is well known as preservative in food, drugs and cosmetics with anti-inflammatory, anti-carcinogenic and skin penetration enhancing  properties.

Name: Nordihydroguaiaretic acid (NDGA)
Information: Nordihydroguaiaretic acid (NDGA) is a phenolic antioxidant found in the leaves and twigs of the evergreen desert shrub, Larrea tridentata (Sesse and Moc. ex DC) Coville (creosote bush). It is a recognized inhibitor of lipoxygenase (LOX) and has antioxidant and free radical scavenging properties.

Name: Methyl 4-hydroxybenzoate
Information: Methyl 4-hydroxybenzoate is an anti-fungal agent often used in a variety of cosmetics, personal-care products and food preservatives.
Synonyms: Methylparaben, Methyl paraben, Methyl p-hydroxybenzoate, Nipagin, Methyl parahydroxybenzoate

Name: L-Arabinose
Information: L-Arabinose (l-Ara) is a plant saccharide that is not found in animals. It is a component of cell wall and may be useful as a natural pharmaceutical.

Name: L-Tryptophan
Information: L-tryprophan is an essential amino acid that acts like a natural mood regulator that is necessary for normal growth in infants and for nitrogen balance in adults.

Name: D-(+)-Trehalose dihydrate
Information: Trehalose is a non-reducing sugar. It is thought to provide plants and animals with the ability to withstanding periods of dehydration.

Name: Guaiazulene
Information: Guaiazulene is a bicyclic sesquiterpene that is a constituent of some essential oils, mainly oil of guaiac and chamomile oil, which also serve as its commercial sources.

Name: Thioctic acid
Information: Thioctic acid (DL-α-Lipoic acid) is a cyclic disulfide antioxidant that interconverts with its reduced dithiol form.

Name: Oxaceprol
Information: Oxaceprol is an anti-inflammatory drug used in the treatment of osteoarthritis.

Name: (+)-α-Lipoic acid
Information: R(+)-α-lipoic acid, a physiological form of thioctic acid, is a strong antioxidant that relieves diabetic neuropathic symptoms. It shows superior antioxidative effects to its racemate.

Name: Pergolide Mesylate
Information: Pergolide Mesylate is an antiparkinsonian agent which functions as a dopaminergic agonist.

Name: Cabozantinib malate (XL184)
Information: Cabozantinib malate (XL184) is the malate of Cabozantinib, a potent VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 of 0.035 nM and also inhibits c-Met, Ret, Kit, Flt-1/3/4, Tie2, and AXL with IC50 of 1.3 nM, 4 nM, 4.6 nM, 12 nM/11.3 nM/6 nM, 14.3 nM and 7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Sitagliptin phosphate monohydrate
Information: Sitagliptin phosphate monohydrate is a potent inhibitor of DPP-IV with IC50 of 19 nM in Caco-2 cell extracts.

Name: Lithocholic acid
Information: Lithocholic acid is a toxic secondary bile acid, causes intrahepatic cholestasis, has tumor-promoting activity, its toxic effect can be protected after it activates the vitamin D receptor, PXR and FXR.

Name: Ethambutol 2HCl
Information: Ethambutol is a bacteriostatic antimycobacterial agent, which obstructs the formation of cell wall by inhibiting arabinosyl transferases.

Name: Pentamidine isethionate
Information: Pentamidine is an inhibitor of PRL Phosphatases and also inhibits synthesis of DNA, RNA and protein.

Name: Mirabegron
Information: Mirabegron is a selective β3-adrenoceptor agonist with EC50 of 22.4 nM.

Name: Acebutolol HCl
Information: Acebutolol is a β-adrenergic receptors antagonist used in the treatment of hypertension, angina pectoris and cardiac arrhythmias.

Name: Ampiroxicam
Information: Ampiroxicam is a nonselective cyclooxygenase inhibitor uesd as anti-inflammatory drug.

Name: Desloratadine
Information: Desloratadine is a potent antagonist for  human histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 51 nM.

Name: Hyoscyamine
Information: Hyoscyamine is an AChR inhibitor with IC50 of 7.5 nM.

Name: Allylthiourea
Information: Allylthiourea is a metabolic inhibitor that selective inhibits ammonia oxidation.

Name: Sennoside B
Information: Sennoside B, a kind of irritant laxative isolated from rhei rhizome, inhibits PDGF-stimulated cell proliferation.

Name: Avanafil
Information: Avanafil is a highly selective PDE5 inhibitor with IC50 of 5.2 nM, >121-fold selectivity over other PDEs.

Name: Sodium Picosulfate
Information: Sodium Picosulfate inhibits absorption of water and electrolytes, and increases their secretion.

Name: Tolcapone
Information: Tolcapone is a selective, potent and reversible of catechol-O-methyl transferase (COMT) inhibitor with Ki of 30 nM.

Name: Probenecid
Information: Probenecid is a classical competitive inhibitor of organic anion transport, which is also a TRPV2 agonist and an inhibitor of TAS2R16.

Name: Procaine HCl
Information: Procaine is an inhibitor of sodium channel, NMDA receptor and nAChR with IC50 of 60 μM, 0.296 mM and 45.5 μM, which is also an inhibitor of 5-HT3 with KD of 1.7 μM.

Name: Homatropine Methylbromide
Information: Homatropine Methylbromide is muscarinic AChR antagonist, inhibits endothelial and smooth muscle muscarinic receptors of WKY-E and SHR-E with IC50 of 162.5 nM and 170.3 nM, respectively.

Name: Homatropine Bromide
Information: Homatropine Bromide is an muscarinic AChR antagonist, inhibits endothelial and smooth muscle muscarinic receptors of WKY-E and SHR-E with IC50 of 162.5 nM and 170.3 nM, respectively.

Name: Hydroxyzine 2HCl
Information: Hydroxyzine is a histamine H1-receptor antagonist, inhibits binding of [3H]pyrilamine/[3H]desloratadine to human histamine H1 receptor with IC50 of 10 nM/19 nM.

Name: Aclidinium Bromide
Information: Aclidinium Bromide inhibits human muscarinic AChR M1, M2, M3, M4 and M5 with Ki of 0.1 nM, 0.14 nM, 0.14 nM, 0.21 nM and 0.16 nM, respectively.

Name: Diphemanil Methylsulfate
Information: Diphemanil Methylsulfate is a quaternary ammonium anticholinergic, it binds muscarinic acetycholine receptors (mAchR).

Name: Doxapram HCl
Information: Doxapram HCl inhibits TASK-1, TASK-3, TASK-1/TASK-3 heterodimeric channel function with EC50 of 410 nM, 37 μM, 9 μM, respectively.

Name: Dibucaine HCl
Information: Dibucaine HCl is a local anesthetics.

Name: Methazolamide
Information: Methazolamide is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor with Ki of 50 nM, 14 nM and 36 nM for hCA I, hCA II and bCA IV isoforms, respectively.

Name: Norethindrone
Information: Norethindrone is a synthetic progestin, which mimic the actions of the endogenous ovarian hormone progesterone.

Name: Olsalazine Sodium
Information: Olsalazine Sodium is an anti-inflammatory prodrug, which consists of two 5-ASA moieties linked by an azo bond.

Name: Nafcillin Sodium
Information: Nafcillin sodium reversibly inhibits β-lactamase with Kd of 33 mM.

Name: Tetrahydrozoline HCl
Information: Tetrahydrozoline HCl is an imidazoline derivative with alpha receptor agonist activity.

Name: Toltrazuril
Information: Toltrazuril is an antiprotozoal agent that acts upon Coccidia parasites.

Name: Pheniramine Maleate
Information: Pheniramine Maleate is an antihistamine with anticholinergic properties used to treat allergic conditions such as hay fever or urticaria.

Name: Estradiol Cypionate
Information: Estradiol cypionate is the 17 β-cyclopentylpropinate ester of estradiol, which inhibits ET-1 synthesis via estrogen receptor.

Name: Bisacodyl
Information: Bisacodyl (INN) is a stimulant laxative drug that works directly on the colon to produce a bowel movement.

Name: Carbimazole
Information: Carbimazole is an imidazole antithyroid agent.

Name: Valdecoxib
Information: Valdecoxib is a potent and selective inhibitor of COX-2 with IC50 of 5 nM.

Name: Valganciclovir HCl
Information: Valganciclovir HCl is a prodrug for ganciclovir with antiviral activity used to treat cytomegalovirus infections.

Name: Nabumetone
Information: Nabumetone is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and its active metabolite inhibits the COX.

Name: Sertraline HCl
Information: Sertraline HCl is a 5-HT antagonist with Ki of 13 nM.

Name: Spironolactone
Information: Spironolactone is a potent antagonist of the androgen receptor with IC50 of 77 nM.

Name: Retapamulin
Information: Retapamulin is a topical antibiotic, which binds to both E. coli and S. aureus ribosomes with similar potencies with Kd of 3 nM.

Name: Methyclothiazide
Information: Methyclothiazide is a substituted benzothiadiazide, used to treat high blood pressure and fluid retention caused by various conditions including heart disease.

Name: Ropivacaine HCl
Information: Ropivacaine HCl is an anaesthetic agent and blocks impulse conduction in nerve fibres through inhibiting sodium ion influx reversibly.

Name: Sodium Nitroprusside Dihydrate
Information: Sodium Nitroprusside  Dihydrate is a potent vasodilator working through releasing NO spontaneously in blood.

Name: Erythromycin Ethylsuccinate
Information: Erythromycin Ethylsuccinate, an oral macrolide antibiotic produced by Streptomyces erythreus, reversibly binds to the 50S ribosome of bacteria, and inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Levobupivacaine HCl
Information: Levobupivacaine HCl, the pure S(-)-enantiomer of bupivacaine, is a reversible neuronal sodium channel inhibitor, used as a long-acting local anesthetic.

Name: Ronidazole
Information: Ronidazole is an antiprotozoal agent.

Name: Escitalopram Oxalate
Information: Escitalopram Oxalate is a selective serotonin (5-HT) reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) with Ki of 0.89 nM.

Name: Guanabenz Acetate
Information: Guanabenz Acetate is an selective agonist of α2a-adrenergic receptor, α2b-adrenergic receptor and α2c-adrenergic receptor with pEC50 of 8.25, 7.01 and ~5, respectively.

Name: Tinidazole
Information: Tinidazole is an anti-parasitic drug.

Name: Guanidine HCl
Information: Guanidine HCl, the crystalline compound of strong alkalinity formed by the oxidation of guanine, is a normal product of protein metabolism and a protein denaturant.

Name: Griseofulvin
Information: Griseofulvin, a production from some strains of the mold Penicillium griseofulvumam, is able to inhibit cell mitosis by interfering with microtubule function.

Name: Decamethonium Bromide
Information: Decamethonium Bromide is a nicotinic AChR partial agonist and neuromuscular blocking agent.

Name: Sodium 4-Aminosalicylate
Information: Sodium 4-Aminosalicylate is an antibiotic used to treat tuberculosis via NF-κB inhibition and free radical scavenging.

Name: Zinc Pyrithione
Information: Zinc pyrithione is an antifungal and antibacterial agent disrupting membrane transport by blocking the proton pump.

Name: Propranolol HCl
Information: Propranolol HCl is a competitive non-selective beta-adrenergic receptors inhibitor with IC50 of 12 nM.

Name: Mequinol
Information: Mequinol (4-Methoxyphenol) is a depigmentation agent.

Name: Mefenamic Acid
Information: Mefenamic Acid is a competitive inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2.

Name: Ticagrelor
Information: Ticagrelor is the first reversibly binding oral P2Y12 receptor antagonist with Ki of 2 nM.

Name: Triamterene
Information: Triamterene blocks epithelial Na+ channel (ENaC) in a voltage-dependent manner with IC50 of 4.5 μM.

Name: Sulfacetamide Sodium
Information: Sulfacetamide Sodium is an anti-biotic.

Name: Spiramycin
Information: Spiramycin is a 16-membered ring macrolide (antibiotic).

Name: Vitamin A Acetate
Information: Vitamin A is a group of unsaturated nutritional hydrocarbons, that includes retinol, retinal, retinoic acid, and several provitamin A carotenoids, among which beta-carotene is the most important.

Name: Lomerizine 2HCl
Information: Lomerizine dihydrochloride is a relatively new L- and T-type calcium channel blocker used in the treatment of migraine.

Name: Levobetaxolol HCl
Information: Levobetaxolol exhibits a higher affinity at cloned human β1 and β2 receptors with Ki value of 0.76 nM and 32.6 nM, respectively.

Name: Loxapine Succinate
Information: Loxapine Succinate is a D2DR and D4DR inhibitor, serotonergic receptor antagonist and also a dibenzoxazepine anti-psychotic agent.

Name: Flumethasone
Information: Flumethasone is a glucocorticoid receptor agonist, this complex binds to the nucleus causing a variety of genetic activation and repressions.

Name: Halobetasol Propionate
Information: Halobetasol Propionate is an anti-inflammatory and a dermatologic agent commonly used to treat psoriasis.

Name: Fenspiride HCl
Information: Fenspiride is a bronchodilator with anti-inflammatory properties, inhibiting phosphodiesterase 4 and phosphodiesterase 3 activities with logIC50 values of 4.16 and 3.44, respectively, in human isolated bronchi.

Name: Ifenprodil Tartrate
Information: Ifenprodil is an atypical noncompetitive antagonist at the NMDA receptor, it interacts with high affinity at a homogeneous population of NMDA receptors in neonatal rat forebrain with IC50 of 0.3 μM.

Name: Pramoxine HCl
Information: Pramoxine is a topical local anesthetic that has been shown to have antipruritic properties.

Name: Difluprednate
Information: Difluprednate (difluoroprednisolone butyrate acetate, or DFBA) is a synthetic difluorinated prednisolone derivative, it is originally developed for dermatologic applications.

Name: Droperidol
Information: Droperidol is a potent antagonist of dopamine subtype 2 receptors in the limbic system.

Name: Halcinonide
Information: Halcinonide is a high potency corticosteroid used in topical preparations as an anti-inflammatory agent.

Name: Dexlansoprazole
Information: Dexlansoprazole, the dextrorotatory enantiomer of lansoprazole, is a proton pump inhibitor (PPI) formulated to have dual delayed-release properties.

Name: Esmolol HCl
Information: Esmolol is a cardioselective b-blocker, used to control rapid heartbeats or abnormal heart rhythms.

Name: Voglibose
Information: Voglibose is an N-substituted derivative of valiolamine, excellent inhibitory activity against α-glucosidases and its action against hyperglycemia and various disorders caused by hyperglycemia.

Name: Eprosartan Mesylate
Information: Eprosartan is a nonpeptide angiotensin II receptor antagonist, [3H]-eprosartan binds to the AT1 receptor with KD of 0.83 nM in rat vascular smooth muscle cells.

Name: Diminazene Aceturate
Information: Diminazene is a di-amidine also known as 4,4-(1-Triazene–1,3–diyl)bis(benzenecarboximidamide), used as an effective trypanocidal agent.

Name: Closantel Sodium
Information: Closantel is a gram positive antibacterial activity inhibitor, inhibiting the KinA/Spo0F system with IC50 of 3.8 μM.

Name: Closantel
Information: Closantel is a gram positive antibacterial activity inhibitor, inhibiting the KinA/Spo0F system with IC50 of 3.8 μM.

Name: Clofazimine
Information: Clofazimine is a rhimophenazine dye, originally developed for the treatment of tuberculosis, it has both antimicrobial and antiinflammatory activity, postulated mechanisms of action include intercalation of clofazimine with bacterial DNA and increasing levels of cellular phospholipase A2.

Name: Estradiol Benzoate
Information: Estradiol benzoate is an estradiol analog which binds to the human, murine and chicken ERα with IC50 of 22-28 nM.

Name: Dicloxacillin Sodium
Information: Dicloxacillin is a β-lactamase resistant penicillin similar to oxacillin and it has activity against gram-positive/negative aerobic and anaerobic bacteria.

Name: Desvenlafaxine Succinate
Information: Desvenlafaxine Succinate is a new serotonin (5-HT) transporter and norepinephrine (NE) transporter reuptake inhibitor with Ki of 40.2 nM and 558.4 nM respectively.

Name: Desvenlafaxine
Information: Desvenlafaxine is a serotonin (5-HT) and norepinephrine (NE) reuptake inhibitor with Ki of 40.2 nM and 558.4 nM, respectively.

Name: Triclabendazole
Information: Triclabendazole is a benzimidazole, it binds to tubulin impairing intracellular transport mechanisms and interferes with protein synthesis.

Name: Histamine 2HCl
Information: Histamine is an organic nitrogen compound, acts on target cells in mammalian brain via stimulation of Histamine 1/2.

Name: Pefloxacin Mesylate Dihydrate

Information: Psoralen is a naturally occurring furocoumarin that intercalates with DNA, inhibiting DNA synthesis and cell division.

Name: Anethole trithione
Information: Anethole trithione is a drug used in the treatment of dry mouth.

Name: Ondansetron Hydrochloride Dihydrate
Information: Ondansetron is a highly specific and selective serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist (Ki=6.16 nM), with low affinity for dopamine receptors.

Name: Citalopram HBr
Information: Citalopram HBr, an antidepressant, is an orally administered selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) with IC50 of 1.8 nM.
Synonyms: Nitalapram HBr, Prepram HBr, Bonitrile HBr, Lu 10-171 HBr

Name: Sulfacetamide sodium salt hydrate
Information: Sulfacetamide is a sulfonamide antibiotic that blocks the synthesis of dihydrofolic acid by inhibiting the enzyme dihydropteroate synthase(DHPS) with IC50 of 9.5 μM. Sulfacetamide is a competitive inhibitor of bacterial para-aminobenzoic acid (PABA), which is required for bacterial synthesis of folic acid.

Name: Cisapride hydrate
Information: Cisapride acts directly as a selective serotonin 5-HT4 receptor agonist with IC50 of 0.483 μM. And It also acts indirectly as a parasympathomimetic.

Name: Corticosterone
Information: Corticosterone, the major stress hormone, is an adrenocortical steroid that has modest but significant activities as a mineralocorticoid and a glucocorticoid.

Name: Ganoderic acid A
Information: Ganoderic acid A (GAA), a representative active triterpenoid from Ganoderma lucidum, has been reported to exhibit antinociceptive, antioxidative, cytotoxic, hepatoprotective and anticancer activities.

Name: Betulin
Information: Betulin (BE), also known as betulinol, betuline, or betulinic alcohol, is a pentacyclic lupane-type triterpenoid naturally distributed in many plants and displays a broad spectrum of biological and pharmacological properties such as anticancer and chemopreventive activity.

Name: p-Coumaric Acid
Information: p-Coumaric acid is a hydroxy derivative of cinnamic acid found in a variety of edible plants and is reported to have antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activity.
Synonyms: 4-Hydroxycinnamic acid, P-Hydroxycinnamic acid, 4-Coumaric acid, Trans-p-Coumaric acid, para-Coumaric Acid

Name: Melibiose
Information: Melibiose is a nondigestible disaccharide that consists of one galactose and one glucose moiety in an alpha (1-6) glycosidic linkage.

Name: L-5-Hydroxytryptophan
Information: 5-Hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP), also known as oxitriptan, is a naturally occurring amino acid and chemical precursor as well as a metabolic intermediate in the biosynthesis of the neurotransmitter serotonin.

Name: alpha-Asarone
Information: Alpha (α)-asarone is one of the main pharmacologically active compounds present in Acorus calamus Linn (Acoraceae), Acorus tatarinowii Schott (Acoraceae), and Acorus gramineus Solander. It has anticonvulsant, neuroprotective, anxiolytic and nootropic effects.

Name: Menadiol Diacetate
Information: Menadiol Diacetate (Vitamin K4) is a synthetic hydrophilic menadione compound, which is clinically used as hemostasis medicine. It induces caspase-3-related apoptosis pathway via mitochondrial dysfunction and DNA fragmentation.

Name: Benzyl isothiocyanate
Information: Benzyl isothiocyanate (BITC) is an isothiocyanate originally found in cruciferous vegetables that exhibits immunomodulatory, anti-parasitic, antibiotic, antioxidative, anti-atherosclerotic, anti-angiogenic, anti-metastatic, anticancer chemotherapeutic, and chemopreventive activities.
Synonyms: Benzyl isothiocyanate, Benzoylthiocarbimide, Isothiocyanic Acid Benzoyl Ester

Name: N-Acetylneuraminic acid
Information: N-Acetylneuraminic acid (Neu5Ac, NeuAc, Acido aceneuramico, Acide aceneuramique, Acidium aceneuramicum, Sialic acid, NANA) is the predominant sialic acid found in mammalian cells. Sialic acids are negatively charged monosaccharides attached to the end of sugar chains, giving rise to a wide variety of glycoproteins and glycolipids in biological fluids and cell membranes.
Synonyms: Neu5Ac, NeuAc, Acido aceneuramico, Acide aceneuramique, Acidium aceneuramicum, Sialic acid

Name: Nicergoline
Information: Nicergoline is an ergot derivative used to treat senile dementia and other disorders with vascular origins. It has a selective alpha-1A adrenergic receptor blocking property and also other additional mechanisms of actions.

Name: Thymidine
Information: Thymidine is a pyrimidine nucleoside that is composed of the pyrimidine base thymine attached to the sugar deoxyribose. As a constituent of DNA, thymidine pairs with adenine in the DNA double helix.

Name: Ceftizoxime
Information: Ceftizoxime is a semisynthetic cephalosporin antibiotic which can be administered intravenously or by suppository. It is highly resistant to a broad spectrum of beta-lactamases and is active against a wide range of both aerobic and anaerobic gram-positive and gram-negative organisms.

Name: Cefuroxime axetil
Information: Cefuroxime axetil, a prodrug of the cephalosporin cefuroxime, is a second generation oral cephalosporin antibiotic with in vitro antibacterial activity against several gram-positive and gram-negative organisms.

Name: L-Cysteine HCl
Information: L-cysteine Hydrochloride, also known as L-CYSTEINE or Cysteine HCL (anhydrous), is classified as a cysteine or a cysteine derivative that increases glutathione levels and is important for lung and brain function and liver detoxification.

Name: Diatrizoate sodium
Information: Diatrizoate sodium is an iodinated radiopaque X-ray contrast medium that is used as a diagnostic aid in angiography, urography and radiography.

Name: Atenolol
Information: Atenolol is a selective β1 receptor antagonist with log Kd values of ?6.66±0.05, ?5.99±0.14, ?4.11±0.07 for binding to the human β1-, β2- and β3-adrenoceptors.

Name: Saccharin
Information: Saccharin is an artificial sweetener with effectively no food energy.
Synonyms: Benzoic sulfimide, O-Sulfobenzimide, O-Benzoic sulfimide, Saccharimide

Name: Diastase
Information: Diastase, a natural enzyme, catalyses the breakdown of starch into maltose.

Name: Maltose
Information: Maltose, an non-essential nutrient that provides energy, is an intermediate in the intestinal digestion of glycogen and starch, and is found in germinating grains (and other plants and vegetables).

Name: Piperonyl butoxide
Information: Piperonyl butoxide (PBO) is a man-made pesticide synergist, working with insect killers to increase their effectiveness.

Name: Tolmetin
Information: Tolmetin is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug of the heterocyclic acetic acid derivative class and also exhibits analgesic and antipyretic activity.

Name: Cefoxitin sodium
Information: Cefoxitin Sodium is the sodium salt form of cefoxitin, a beta-lactam, second-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Aceclofenac
Information: Aceclofenac is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) with anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties.

Name: Nilutamide
Information: Nilutamide is a nonsteroidal antiandrogen (NSAA) with affinity for androgen receptors (but not for progestogen, estrogen, or glucocorticoid receptors). It is used in the treatment of prostate cancer.

Name: Ibudilast
Information: Ibudilast is a relatively non-selective phosphodiesterase inhibitor with anti-inflammatory and neuroprotective activities.

Name: Acotiamide hydrochloride
Information: Acotiamide Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of acotiamide, a prokinetic agent with gastrointestinal (GI) motility-enhancing activity. It is a new orally active selective acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.

Name: Mosapride
Information: Mosapride is a gastroprokinetic agent that acts as a selective 5HT4 agonist.

Name: Laurocapram
Information: Laurocapram is a skin penetration enhancer that facilitates absorption of cutaneously applied substances.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Synonyms: N-Dodecylcaprolactam, Azone, N-0252, N-Lauryl caprolactam, Tranzone

Name: Potassium acetate
Information: Potassium acetate is the potassium salt of acetic acid, which is a synthetic carboxylic acid with antibacterial and antifungal properties.

Name: Cefcapene Pivoxil Hydrochloride
Information: Cefcapene Pivoxil is the pivalate ester prodrug form of cefcapene, a semi-synthetic third-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Rabeprazole
Information: Rabeprazole is an oral inhibitor of proton pump and blocks the production of acid by the stomach.

Name: Meropenem Trihydrate
Information: Meropenem is a broad-spectrum antibacterial agent of the carbapenem family with a broad spectrum of in vitro activity against Gram-positive and Gram-negative pathogens.

Name: Faropenem Sodium
Information: Faropenem sodium is an orally active beta-lactam antibiotic that has been used in trials studying the treatment of Tuberculosis, Pulmonary Tuberculosis, and Community Acquired Pneumonia.

Name: Dalbavancin
Information: Dalbavancin is a lipoglycopeptide antibiotic that has bactericidal activity against Gram-positive bacteria including various staphylococci.

Name: Levocetirizine Dihydrochloride
Information: Levocetirizine is the active R-enantiomer of cetirizine and represents a new second-generation histamine H1 antagonist.

Name: Flucloxacillin sodium
Information: Flucloxacillin sodium is the sodium salt of flucloxacillin, a penicillin antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections.

Name: Tafluprost
Information: Tafluprost is a novel prostaglandin analog with a high affinity for the fluoroprostaglandin (FP) receptor PGF2α. A prostanoid selective FP receptor agonist.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Gadopentetate Dimeglumine
Information: Gadopentetate Dimeglumine, a complex of gadolinium with a chelating agent, diethylenetriamine penta-acetic acid, is an extracellular intravenous contrast agent used in magnetic resonance imaging.
Synonyms: Gadopentetic acid dimeglumine, Gd-DTPA, Meglumine gadopentetate

Name: Ecabet sodium
Information: Ecabet sodium is a widely employed mucoprotective agent for the treatment of gastric ulcers.

Name: Bedaquiline fumarate
Information: Bedaquiline fumarate, an oral diarylquinoline,  is a bactericidal antimycobacterial drug. It is a proton-translocating ATP synthetase inhibitor.

Name: Iproniazid
Information: Iproniazid is a non-selective, irreversible monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibitor (MAOI) that is used as an antidepressive agent.

Name: TriacetonaMine
Information: TriacetonaMine, a member of the class of compounds known as piperidinones, is an extremely weak acidic compound found in green vegetables and tea.

Name: Indole-3-carboxylic acid
Information: Indole-3-carboxylic acid is a normal urinary indolic tryptophan metabolite which belongs to a class of organic compounds known as indolecarboxylic acids and derivatives.

Name: Squalene
Information: Squalene, a naturally occurring substance found in plants, animals and humans, is a component of some adjuvants that is added to vaccines to enhance the immune response.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Cefetamet pivoxil hydrochloride
Information: Cefetamet pivoxil hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of cefetamet pivoxil, which is an oral third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Nicarbazin
Information: Nicarbazin, an effective anticoccidial, is also a wide-spectrum anti-parasitic drug.

Name: Propacetamol hydrochloride
Information: Propacetamol hydrochloride (PRO) is a water-soluble prodrug of paracetamol (PA) which can be parenterally administered as analgesic for the treatment of postoperative pain, acute trauma, and gastric and/or intestinal disorders.

Name: Xanthinol Nicotinate
Information: Xanthinol Nicotinate is a potent vasodilator that can easily pass through the cell membrane and once inside the cell it causes an increase in glucose metabolism resulting in an increased energy.

Name: Sulfamethoxazole sodium
Information: Sulfamethoxazole sodium is an antibiotic used for bacterial infections.

Name: Cefodizime Sodium
Information: Cefodizime Sodium, a third generation cephalosporin antibiotic, has broad-spectrum activity and is stable to most beta-lactamases.

Name: Pyridoxal 5-phosphate monohydrate
Information: Pyridoxal 5-phosphate monohydrate is an active vitamin B6 metabolite, which is a cofactor in many reactions of amino acid metabolism.

Name: Cefazedone
Information: Cefazedone is a semisynthetic first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Cephapirin Benzathine
Information: Cephapirin Benzathine is the benzathine salt form of cephapirin, which is a semisynthetic, broad-spectrum, first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Robenidine Hydrochoride
Information: Robenidine hydrochloride is an anticoccidial agent mainly for poultry.

Name: Eperisone hydrochloride
Information: Eperisone hydrochloride is muscle relaxant agent with antispasmodic effects. It is widely used in the treatment of patients with muscular contractures, low back pain or spasticity.

Name: Neticonazole Hydrochloride
Information: Neticonazole is an imidazole antifungal for the treatment of fungal skin infections.

Name: Cefathiamidine
Information: Cefathiamidine is the first generation of cephalosporin antibacterial used for the treatment of respiratory, liver, five senses, urinary tract infections, endocarditis and sepsis.

Name: Calcium Dobesilate
Information: Calcium dobesilate is a small molecule that has been widely used for treating diabetic retinopathy and chronic venous insufficiency.

Name: Lynestrenol
Information: Lynestrenol is a synthetic progestational hormone, an agonist of the progesterone receptor and has weak androgenic and estrogenic activity.

Name: Taurolidine
Information: Taurolidine is a synthetic broad-spectrum antibiotic with antibacterial, anticoagulant and potential antiangiogenic activities.

Name: Menbutone
Information: Menbutone, or genabilic acid, is a derivative of oxybutyric acid which acts as a choleretic stimulating secretion, a trypsinogen and a pepsinogen.

Name: Perospirone hydrochloride
Information: Perospirone is an atypical or second-generation antipsychotic of the azapirone family that antagonizes serotonin 5HT2A receptors and dopamine D2 receptors. It also displays affinity towards 5HT1A receptors as a partial agonist.

Name: Bifendate
Information: Bifendate, a synthetic intermediate of schisandrin C, is an anti-HBV drug used in Chinese medicine for the treatment of chronic hepatitis B.

Name: Cytosine
Information: Cytosine is one of the four main bases found in DNA and RNA used in storing and transporting genetic information within a cell.

Name: Elagolix Sodium
Information: Elagolix Soidum is a potent, selective, orally active, non-peptide antagonist of the gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor (GnRHR) with Kd value of 54 pM. Concentration at 10 μM shows no significant activity on ion channels, enzymes, and transporters (inhibition <50%).

Name: Sulfogaiacol
Information: Sulfogaiacol is a antitussive agent that is used for acute respiratory tract infections, cough and other conditions.

Name: Propiverine hydrochloride
Information: Propiverine is an anticholinergic drug used for the treatment of overactive bladder and urinary incontinence.

Name: Proxyphylline
Information: Proxyphylline is a derivative of theophylline which is used as a bronchodilator and for its cardiovascular properties. It selectively antagonizes A1 adenosine receptors (Ki = 82 nM for bovine brain) versus A2 adenosine receptors (Ki = 850 ?M for platelets).

Name: Asunaprevir
Information: Asunaprevir is an orally bioavailable inhibitor of the hepatitis C virus enzyme serine protease NS3 that is necessary for protein processing required for viral replication.

Name: cis-Aconitic acid
Information: Cis-Aconitic acid is an intermediate in the tricarboxylic acid cycle produced by the dehydration of citric acid.
Synonyms: cis-aconitate, Achilleic acid, Citridinic acid, Equisetic acid, Pyrocitric acid

Name: Maltol
Information: Maltol is a naturally occurring organic compound that is flavour enhancer and flavouring agent.

Name: Farnesol
Information: Farnesol is a natural sesquiterpene alcohol that is potent in treating antimetabolic disorders, anti-inflammation, showing antioxidant, anticancer, and antibiotic effects.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Nonanoic acid
Information: Nonanoic acid is a naturally occurring fatty acid found in both vegetable and animal fats.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Fumaric acid
Information: Fumaric acid is an intermediate in the citric acid cycle used by cells to produce energy in the form of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) from food also a product of the urea cycle.
Synonyms: 2-Butenedioic acid, Trans-Butenedioic acid, Allomaleic acid, Boletic acid, Donitic acid, Lichenic acid, Fumarate

Name: Usnic acid
Information: Usnic acid is a furandione found uniquely in lichen that is used widely in cosmetics, deodorants, toothpaste and medicinal creams as well as some herbal products. It exhibits antiviral, antiprotozoal, antiproliferative, anti-inflammatory and analgesic activity.

Name: Benzamidine HCl
Information: Benzamidine is an inhibitor of serine proteases with Ki values of 35, 350, and 220 µM for trypsin, plasmin, and thrombin, respectively.

Name: Linalool
Information: Linalool, a monoterpene compound commonly found as major component of essential oils of several aromatic species, is a competitive antagonist of NMDA receptors.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Glycocholic acid
Information: Glycocholic acid is a natural secondary bile acid involved in the emulsification of fats.

Name: Lactobionic acid
Information: Lactobionic acid, an α-hydroxyacid (AHA) with antioxidation activity, is used in the development of cosmeceuticals for skin.

Name: Tropine
Information: Tropine is a naturally occurring tropane alkaloid that serves as an intermediate in the synthesis of a variety of bioactive alkaloids, many of which have potent neurological actions.

Name: Buparvaquone
Information: Buparvaquone is a second-generation hydroxynaphthoquinone related to parvaquone, with novel features that make it a promising compound for the therapy and prophylaxis of all forms of theileriosis.

Name: Iminostilbene
Information: Iminostilbene (Dibenzazepine) is a chemical precursor of carbamazepine which is used primarily in the treatment of epilepsy and neuropathic pain.

Name: Fimasartan
Information: Fimasartan is a non-peptide angiotensin II receptor antagonist (ARB) with noncompetitive, insurmountable binding with the AT1 receptor. It is used for the treatment of hypertension and heart failure.

Name: Sulfalene(SMPZ)
Information: Sulfalene（SMPZ）is a cyclic organic chemical used as a versatile synthetic intermediate.

Name: Efonidipine
Information: Efonidipine is an L- and T-type calcium channel blocker leading to vasodilation and decreased automaticity of the heart. It also suppresses aldosterone secretion from the adrenal.

Name: Azathramycin
Information: Azathramycin (Azaerythromycin) is a macrolide antibiotic containing cladinose.

Name: Anamorelin
Information: Anamorelin (ONO-7643, RC-1291, ST-1291) is an orally active, high-affinity, selective agonist of the ghrelin receptor with an EC50 value of 0.74 nM in the HEK293/GRLN  FLIPR assay.

Name: Sorbic acid
Information: Sorbic acid is a naturally occurring compound that originated from the unripe berries of the Rowan Tree. It inhibits various bacteria, including sporeformers, at various stages of their life cycle (germination, outgrowth and cell division).

Name: Tiamulin fumarate
Information: Tiamulin fumarate is a semisynthetic pleuromutilin antibiotic that binds to the ribosomal peptidyl transferase centre and inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Valpromide
Information: Valpromide is an antiepileptic drug, derivative of Valproic acid (VPA), used as a mood-stabilizer in bipolar disorder.

Name: Methylcobalamin
Information: Methylcobalamin is one active form of vitamin B12 which can directly participate in homocysteine metabolism. It is used to treat some nutritional diseases and other diseases in clinic, such as Alzheimer's disease and rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Tavaborole (AN-2690)
Information: Tavaborole (AN-2690) is a boron-containing small molecule with broad spectrum antifungal activity.

Name: Avermectin B1(Abamectin)
Information: Avermectin B1 (Abamectin) is a widely used insecticide and anthelmintic.

Name: Tofacitinib (CP-690550) Citrate
Information: Tofacitinib citrate (CP-690550 citrate) is a novel inhibitor of JAK with IC50 of 1 nM, 20 nM and 112 nM against JAK3, JAK2, and JAK1, respectively.

Name: Fingolimod (FTY720) HCl
Information: Fingolimod (FTY720) HCl is a S1P antagonist with IC50 of 0.033 nM in K562, and NK cells.

Name: Tacrolimus (FK506)
Information: Tacrolimus (FK506) is a 23-membered macrolide lactone, it reduces peptidyl-prolyl isomerase activity in T cells by binding to the immunophilin FKBP12 (FK506 binding protein) creating a new complex.

Name: Pimecrolimus
Information: Pimecrolimus is an immunophilin ligand, which binds specifically to the cytosolic receptor, immunophilin macrophilin-12 (FKBP-12) a calcineurin inhibitor.

Name: Cefotiam hydrochloride
Information: Cefotiam hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of cefotiam and has a broad spectrum of activity against both gram-positive and gram-negative microorganisms.

Name: Teprenone
Information: Teprenone, an acylic polyisoprenoid, that is known as tetraprenylacetone or geranylgeranylacetone, is an anti-ulcer drug, clinically used for gastritis.

Name: Delamanid
Information: Delamanid is a new anti-tuberculosis drug with an excellent intracellular bactericidal activity and a high accumulation rate.

Name: Brivudine
Information: Brivudine is a uridine derivative and nucleoside analog with pro-apoptotic and chemosensitizing properties. It is incorporated into the viral DNA and blocks the action of DNA polymerases, thus inhibiting viral replication.

Name: Indometacin Sodium
Information: Indometacin is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used most commonly for the treatment of inflammation and pain resulting from rheumatic disease (arthritis), and less commonly in postoperative pain management. When taken for chronic pain conditions, indometacin has been associated with a high incidence of adverse events. The benefits and harms of orally-administered indometacin for postoperative pain are not clear.

Name: Octenidine Dihydrochloride
Information: Octenidine, a cationic surfactant, is active against gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria.

Name: Ioversol
Information: Ioversol is an organoiodine compound used as a radiographic contrast agent.

Name: Crisaborole (AN2728)
Information: Crisaborole is a small-molecule, boron-based, selective PDE4 inhibitor and has broad-spectrum anti-inflammatory activity.

Name: Simeprevir
Information: Simeprevir is a competitive, reversible, macrocyclic, noncovalent hepatitis C virus (HCV) NS3/4A protease inhibitor that acts directly against the hepatitis C virus. It has a medium inhibitory concentration (IC50) <13 nM for all HCV NS3/4A enzymes(genotypes 1a, 1b, 2, 4, 5, and 6), but has an IC50 value of 37 nM for genotype 3.

Name: Isoprinosine
Information: Isoprinosine is an immunopharmacologic agent with antiviral activities.

Name: Oxyclozanide
Information: Oxyclozanide is a salicylanilide anthelmintic and mitochondrial uncoupling anthelmintic drug approved for veterinary use.

Name: Indobufen
Information: Indobufen is a reversible platelet aggregation inhibitor. It inhibits the platelet cyclooxygenase enzyme and suppresses thromboxane synthesis.

Name: Tilorone dihydrochloride
Information: Tilorone dihydrochloride is a broad-spectrum, orally active antiviral agent that activates interferon production. It has antitumor, anti-inflammatory properties.

Name: Nadolol
Information: Nadolol is a non-selective beta-adrenergic antagonist with antihypertensive and antiarrhythmic activities.

Name: Efinaconazole
Information: Efinaconazole is an inhibitor of 14 alpha-demethylase which is involved in the biosynthesis of ergosterol, a constituent of fungal cell membranes.

Name: Mebeverine Hydrochloride
Information: Mebeverine, a 3-phenylethylamine derivative of methoxybenzamine, acts as a musculotropic antispasmodic agent.
Synonyms: Duspatalin Hydrochloride, Duspatal Hydrochloride, Colofac Hydrochloride

Name: Etofylline
Information: Etofylline is a N-7 substituted theophylline derivative used as a bronchodilator.

Name: Dihydralazine sulphate
Information: Dihydralazine sulphate is a dihydralazine-l,4-phthalazine derivative and used as an antihypertensive drug.

Name: Mephenesin
Information: Mephenesin is centrally acting muscle relaxant, a topical analgesic and may be an NMDA receptor antagonist.

Name: Terconazole
Information: Terconazole is a new, broad-spectrum, triazole antifungal agent which is primarily used to treat vaginal fungal infections.

Name: Melitracen hydrochloride
Information: Melitracen hydrochloride is a potential dopamine D1/2 receptor antagonist which has antidepressant properties.

Name: Phenazine methosulfate
Information: Phenazine methosulfate is widely used as an intermediate electron carrier for coupling the production of NADH or NADPH to the reduction of tetrazolium salts to coloured formazans.

Name: Valethamate Bromide
Information: Valethamate bromide is an alkylbenzene which is useful for facilitating cervical ripening, dilatation and thereby decreasing the duration of labor.

Name: Tiamulin
Information: Tiamulin is a semisynthetic pleuromutilin antibiotic that binds to the ribosomal peptidyl transferase centre and inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Difloxacin hydrochloride
Information: Difloxacin is a second-generation, synthetic fluoroquinolone antimicrobial antibiotic used in veterinary medicine.

Name: Bevantolol hydrochloride
Information: Bevantolol hydrochloride is a cardioselective, beta adrenoceptor antagonist, devoid of intrinsic β sympathomimetic activity and with weak membrane-stabilizing and local anesthetic properties.

Name: Benorylate
Information: Benorylate is the esterification product of paracetamol and acetylsalicylic acid with anti-inflammatory, analgesic and antipyretic properties.

Name: Clonixin
Information: Clonixin is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug with analgesic, antipyretic, and platelet-inhibitory actions.

Name: Thiocolchicoside
Information: Thiocolchicoside is a natural occuring glycoside originated from the flower seeds of superba gloriosa with anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties as well as pronounced convulsant activity. It is also an antagonist of GABAA receptor.

Name: Granisetron
Information: Granisetron is a serotonin receptor (5HT-3 selective) antagonist that is used as an antiemetic and antinauseant for cancer chemotherapy.

Name: Imazalil
Information: Imazalil is a fungicide widely used in agriculture, also used in veterinary medicine as a topical antimycotic.

Name: Rifamycin sodium salt
Information: The antibiotics, rifamycin SV and rifampicin, are known to interfere with hepatic bile salt and organic anion uptake.

Name: Milbemycin Oxime
Information: Milbemycin Oxime is a broad spectrum anti-parasitic drug that is active against worms (anthelmintic) and mites (miticide).

Name: Dinoprost tromethamine
Information: Dinoprost Tromethamine is a synthetic analogue of the naturally occurring prostaglandin F2 alpha, which stimulates myometrial activity, relaxes the cervix, inhibits corpus luteal steroidogenesis, and induces luteolysis by direct action on the corpus luteum.
Synonyms: Dinolytic, PGF2-alpha tham, Zinoprost, Prostin F2 alpha, Dinoprost Trometamol

Name: Revaprazan Hydrochloride
Information: Revaprazan Hydrochloride is a new reversible proton pump inhibitor with long-lasting acid-suppressive effects.

Name: Pixantrone Maleate
Information: Pixantrone is a novel aza-anthracenedione compound with antitumor activity. It is a weak topoisomerase II inhibitor and forms stable DNA adducts through alkylation with specificity for DNA hypermethylated sites.

Name: Metadoxine
Information: Metadoxine, also known as pyridoxine-pyrrolidone carboxylate, is a drug used to treat chronic and acute alcohol intoxication.

Name: Daclatasvir Digydrochloride
Information: Daclatasvir is an orally available antiviral agent that inhibits the NS5A region of the hepatitis C virus (HCV) used for the treatment of chronic HCV genotype 1 and 3 infection.

Name: Trelagliptin succinate
Information: Trelagliptin succinate is a dipeptidyl peptidase IV (DPP-4) inhibitor which is used as a new long-acting drug for once-weekly treatment of type 2 diabetes mellitus (DM).

Name: Ganciclovir sodium
Information: Ganciclovir sodium is an antiviral medication used to treat cytomegalovirus (CMV) infections

Name: Pramipexole dihydrochloride
Information: Pramipexole dihydrochloride is a dopamine agonist of the non-ergoline class indicated for treating Parkinson's disease (PD) and restless legs syndrome (RLS) with Ki values of 3.9 nM, 2.2 nM, 0.5 nM and 5.1 nM for D2S receptor, D2L receptor, D3 receptor and D4 receptor.

Name: Losartan
Information: Losartan D4 is the deuterium labeled Losartan. Losartan is an angiotensin II receptor antagonist, competing with the binding of angiotensin II to AT1 receptors with IC50 of 20 nM.

Name: Dabrafenib Mesylate
Information: Dabrafenib Mesylate is the mesylate salt form of dabrafenib, an orally bioavailable inhibitor of B-raf (BRAF) protein with IC50s of 0.8 nM, 3.2 nM and 5 nM for B-Raf (V600E), B-Raf (WT) and C-Raf, respectively.

Name: Mupirocin calcium
Information: Mupirocin Calcium is the calcium salt form of mupirocin, a natural crotonic acid derivative extracted from Pseudomonas fluorescens,which inhibits bacterial protein synthesis and is used as an antibiotic.

Name: Duloxetine
Information: Duloxetine(LY-248686) is a potent inhibitor of serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine, 5-HT) and noradrenaline (NE) uptake in vitro and in vivo and is 3- to 5-times more effective at inhibiting 5-HT uptake.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Donepezil
Information: Donepezil is a piperidine based, potent, specific, non-competitive and reversible inhibitor of acetylcholinesterase (AChE) used for the treatment of mild to moderate dementia of the Alzheimer's type.

It has potent inhibitory activity against hepatic ATP-citrate lyase(IC50=29 uM).

Name: Empagliflozin (BI 10773)

Name: Apremilast (CC-10004)

Name: Cobimetinib (GDC-0973, RG7420)

Phase 3.

Information: Oclacitinib(PF 03394197) is a novel inhibitor of JAK family members with IC50 ranging from 10 to 99 nM and JAK1-dependent cytokines with IC50 ranging from 36 to 249 nM. It does not inhibit a panel of 38 non-JAK kinases.

Name: Enasidenib (AG-221)
Information: Enasidenib (AG-221) is a first-in-class, oral, potent, reversible, selective inhibitor of the IDH2 mutant enzyme with IC50 of 12 nM.

Name: Ivosidenib (AG-120)
Information: Ivosidenib (AG-120) is an orally available inhibitor of isocitrate dehydrogenase type 1 (IDH1), with potential antineoplastic activity.

Name: Olmutinib (HM61713, BI 1482694)
Information: Olmutinib is a novel third-generation epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) mutation-specific tyrosine kinase inhibitor (TKI). Also a potent inhibitor of Bruton's tyrosine kinase.

Name: Irbinitinib (ARRY-380, ONT-380)
Information: ARRY-380 (ONT-380) is an oral, potent, selective, reversible and ATP-competitive small-molecule inhibitor of ErbB-2 (also called HER2) with IC50s of 8 nM and 7 nM for ErbB-2 and p95 HER2, respectively in cell-based assays, showing ~500-fold selective for HER2 vs EGFR. It has potential antineoplastic activity.

Name: Erdafitinib (JNJ-42756493)
Information: Erdafitinib (JNJ-42756493) is a potent and selective orally bioavailable, pan fibroblast growth factor receptor (FGFR) inhibitor with potential antineoplastic activity.

Name: Troglitazone (CS-045)
Information: Troglitazone is a potent agonist for the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-(PPAR) that is a ligand activated transcription factor regulating cell differentiation and growth.
Synonyms: Rezulin, Romglizone, Prelay, CS-045, CS045, CS 045, Romozin

Name: TAS-102
Information: TAS-102 is an orally administered combination of a thymidine-based nucleic acid analogue, trifluridine, and a thymidine phosphorylase inhibitor, tipiracil hydrochloride.

Name: Voxelotor(GBT440, GTx011)
Information: Voxelotor(GBT440, GTx011) is a novel small molecule hemoglobin modifier which increases hemoglobin oxygen affinity.

Name: Tofogliflozin(CSG 452)
Information: Tofogliflozin is a novel sodium-glucose co-transporter 2(SGLT2) inhibitor with IC50 values of 2.9 nM and 8444 nM for hSGLT2 and hSGLT1, respectively.

Name: Omarigliptin (MK-3102)
Information: Omarigliptin (MK-3102) is a competitive, reversible inhibitor of DPP-4 (IC50 = 1.6 nM, Ki = 0.8 nM). It is highly selective over all proteases tested (IC50 > 67 μM), including QPP, FAP, PEP, DPP8, and DPP9 and has weak ion channel activity (IC50 > 30 μM at IKr, Caγ1.2, and Naγ1.5).

Name: Tucidinostat (Chidamide)
Information: Chidamide is a low nanomolar inhibitor of HDAC1, 2, 3, and 10, the HDAC isotypes well documented to be associated with the malignant phenotype with IC50 values of 95, 160, 67, 78 nM for HDAC1, 2, 3, 10 respectively.

Name: Tirofiban Hydrochloride
Information: Tirofiban Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of tirofiban, a selective platelet GPIIb/IIIa antagonist which inhibits platelet aggregation. It is more soluable than Tirofiban.

Name: Sodium dichloroacetate (DCA)
Information: Dichloroacetate, a specific inhibitor of pyruvate dehydrogenase kinase (PDK) with IC50 values of 183 and 80 μM for PDK2 and PDK4 respectively, has been shown to derepress a mitochondrial potassium-ion channel axis, trigger apoptosis in cancer cells, and inhibit tumor growth.

Name: Ipragliflozin (ASP1941)
Information: Ipragliflozin (ASP1941) is a highly selective sodium-glucose cotransporter 2 (SGLT2) inhibitor with an IC50 value of 7.4 nM for hSGLT2 and a 254-fold selectivity versus SGLT1.

Name: Anlotinib (AL3818) dihydrochloride
Information: Anlotinib (AL3818) is a highly potent and selective VEGFR2 inhibitor with IC50 less than 1 nM. It has broad-spectrum antitumor potential in clinical trials.

Name: Ripretinib (DCC-2618)
Information: DCC-2618 is an orally bioavailable switch pocket control inhibitor of wild-type and mutated forms of the tumor-associated antigens (TAA) mast/stem cell factor receptor (SCFR) KIT and PDGFR-alpha, with IC50 values of 4 nM, 8 nM, 18 nM, 5 nM and 14 nM for WT KIT, V654A KIT, T670I KIT, D816H KIT and D816V KIT, respectively.

Name: Zanubrutinib (BGB-3111)
Information: Zanubrutinib (BGB-3111) is a potent, specific and irreversible BTK inhibitor that has been shown to have a lower off-target inhibitory activity on other kinases, including ITK, JAK3 and EGFR.

Name: HS-10296
Information: HS-10296 is a small molecule inhibitor of EGFR-activating mutations and T790M-resistant mutation with limited activity against wild-type EGFR.

Name: Omadacycline tosylate
Information: Omadacycline is a first-in-class aminomethylcycline antibiotic, demonstrating antimicrobial activity in vitro against a range of Gram-positive and Gram-negative aerobes and some anaerobic bacteria.

Name: Letermovir(AIC246)
Information: Letermovir(AIC246, MK-8228) is a novel  anti-CMV  compound which targets the viral terminase complex and remains active against virus resistant to DNA polymerase inhibitors.

Name: Malic acid
Information: Malic acid is a dicarboxylic acid that can be prepared by hydration of maleic acid or fumaric acid

Name: L-Fucose
Information: L-Fucose (6-Deoxy-L-galactose) is used in studies of fucoidan polysaccharide containing glycans

Name: (R)-(-)-Mandelic acid
Information: (R)-(-)-Mandelic acid has been used in studies to assess its ability to undergo spontaneous oscillatory chiral conversion and spontaneous condensation to form polymandelic acid.

Name: 2'-Deoxyguanosine monohydrate
Information: Deoxyguanosine(2'-Deoxyguanosine) is composed of the purine nucleoside guanine linked by its N9 nitrogen to the C1 carbon of deoxyribose.

Name: Sanguinarine
Information: Sanguinarine is a specific inhibitor of Rac1b  with anti-microbial, anti-oxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.

Name: Wedelolactone
Information: Wedelolactone inhibits NF-κB-mediated gene transcription in cells by blocking the phosphorylation and degradation of IκBα.

Name: Berberine
Information:
Berberine is a potent oral hypoglycemic agent with beneficial effects on lipid metabolism.
Berberine may as a broad-spectrum anti-microbial medicine,  a complementary therapeutic agent for HIV/AIDS.
Berberine seems to act as an herbal antidepressant and a neuroprotector against neurodegenerative disorders.
Berberine is used in histology for staining heparin in mast cells. As a natural dye, berberine has a colour index of 75160. 
Berberine reduces hepatic fat content in rats with nonalcoholic fatty liver disease;  also prevents proliferation of hepatic stellate cells (HSCs), which are central for the development of fibrosis during liver injury.
Berberine can ameliorate proinflammatory cytokines-induced intestinal epithelial tight junction damage in vitro, and berberine may be one of the targeted therapeutic agents that can restore barrier function in intestinal disease states.
Berberine has  antineoplastic effects, including breast cancer, leukemia, melanoma, epidermoid carcinoma, hepatoma, pancreatic cancer, oral carcinoma, tongue carcinoma, glioblastoma, prostate carcinoma and gastric carcinoma, etc.

Name: Harringtonine
Information: Harringtonine, a natural Cephalotaxus alkaloid, is an inhibitor of protein synthesis.

Name: Pulegone
Information:
Pulegone has cytotoxicity followed by regenerative cell proliferation is the MOA for Pulegone-induced urothelial tumors in female rats.
Pulegone induces a verapamil-sensitive psychostimulant effect that appears to independ on the opening of L-type calcium channels. 
Pulegone has negative reinforcing properties and seems to possess anxiolytic-like actions unrelated to the benzodiazepine site of the γ-aminobutyric acid type A (GABAA) receptor.
DMSO (mM)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Berbamine
Information:
Berbamine has high binding affinity toward the (GGA)8  G-quadruplex.
Berbamine and its derivatives are promising agents to suppress liver cancer growth by targeting CAMKII.
Berbamine may be the first ATP-competitive inhibitor of CaMKII γ, could be as a new type of molecular targeted agent through inhibition of the CaMKII γ activity for treatment of leukemia.
Berbamine can enhance the antitumor activity of gemcitabine by inhibiting cell growth and inducing apoptosis, possibly through the regulation of the expression of apoptosis-related proteins and the activation of TGF-β/Smad signaling pathway. 
Berbamine confers cardioprotection against I/R injury by attenuating [Ca(2+)inf(i) overloading and preventing calpain activation through the activation of the PI3K-Akt-GSK3β pathway and, subsequently, opening of the mitoK(ATP) channel.

Name: Sparteine
Information: Inhibition of human CYP2D6 expressed in Escherichia coli JM109
DMSO (mM)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Ammonium Glycyrrhizate
Information: Glycyrrhizic acid ammonium salt has wound healing activity.

Name: Catharanthine hemitartrate
Information: Catharanthine hemitartrate is the starting material for the synthesis of the antitumor drugs vinblastine and vincristine.

Name: Aristolochic acid A
Information: Aristolochic acid A is a carcinogenic, mutagenic, and nephrotoxic agent extracted from the flowering plant family Aristolochiaceae.
Synonyms: Aristolochic Acid I, Aristolochin, Aristolochine, TR 1736

Name: Melamine
Information:
Melamine has nephrotoxic, the combination of melamine and cyanuric acid  can cause acute renal failure in cats. 
 The intumescent system additives( filled with ammonium polyphosphate, pentaerythritol and melamine) is an effective flame retardant on improving combustion properties for polypropylene.

Name: Dipotassium glycyrrhizinate
Information: Dipotassium glycyrrhizinate is an anionic surfactant having anti-allergic and anti-inflammatory activities.

Name: Sinensetin
Information: Sinensetin is a methylated flavone found in certain citrus fruits. pocess potent antiangiogenesis and anti-inflammatory, sinensetin enhances adipogenesis and lipolysis.

Name: Isofraxidin
Information:
Isofraxidin possesses significant analgesic and anti-inflammatory activities that may be mediated through the regulation of pro-inflammatory cytokines, TNF-α and the phosphorylation of p38 and ERK1/
Isofraxidin has definite anti-bacterial, anti-oxidant, and anti-inflammatory activities, it also has a protective effect against LPS-induced acute lung injury (ALI), and the protective effect of IF seems to result from the inhibition of COX-2 protein expression in the lung, which regulates the production of PGE2.
Isofraxidin inhibits expression of MMP-7 and in vitro cell invasion at a non-toxic level through inhibiting ERK1/2 phosphorylation in hepatoma cell lines, which suggest isofraxidin might become an effective agent for suppressing hepatoma cell invasion.
Isofraxidin is one possible radio-protector, it can protect leukemia cells from radiation-induced apoptosis via ROS/mitochondria pathway in a p53-independent manner.

Name: Securinine
Information: (-)-Securinine is plant-derived alkaloid and also a GABAA receptor antagonist.

Name: Corydaline
Information:
Corydaline, an isoquinoline alkaloid, is one of the major active constituents in a new prokinetic botanical agent. 
Corydaline promotes gastric emptying and small intestinal transit and facilitates gastric accommodation.
Corydaline exhibits the anti-acetylcholinesterase, antiallergic, and antinociceptive activities.
Corydaline has potent inhibition of CYP2C19 and CYP2C9.

Name: 3-n-Butylphathlide
Information:
Dl-3-n-Butylphthalide has antihypertensive effects, may slow the progression of hypertensive nephropathy by a variety of mechanisms.
