Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Tenofovir Disoproxil (Bis(POC)-PMPA, GS 4331) is a prodrug of tenofovir, which is metabolised intracellularly to its active anabolite tenofovir diphosphate, a competitive inhibitor of HIV-1 reverse transcriptase and terminates the growing DNA chain.

Name: Dabigatran etexilate mesylate
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Dabigatran etexilate mesylate (Pradaxa, BIBR 1048MS, Dabigatran etexilate methanesulfonate) is an orally active prodrug of Dabigatran which is a reversible and selective, direct thrombin inhibitor (DTI). Dabigatran selectively and reversibly inhibits human thrombin with Ki of 4.5 nM and thrombin-induced platelet aggregation with IC50 of 10 nM.

Name: Sulfathiazole sodium
Information: Sulfathiazole sodium, an antimicrobial agent, is an organosulfur compound that has been used as a short-acting sulfa drug.

Name: Urapidil
Information: Urapidil is an antihypertensive drug acting as an α1 adrenoreceptor antagonist and a 5-HT1A agonist.

Name: Amlodipine maleate
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Pharmacopoeia: EP10.5, USP43-NF38, KP Ⅹ, JP17, IP2010
Information: Amlodipine (Amvaz, UK-48340) maleate is a long-acting calcium channel blocker, used to lower blood pressure and prevent chest pain.

Name: Dicloxacillin Sodium hydrate
Pharmacopoeia: EP10.5, USP43-NF38, KP Ⅹ, JP17, IP2010
Information: Dicloxacillin Sodium hydrate (DLX, Dycill, Dynapen, Pathocil), a narrow-spectrum β-Lactam antibiotic of the penicillin class, induces drug-metabolizing CYP enzymes to a clinically relevant extent.

Name: Pemetrexed
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Pemetrexed (LY231514, Alimta) is a novel antifolate and antimetabolite for thymidylate synthase (TS), dihydrofolate reductase (DHFR) and glycinamide ribonucleotide formyltransferase (GARFT) with Ki of 1.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 65 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Pemetrexed induces autophagy and apoptosis.

Name: Hydrocortisone hemisuccinate
Information: Hydrocortisone hemisuccinate (A-hydrocort, Hydrocortisone 21-hemisuccinate), a physiological glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory properties, is an inhibitor of proinflammatory cytokine with IC50 of 6.7 μM and 21.4 μM for Interleukin-6 (IL-6) and IL-3, respectively.

Name: Methylprednisolone Acetate
Pharmacopoeia: EP10.5, USP43-NF38, KP Ⅹ, JP17, IP2010
Information: Methylprednisolone (NSC-19987, Medrol) acetate is a synthetic glucocorticoid receptor agonist, used to achieve prompt suppression of inflammation. Methylprednisolone activates ACE2 and reduces IL-6 levels, thus improves severe or critical COVID-19. Methylprednisolone markedly reduces autophagy and apoptosis.

Name: S(-)-Propranolol hydrochloride
Information: (S)-(-)-Propranolol hydrochloride, the active enantiomer of propranolol, is a β-Adrenoceptor (β-Adrenergic Receptor) antagonist with log Kd values of -8.16, -9.08, and -6.93 for β1, β2, and β3, respectively.

Name: Purine
Information: Purine is a heterocyclic aromatic organic compound which plays crucial roles in DNA and RNA. It is also significant components in a number of other important biomolecules, such as ATP, GTP, cyclic AMP, NADH, and coenzyme A.

Name: Oxolamine Citrate
Information: Oxolamine (SKF-9976, AF-438) citrate, a cough suppressant, is an inhibitor of CYP2B1/2. Oxolamine citrate also exhibits anti-inflammatory effect.

Name: Sodium tauroglycocholate
Information: Sodium tauroglycocholate (STGC, Tauroglycocholic acid sodium salt) is an absorption enhancer of transdermal permeation of drug.

Name: Eicosapentaenoic acid ethyl ester
Information: Eicosapentaenoic acid ethyl ester (AMR101, EPA ethyl ester, Ethyl eicosapentaenoate) is an omega-3 fatty acid agent that significantly reduces the triglyceride (TG) levels and improves other lipid parameters without significantly increasing the low-density lipoprotein (LDL) cholesterol levels.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Synonyms: AMR101, EPA ethyl ester, Ethyl eicosapentaenoate

Name: amdinocillin
Information: Amdinocillin (Mecillinam, Coactin, FL 1060) is a β-lactam antibiotic with a broad spectrum of antibacterial activity. Amdinocillin is active alone against many gram-negative organisms.

Name: Lusutrombopag
Information: Lusutrombopag (Mulpleta, S-888711) is an orally bioavailable thrombopoietin (TPO) receptor agonist being developed for chronic liver disease (CLD).

Name: Chloroquine
Information: Chloroquine (Aralen, CHQ, CQ) is an antimalarial drug and autophagy/lysosome inhibitor. Chloroquine also suppresses Toll-like receptor-9 (TLR9) protein expression. Chloroquine is highly effective agianst SARS-CoV-2 (COVID-19) infection with EC50 of 1.13 μM in Vero E6 cells. Chloroquine has anti-HIV-1 activity.

Name: Fostemsavir
Information: Fostemsavir (BMS-663068, Rukobia), the phosphonooxymethyl prodrug of BMS626529, is an attachment inhibitor that targets HIV-1 gp120 and prevents its binding to CD4+ T cells with EC50 of < 10 nM.

Name: Remdesivir (GS-5734)
Information: Remdesivir (GS-5734), a monophosphoramidate prodrug of an adenosine analog, is an investigational broad-spectrum antiviral agent with in vitro activity against multiple RNA viruses, including Ebola and CoV.

Name: Puromycin aminonucleoside
Information: Puromycin aminonucleoside (NSC 3056, PAN, Stylomycin aminonucleoside, ARDMA, SAN), the aminonucleoside portion of the antibiotic puromycin, is a reversible inhibitor of dipeptidyl-peptidase II and cytosol alanyl aminopeptidase that induces apoptosis in mesangial cells (MCs) accompanied by declined cell viability and enhanced inflammatory response.
Synonyms: NSC 3056, PAN, Stylomycin aminonucleoside, ARDMA, SAN

Name: Vericiguat
Information: Vericiguat (BAY1021189, Verquvo) is a potent, orally available and soluble guanylate cyclase (sGC) stimulator.

Name: GS-9876 (lanraplenib)
Information: Lanraplenib (GS-9876, GS-SYK) is a potent, highly selective and orally active inhibitor of Spleen Tyrosine Kinase (SYK) with IC50 of 9.5 nM. Lanraplenib inhibits SYK activity in platelets via the glycoprotein VI (GPVI) receptor without prolonging bleeding time (BT) in monkeys or humans.

Name: 6-Aminonicotinamide
Information: 6-Aminonicotinamide (6AN) is an antimetabolite used to inhibit the NADPH-producing pentose phosphate pathway (PPP) in many cellular systems, making them more susceptible to oxidative stress. 6-Aminonicotinamide is a competitive inhibitor of NADP+-dependent enzyme glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (G6PD) with Ki of 0.46 μM.

Name: Iodoacetamide
Information: Iodoacetamide (IA, IAM, 2-Iodoacetamide) is an alkylating agent that is commonly used for alkylation of cysteine during sample preparation for proteomics.

Name: Remogliflozin etabonate (GSK189075)
Information: Remogliflozin etabonate (GSK189075) is an orally active, selective and low-affinity inhibitor of sodium glucose cotransporter (SGLT2) with Ki of 1950 nM, 2140 nM, 43100 nM, 8570 nM for hSGLT2, rSGLT2, hSGLT1, rSGLT1, respectively. Remogliflozin etabonate exhibits antidiabetic efficacy in rodent models.

Name: Olodaterol (BI 1744)
Information: Olodaterol (BI 1744) is a long-acting β2-adrenergic receptor agonist that is used as a component of an inhalation (Tiotropium/Olodaterol) for treating patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

Name: (R)-(-)-Ibuprofen
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC
Information: (R)-(-)-Ibuprofen ((R)-Ibuprofen) inhibits the activation of NF-κB in response to T-cell stimulation with IC50 of 121.8 μM. R(-)-ibuprofen exerts anti-inflammatory and antinociceptive effects.

Name: Alpha-Estradiol
Information: Alpha-Estradiol (α-Estradiol, 17 alpha-Estradiol, Alfatradiol, Epiestradiol, Epiestrol, Alora, 17 α-E2), a natural, non-feminizing stereoisomer, a hormonally almost inactive isomer of physiological 17 beta-estradiol (17 β-E2), is a weak inhibitor of estrogen.
Synonyms: α-Estradiol, 17alpha-Estradiol, Alfatradiol, Epiestradiol, Epiestrol, Alora, 17 α-E2

Name: Glycerol phenylbutyrate
Information: Glycerol phenylbutyrate (GT4P, HPN-100M, Ravicti) is a nitrogen-binding agent and acts as a sigma-2 (σ2) receptor ligand with a pKi of 8.02. Glycerol phenylbutyrate is a prodrug in which phenylbutyrate (PBA) is released from the glycerol backbone by lipases in the gastrointestinal tract.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Varenicline
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Varenicline is highly selective and blocks more potently to α4β2 receptors than to other common nicotinic receptors (>500-fold α3β4, >3,500-fold α7, >20,000-fold α1βγδ), or to non-nicotinic receptors and transporters (>2,000-fold). Varenicline also acts as an agonist of 5-HT3 serotonine receptors.

Name: Iron Dextran
Information: Iron dextran (Fero Gradumet, Conferon, Fe dextran, INFeD) is an anti-anemia drug that can be used in the study of iron-deficiency anemia in animals.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Synonyms: Fero Gradumet, Conferon, Fe dextran, INFeD

Name: Gadoteridol
Information: Gadoteridol (ProHance, SQ-32692, Gd-HP-DO3A) is a nonionic contrast agent for magnetic resonance imaging (MRI).

Name: Isosulfan Blue
Information: Isosulfan Blue (Lymphazurin dye) is a blue dye used as a visual imaging agent in lymph node mapping procedures.

Name: Triheptanoin
Information: Triheptanoin (API, IND106011, UX007, Glycerol trienanthate) is a synthetic, medium-chain triglyceride consisting of three odd-chain 7-carbon (heptanoate) fatty acids on a glycerol backbone. Triheptanoin is used for treatment of fatty acid oxidation disorders and GLUT1.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Dipivefrin Hydrochloride
Information: Dipivefrin (Dipivefrine,  Propine, Pivalephrine) is a prodrug of epinephrine which is hydrolyzed to epinephrine after absorption into the eye.

Name: Cyclizine
Information: Cyclizine is a piperazine first-generation antagonist of histamine 1 receptor.

Name: Propidium Iodide
Information: Propidium iodide (PI) is a red-fluorescent DNA stain which penetrates only damaged cellular membranes. Propidium iodide (PI) is described for use in the determination of cell viability in cell suspension.

Name: Saquinavir (Ro 31-8959)
Information: Saquinavir (Ro 31-8959) is a potent and selective inhibitor of HIV proteinase with a mean IC50 of 2.7 nM in JM cells.

Name: Imeglimin (EMD 387008) Hydrochloride
Information: Imeglimin (EMD 387008, IMEG, PXL 008, RVT-1501) Hydrochloride is a new class of oral glucose-lowering agents. Imeglimin normalizes glucose tolerance and insulin sensitivity by preserving mitochondrial function from oxidative stress and favoring lipid oxidation in liver of HFHSD mice.
Synonyms: PXL 008 Hydrochloride, RVT-1501 Hydrochloride, IMEG Hydrochloride

Name: Bradykinin
Information: Bradykinin is a potent vasodilator peptide that exerts its vasodilatory action through stimulation of specific endothelial B2 receptors, thereby causing the release of prostacyclin, NO, and EDHF.

Name: β-Cyclodextrin
Information: β-Cyclodextrin (β-CD, Beta-Cyclodextrin) is a cyclic derivative of starch prepared from partially hydrolyzed starch (maltodextrin) by an enzymatic process. β-Cyclodextrin can be used as complexing agents to increase aqueous solubility of poorly soluble drugs and to increase their bioavailability and stability.

Name: Baloxavir
Information: Baloxavir (Baloxavir acid, S-033447) is a first-in-class, potent and selective cap-dependent endonuclease (CEN) inhibitor with an IC50 of 2.5 nM. BXA inhibits viral RNA transcription via selective inhibition of CEN activity.

Name: Vernakalant (RSD1235) Hydrochloride
Information: Vernakalant (RSD-1235, MK-6621) is a novel, frequency-dependent Na+ channel and early activating K+ channel blocker that selectively prolongs the atrial refractory period.

Name: Linalyl Acetate
Information: Linalyl Acetate (Bergamiol, Bergamol, Linalool acetate) is a naturally occurring phytochemical found in many flowers and spice plants. Linalyl Acetate is a potentially anti-inflammatory agent.
DMSO (mM)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Lithium Chloride
Information: Lithium Chloride (LiCl) inhibits the replication of type 1 and type 2 Herpes simplex virus at concentrations which permitted host cell replication. Lithium chloride also prevents glucocorticoid-induced osteonecrosis of femoral heads and strengthens mesenchymal stem cell activity in rats.

Name: Taurocholic acid sodium salt
Information: Taurocholic acid sodium salt (Sodium Taurocholate, TANa) is a sodium salt of taurocholic acid and occurs in the bile of mammals. Taurocholic acid  is used as a cholagogue and choleretic.

Name: Thioacetamide
Information: Thioacetamide (TAA) is a hepatotoxin frequently used for experimental purposes which produces centrilobular necrosis after a single dose administration.

Name: Hexaminolevulinate hydrochloride
Information: Hexaminolevulinate hydrochloride (5-Aminolevulinic acid hexyl ester hydrochloride) is a tumour photosensitizer.

Name: Phenelzine sulfate
Information: Phenelzine Sulfate is a hydrazine derivative and acts as a potent non-selective monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.9 μM.

Name: Tazobactam Sodium
Status: FDA, EMA, HMA, CFDA, PMDA, NDC
Information: Tazobactam (Tazobactam acid, Tazobactamum) Sodium is a beta-lactamase inhibitor that prevents the breakdown of other antibiotics by beta-lactamase enzyme producing organisms.

Name: Zinc acetate
Information: Zinc acetate induces the expression of enterocyte metallothionein.

Name: Imidacloprid
Information: Imidacloprid is a nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) agonist with potent insecticidal activity.

Name: Betamethasone sodium phosphate
Pharmacopoeia: JP18, USP–NF 2021(Issue 2), EP10.5, KP Ⅹ, IP2010
Information: Betamethasone sodium phosphate (Betamethasone 21-Phosphate Disodium Salt) is a potent glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory activity.

Name: Hydrocortisone sodium succinate
Pharmacopoeia: JP18, USP–NF 2021(Issue 2), KP Ⅹ, Ph.Int_6th, IP2010
Information: Hydrocortisone sodium succinate (Hydrocortisone 21-hemisuccinate sodium salt) has significant inhibitory effects on the IL-6 bioactivity with IC50 of 6.7 μM. Hydrocortisone sodium succinate can bind to glucocorticoid receptor, initiating the transcription of anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive mediators.

Name: Zinc acetate dihydrate
Information: Zinc acetate dihydrate (Acetic acid zinc salt dihydrate, Dicarbomethoxyzinc dihydrate) contributes to the antiviral activity of microbicide gel through zinc targeting the reverse transcriptase.
Synonyms: Acetic acid zinc salt dihydrate, Dicarbomethoxyzinc dihydrate

Name: Magnesium chloride
Pharmacopoeia: USP–NF 2021(Issue 2), EP10.5, KP Ⅹ, JP17, IP2010
Information: Magnesium chloride can reduce the activated thromboplastin times.

Name: Enclomiphene Citrate
Information: Enclomiphene citrate is the trans isomer of clomiphene citrate and acts as a non-steroidal estrogen receptor antagonist.

Name: Setmelanotide (RM-493)
Information: Setmelanotide (RM-493, BIM-22493, CAM 4072) is a cyclic peptide full agonist of melanocortin-4 receptor (MC4R) with an EC50 of 0.27 nM and a Ki of 2.1 nM.

Name: Miglustat
Information: Miglustat (Zavesca, N‐butyldeoxynojirimycin, OGT 918) is an orally administered ceramide glucosyltransferase inhibitor which prevents the lysosomal accumulation of glucocerebroside.

Name: Abaloparatide (BA058)
Information: Abaloparatide (BA058, BIM-44058, ITM-058) is a novel 34-amino acid peptide selected to be a potent and selective activator of the parathyroid hormone receptor (PTH1R) signaling pathway with an IC50 of 0.117 nM in SOST analysis.

Name: Cycloguanil hydrochloride
Information: Cycloguanil hydrochloride, an active metabolite of proguanil, acts on malaria schizonts in erythrocytes and hepatocytes.

Name: Euquinine
Information: Euquinine is generally used as a febrifuge, antimalarial, and tonic.

Name: Fenoldopam
Information: Fenoldopam (SKF 82526) is a selective dopamine-1 (DA1) receptor agonist with natriuretic/diuretic properties with EC50 of 55.5 nM in stimulating cAMP accumulation in LLC-PK1 cells, which is more potent than DA .

Name: DLinDMA
Information: DLinDMA (1,2-dilinoleyloxy-N,N-dimethyl-3-aminopropane) is a key component to facilitate endosomal escape through membrane fusion between the SNALP and the endosomal membranes.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion

Name: Deserpidine
Information: Deserpidine (Harmonyl), an alkaloid isolated from the roots of Rauwolfia canescens, is a competitive angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, also decreases angiotensin II-induced aldosterone secretion by the adrenal cortex.

Name: Mirodenafil Dihydrochloride
Information: Mirodenafil Dihydrochloride(SK-3530 dihydrochloride) is an oral phosphodiesterase type 5 (PDE-5) inhibitor used to treat erectile dysfunction (ED).

Name: Isavuconazonium sulfate
Information: Isavuconazonium sulfate (BAL8557-002), the prodrug of the active triazole Isavuconazole, is an orally active antifungal agent, using for invasive aspergillosis and mucormycosis.

Name: Flumatinib (HH-GV-678)
Information: Flumatinib (HH-GV-678) is a novel inhibitor of Bcr-Abl with IC50 values of 1.2  nM, 307.6  nM and 665.5  nM for c-Abl, PDGFRβand c-Kit, respectively.

Name: Raclopride
Information: Raclopride is a selective dopamine D2/D3 receptor antagonist that discriminates between dopamine-mediated motor functions. Raclopride binds to D2 and D3 receptors with dissociation constants of between 1.8 nM and 3.5 nM, but has a very low affinity for D4 receptors.

Name: Invert sugar
Information: Invert Sugar is a popular sweetener.

Name: DL-α-tocopherol acetate
Information: DL-α-Tocopherol acetate (DL-Alpha-tocopherol acetate , Vitamin E acetate), a vitamin E derivative, is used as a vitamin E supplement in poultry feeds.

Name: Mometasone Furoate Hydrate
Information: Mometasone Furoate (SCH 32088) Hydrate is a synthetic glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory activity.

Name: Rhamnose
Information: Rhamnose is an important 6-deoxy sugar present in many natural products, glycoproteins, and structural polysaccharides.

Name: (R)-Avanafil
Information: R-Avanafil is a strong competitive inhibitor of phosphodiesterase 5 (PDE5) with a demonstrated in vitro IC 50 of 5.2 nM.

Name: Metrizoic acid
Information: Metrizoic acid is a diagnostic radiopaque. The mechanism of action of metrizoic acid is as a X-Ray contrast activity.

Name: Cefatrizine
Information: Cefatrizine, a broad-spectrum, semisynthetic, first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity, binds to and inactivates penicillin-binding proteins (PBPs) located on the inner membrane of the bacterial cell wall.

Name: Norgestimate
Information: Norgestimate, a synthetic progesterone analog, is an orally active progestin with highly selective progestational activity and minimal androgenicity.

Name: Flecainide
Information: Flecainide is a common medication used to help restore and maintain sinus rhythm in patients with atrial fibrillation.

Name: Metipranolol
Information: Metipranolol (Betamann) is potent β-adrenergic receptor antagonist, possessing the beta-blocking potencies (pA2) of 8.3, 8.4 at guinea pig atrial β1-adrenoceptor and β2-adrenoceptor of the rat uterus, respectively, also is a potent displacer of 3H-DHA binding, ligand concentration 0.7 nM, possessing a Ki value of 39 ± 24 nM.

Name: Prednicarbate
Information: Prednicarbate (Dermatop) is a medium potency topical corticosteroid used to manage pruritus and inflammation associated with responsive skin conditions.

Name: Methyl methanesulfonate
Information: Methyl methanesulfonate (MMS), a DNA alkylating agent, modifies both guanine (to 7-methylguanine) and adenine (to 3-methlyladenine) to cause base mispairing and replication blocks, respectively.

Name: γ-Terpinene
Information: γ-Terpinene (γ-TPN), a monoterpene, is an orally active antioxidant compound which can scavenge radicals directly.

Name: Gemifloxacin mesylate
Information: Gemifloxacin mesylate (SB265805 mesylate; LB20304 mesylate) is a novel fluoronaphthyridone with a broad spectrum of antimicrobial activity and enhances activity against gram-positive aerobes.

Name: Nomegestrol Acetate
Information: Nomegestrol Acetate is a potent, highly selective progestogen, which is characterized as a full agonist at the progesterone receptor, with no or minimal binding to other steroid receptors, including the androgen and glucocorticoid receptors.

Name: Masitinib mesylate
Information: Masitinib mesylate (AB-1010 mesylate) is a potent, orally bioavailable, and selective inhibitor of c-Kit with IC50 of 200 nM for human recombinant c-Kit, also inhibits PDGFRα/β with IC50s of 540/800 nM, Lyn with IC50 of 510 nM for LynB, and, to a lesser extent, FGFR3 and FAK.

Name: Rilpivirine Hydrochloride
Information: Rilpivirine (TMC278), is a second-generation non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) with higher potency, longer half-life and reduced side-effect profile compared with older NNRTIs, such as efavirenz.

Name: Oritavancin Diphosphate
Information: Oritavancin Diphosphate is an orally active glycopeptide antibiotic which is active against Gram-positive bacteria and also has antibacterial activity against multidrug-resistant Streptococcus pneumoniae.

Name: Levamlodipine Besylate
Information: Levamlodipine Besylate is a powerful dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker, possessing vasodilation properties and used in the treatment of hypertension and angina.

Name: Segesterone acetate
Information: Segesterone acetate (Nestoron, ST-1435) is a synthetic progestin that binds to the progesterone receptor with EC50 of 50.3 nM.

Name: Insulin Degludec
Information: Insulin degludec is an acylated basal insulin with a unique mechanism of protracted absorption involving the formation of a depot of soluble multihexamer chains after subcutaneous injection, shows a very long duration of action, with a half-life exceeding 25 h in PK/PD studies.

Name: p-Nitrobenzyl mesylate
Information: p-Nitrobenzyl mesylate is an alkylating reagent for direct kinase substrate identification.

Name: Dotinurad
Information: Dotinurad (FYU-981), a selective urate reabsorption inhibitor (SURI), potently inhibits urate transporter 1 (URAT1) with IC50 of 37.2 nM.

Name: Tandospirone
Information: Tandospirone (SM-3997), a potent and selective 5-HT1A receptor partial agonist, with a Ki of 27 nM, has anxiolytic and antidepressant activities.

Name: Azosemide
Information: Azosemide is a potent Na+–K+–2Cl− cotransporter NKCC1 inhibitor with IC50s of 0.246 µM for hNKCC1A and 0.197 µM for NKCC1B, respectively.

Name: Doxorubicin
Information: Adriamycin (Doxorubicin, Hydroxydaunorubicin), a cytotoxic anthracycline antibiotic, is an anti-cancer chemotherapy agent, inhibits topoisomerase II with an IC50 of 2.67 μM, thus stopping DNA replication, and induces apoptosis, also inhibits human DNA topoisomerase I with an IC50 of 0.8 μM.

Name: H-Leu-Leu-OMe Hydrochloride
Information: H-Leu-Leu-OMe Hydrochloride (H-LEU-LEU-OME HCL), a dipeptide condensation product of L-leucine methyl ester generated by human monocytes or polymorphonuclear leukocytes, selectively eliminates lymphocytes with cytotoxic potential, also can induce endolysosomal pathway stress.

Name: Ursodeoxycholic acid sodium
Information: Ursodeoxycholic acid sodium is a sodium salt of a naturally occurring bile acid that is used to treat a variety of hepatic and gastrointestinal diseases.

Name: 3,3'-Diaminobenzidine tetrahydrochloride
Information: 3,3'-Diaminobenzidine tetrahydrochloride (DAB) is the most sensitive and commonly used substrate for horseradish peroxidase, which can visualize the color of cells or tissues bound by horseradish peroxidase during immunohistochemistry or in situ hybridization.

Name: Carbetocin Acetate
Information: Carbetocin Acetate is a long-acting oxytocin-analogue and a potent agonist of the oxytocin receptor (OXTR), with improved in vivo stability over oxytocin.

Name: Bremelanotide Acetate
Information: Bremelanotide Acetate (PT-141 Acetate) is a melanocortin receptor (MCR) agonist recently approved in the USA for the treatment of premenopausal women with acquired, generalized hypoactive sexual desire disorder (HSDD), as characterized by low sexual desire that causes marked distress or interpersonal difficulty.

Name: Etelcalcetide HCl
Information: Etelcalcetide HCl (AMG 416) is a novel synthetic peptide agonist of the calcium-sensing receptor (CaSR) composed of a linear chain of seven d-amino acids with a d-cysteine linked to an l-cysteine via a disulfide bond.

Name: Dasiglucagon
Information: Dasiglucagon, a stable peptide analog of human glucagon, is a fast and effective treatment option for severe hypoglycemia.

Name: Gastrin Tetrapeptide
Information: Gastrin Tetrapeptide (Cholecystokinin tetrapeptide, tetragastrin, CCK-4) is the C-terminal tetrapeptide of gastrin, can stimulate gastric secretion, also is a cholecystokinin (CCK)-4 receptor agonist, with the effect of gastric mucosal protection.

Name: Calcifediol
Information: Calcifediol (Calcidiol, Didrogyl, Hidroferol, 25-hydroxyvitamin D3, 25-Hydroxycholecalciferol) is a major circulating metabolite of vitamin D3 and acts as a competitive inhibitor with an apparent Ki of 3.9 μM. It also suppresses PTH secretion and mRNA (ED50=2 nM).

Name: Talazoparib (BMN 673)
Information: Talazoparib (BMN 673, LT-673) is a novel PARP inhibitor with IC50 of 0.57 nM for PARP1 in a cell-free assay. It is also a potent inhibitor of PARP-2, but does not inhibit PARG and is highly sensitive to PTEN mutation. Phase 3.

Name: Encorafenib (LGX818)
Information: Encorafenib (LGX818) is a highly potent RAF inhibitor with selective anti-proliferative and apoptotic activity in cells expressing B-RAF(V600E) with EC50 of 4 nM. Phase 3.
Formula: C22 H27 Cl F N7 O4 S

Name: Upadacitinib (ABT-494)
Information: Upadacitinib (ABT-494) is a selective JAK1 inhibitor which demonstrates activity against JAK1 (0.045 μM) and JAK2 (0.109 μM), with > 40 fold selectivity over JAK3 (2.1 μM) and 100 fold selectivity over TYK2 (4.7 μM) as compared to JAK1.

Name: Avapritinib (BLU-285)
Information: Avapritinib (BLU-285) is a small molecule kinase inhibitor that potently inhibits PDGFRα D842V mutant activity in vitro (IC50 = 0.5 nM) and PDGFRα D842V autophosphorylation in the cellular setting (IC50 = 30 nM); also a potent inhibitor of the analogous Kit (c-Kit) mutation, D816V in Kit (c-Kit) Exon 17 (IC50 = 0.5 nM).

Name: Deslanoside
Information: Deslanoside(Desacetyllanatoside C) is a cardenolide glycoside, has the effects of anti-arrhythmia and cardiotonic, also is used as an EC 3.6.3.9 (Na+/K+-transporting ATPase) inhibitor.

Name: Laninamivir Octanoate
Information: Laninamivir octanoate (CS-8958, R-118958, Inavir, LANI), a prodrug of Laninamivir (R-125489), is a long-acting neuraminidase (NA) inhibitor with superior anti-influenza virus activity.

Name: Cyclophosphamide
Information: Cyclophosphamide is a nitrogen mustard alkylating agent from the oxazophorines group.

Name: Apatinib (YN968D1) mesylate
Information: Apatinib mesylate (YN968D1, Rivoceranib) is a potent inhibitor of the VEGF signaling pathway with IC50 values of 1 nM, 13 nM, 429 nM and 530 nM for VEGFR-2, Ret (c-Ret), c-Kit and c-Src, respectively. Apatinib mesylate induces both autophagy and apoptosis.

Name: Podophyllotoxin (Podofilox)
Information: Podophyllotoxin (Podofilox) is a lignan (lignans) found in podophyllin resin from the roots of podophyllum plants.

Name: Romidepsin
Information: Romidepsin (FK228, Depsipeptide, FR 901228, NSC 630176) is a potent HDAC1 and HDAC2 inhibitor with IC50 of 36 nM and 47 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. Romidepsin (FK228/depsipeptide) controls growth and induces apoptosis in neuroblastoma tumor cells.

Name: Iodixanol
Information: Iodixanol is a nonionic hydrophilic compound commonly used as a contrast agent during coronary angiography.

Name: Liarozole dihydrochloride
Information: Liarozole Dihydrochloride is identified as a modest inhibitor of P450 with IC50 of 2.2–6.0 μM and 260 nM for CYP26 and rat CYP17 respectively.

Name: Dianhydrogalactitol (VAL-083)
Information: Dianhydrogalactitol (VAL-083, Dianhydrodulcitol, Dulcitol Diepoxide) is a bi-functional alkylating agent that readily crosses the blood-brain barrier and creates N7 methylation on DNA. Dianhydrogalactitol shows antitumor activity.

Name: Ixabepilone (BMS-247550)
Information: Ixabepilone (BMS-247550, Azaepothilone B, BMS 247550-1, Ixempra, Aza-epothilone B) is an orally bioavailable microtubule inhibitor. It binds to tubulin and promotes tubulin polymerization and microtubule stabilization, thereby arresting cells in the G2-M phase of the cell cycle and inducing tumor cell apoptosis.
Synonyms: Azaepothilone B, BMS 247550, BMS 247550-1, Ixempra, Aza-epothilone B

Name: Midostaurin (PKC412)
Information: Midostaurin (pkc412, CGP 41251) is a multi-targeted kinase inhibitor, including PKCα/β/γ, Syk, Flk-1, Akt, PKA, c-Kit, c-Fgr, c-Src, FLT3, PDFRβ and VEGFR1/2 with IC50 ranging from 80-500 nM.

Name: Pralsetinib (BLU-667)
Information: Pralsetinib (BLU-667, CS 3009, Gavreto) is a highly potent and selective RET (c-RET) inhibitor with an IC50 of 0.4 nM for WT RET. It also demonstrates potent activity (IC50 0.4 nmol/L) against common oncogenic RET alterations, including RET (M918T).

Name: Sotorasib (AMG510)
Information: Sotorasib (AMG510) is a potent KRAS G12C covalent inhibitor with potential antineoplastic activity. AMG510 is a chiral compound

Name: Elexacaftor (VX-445)
Information: Elexacaftor (VX-445) is a next-generation cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) corrector.This is a compound which is not chiral purity.

Name: Valemetostat (DS-3201)
Information: Valemetostat (DS-3201, DS-3201b) is a selective EZH1/2 dual inhibitor.

Name: Suramin sodium salt
Information: Suramin sodium salt (Suramin hexasodium salt) is a reversible and competitive protein-tyrosine phosphatase (PTPases) inhibitor, also is the potent inhibitor of sirtuins, purified topoisomerase II and SARS-CoV-2 RNA-dependent RNA polymerase (RdRp).

Name: Sotorasib (AMG510) racemate
Information: Sotorasib (AMG510) racemate is a racemic of AMG-510 which is a potent KRAS G12C covalent inhibitor with potential antineoplastic activity.

Name: Exatecan Mesylate
Information: Exatecan Mesylate (DX-8951f) is a water-soluble and non-pro-drug analog of camptothecin and shows significant topoisomerase I inhibition with IC50 of 0.975 μg/ml.

Name: Valrubicin
Information: Valrubicin is a chemotherapy drug used to treat bladder cancer. Valrubicin is a chemotherapy agent, inhibits TPA- and PDBu-induced PKC activation with IC50s of 0.85 and 1.25 μM, respectively.

Name: Finerenone
Information: Finerenone (FIN, BAY 94-8862) is a highly selective and orally available nonsteroidal antagonist of mineralocorticoid receptor (MR) with IC50 of 18 nM. Finerenone has the potential for cardiorenal diseases research, such as type 2 diabetes mellitus and chronic kidney disease.

Name: Rimiducid (AP1903)
Information: Rimiducid (AP1903) is a chemical protein dimerizer and binds tightly to the target FKBP fusion protein while binding minimally to the abundant natural FKBP. Rimiducid elicites potent and dose-dependent apoptosis of cells in culture expressing dimerizer-dependent Fas constructs, with an EC50 of ≈0.1 nM.

Name: Nirmatrelvir (PF-07321332)
Information: Nirmatrelvir (PF-07321332) is an reversible covalent inhibitor of SARS-CoV-2 main protease (Mpro, also referred to as 3CL protease) with an ki of 3.11 nM. PF-07321332 binds directly to the catalytic cysteine (Cys145) residue of the enzyme.

Name: Teduglutide
Information: Teduglutide (ALX-0600, Gattex, Revestive, TAK 633) is an analogue of human glucagon-like peptide-2 (GLP-2) and binds to the GLP-2 receptors. Teduglutide prolongs the intestinotrophic properties of GLP-2 in animal models.

Name: Antazoline Phosphate
Information: Antazoline Phosphate is the phosphate salt of antazoline. Antazoline is a first-generation antihistaminic agent and acts as a histamine H1 receptor antagonist.

Name: Melengestrol Acetate
Information: Melengestrol Acetate, progestational steroid  suppress the AT3 tumour.

Name: Quinupristin
Information: Quinupristin, a streptogramin antibiotic, blocks peptide bond synthesis to prevent the extension of polypeptide chains and promote the detachment of incomplete protein chains in the bacterial ribosomal subunits.

Name: Ginsenoside Rg3
Information: Ginsenoside Rg3 is a ginsenoside found in Panax japonicus var. and Panax ginseng, mainly used for the study of tumor diseases.

Name: Tafenoquine
Information: Tafenoquine (WR 238605) is an 8-aminoquinoline, used as an anti-malarial prophylactic agent.

Name: Abarelix Acetate
Information: Abarelix Acetate is a potent gonadotrophin-releasing hormone (GnRH) antagonist, used for prostate cancer research.

Name: CCK Octapeptide (Sincalide)
Information: CCK Octapeptide (Sincalide, Cholecystokinin Octapeptide, CCK-OP, CCK-8, SQ 19,844) is a endogenous peptide hormone found in the intestine and brain that stimulates digestion.

Name: Ganirelix acetate (Antagon)
Information: Ganirelix acetate (Antagon,Orgalutran) is a synthetic decapeptide with high antagonistic activity against naturally occurring gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH).

Name: Linaclotide
Information: Linaclotide is a potent and selective guanylate cyclase C (GC-C) agonist that elicits pharmacological effects locally in the gastrointestinal tract.

Name: Difelikefalin
Information: Difelikefalin (CR-845, FE-202845), a peripherally restricted and selective agonist of kappa opioid receptor (KOR), produces anti-inflammatory effects and has the potential in modulating pruritus in conditions such as chronic kidney disease.

Name: Menthol
Information: Menthyl alcohol is an organic compound made synthetically or obtained from peppermint or mint oils with flavoring and local anesthetic properties.

Name: (-)-Menthone
Indication: stone formation in the gallbladder and liver.
Information: (-)-Menthone is a natural product.

Name: Tyramine hydrochloride
Information: Tyramine hydrochloride is a biogenic trace amine that is generated via the decarboxylation of the amino acid tyrosine, exhibiting neuromodulatory properties as well as cardiovascular and immunological effects.

Name: Evocalcet
Information: Evocalcet (KHK7580) is an novel oral calcimimetic agent which acts via allosteric activation of the calcium sensing receptor (CaSR). Evocalcet (0, 20 and 60 nM) dose-dependently increases cytoplasmic  [Ca2+] concentrations  with an EC50 value of 92.7 nM in hCaR-HEK293 cells.

Name: DPCPX
Information: DPCPX (PD 116948), a xanthine derivative, is a highly potent and selective adenosine A1 receptor (ADORA1) antagonist, with a Ki of 0.46 nM.

Name: Digitonin
Information: Digitonin, a steroidal saponin and glycoside obtained from Digitalis purpurea, has strong lytic activity on various cell membranes with an IC50 of 15.1 µM on sheep RBC membranes.

Name: Fluspirilene
Information: Fluspirilene(R 6218; Redeptin) is a non-competitive antagonist of L-type calcium channels with an IC50 of 0.03 μM in cell-free assays. Fluspirileneis a long-acting injectable depot antipsychotic agent used for schizophrenia.

Name: Sodium tetradecyl sulfate
Indication: Uncomplicated competent valves, simple dilation varicose veins of legs
Information: Sodium tetradecyl sulfate, a detergent sclerosant, is widely used agent for esophageal varices and varicose veins.

Name: Naloxegol Oxalate
Information: Naloxegol oxalate (NKTR-118 oxalate) is a μ-opioid-receptor antagonist with a Ki of 33.8 nM. Naloxegol oxalate inhibits opioid binding in μ-opioid receptors in the gastrointestinal tract and effective for alleviating opioid-induced constipation.

Name: Trovafloxacin Mesylate
Information: Trovafloxacin mesylate, a broad-spectrum quinolone antibiotic, is a potent, selective and orally active pannexin 1 channel (PANX1) inhibitor with an IC50 of 4 μM for PANX1 inward current.

Name: Clocortolone Pivalate
Information: Clocortolone pivalate is a mid-potent topical corticosteroid available as a 0.1% emollient cream used in the treatment of corticosteroid-responsive dermatoses.

Name: Laropiprant
Information: Laropiprant is a potent and selective prostaglandin D2 (DP) receptor antagonist with a Ki value of 0.57 nM.

Name: Sofpironium bromide
Information: Sofpironium bromide (BBI 4000) is an anticholinergic agent that reduces sweat by inhibiting  M3 muscarinic receptors  in eccrine glands.

Name: Levobunolol(l-Bunolol) hydrochloride
Information: Levobunolol (l-Bunolol) hydrochloride is a potent and nonselective β-adrenergic receptor antagonist with an IC50 of 48 μM.

Name: pemafibrate
Information: Pemafibrate(K-877) is a selective agonist of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor (PPAR) α with an IC50  of 10 µM.

Name: iothalamate sodium
Information: Iothalamate sodium is the sodium salt form of iothalamate, an organic iodine compound and a radiographic contrast medium.

Name: methylnaltrexone bromide
Information: Methylnaltrexone bromide is an antagonist of µ-opioid receptor that reduces the viability of lung cancer cells by inhibiting Src activation.

Name: (-)-Isoproterenol hydrochloride
Information: (-)-Isoproterenol hydrochloride is an agonist of  beta-adrenergic receptor. (-)-Isoproterenol hydrochloride is also used in the treatment of bradycardia; bronchodilator.

Name: Norepinephrine hydrochloride
Information: Norepinephrine (Levarterenol; L-Noradrenaline) hydrochloride is a potent agonist of adrenergic receptor (AR). Norepinephrine activates α1, α2, β1 receptors.

Name: Toluidine Blue O
Information: Toluidine Blue O (Toluidine Blue) is a thiazine dye of the quinone-imine family and is cationic in nature. Toluidine Blue O along with light-emitting diode has been used as a photosensitizer to control in vitro biofilms and to kill gram-negative bacteria. Toluidine Blue has wide applications in vital staining in living tissues and used as a special stain.

Name: Norepinephrine tartrate
Indication: hypotensive states and as an adjunct treatment during cardiac arrest
Information: Norepinephrine tartrate is a potent agonist of adrenergic receptor (AR). Norepinephrine activates α1, α2, β1 receptors.

Name: Zinc sulfate heptahydrate
Information: Zinc sulfate heptahydrate is a hydrate that is the heptahydrate form of zinc sulfate. Zinc sulfate heptahydrate is a dietary supplement used for zinc deficiency and can also accelerate the rate of healing. It is also used in prepration of zinc tris(thiourea) sulphate (ZTS), a semiorganic nonlinear optic (NLO) material that may be useful in laser fusion experiments and in second-harmonic-generation (SHG) devices.

Name: Gramicidin
Information: Gramicidin from Bacillus aneurinolyticus (Bacillus brevis) is an antimicrobial peptide that destroys gram-positive bacteria. It inhibits the growth of bacteria by forming pores and channels in the cell wall, which increase its permeability to monovalent cations.

Name: L-3,4-Dihydroxyphenylalanine methyl ester hydrochloride
Information: L-3,4-Dihydroxyphenylalanine methyl ester hydrochloride(Melevodopa hydrochloride) is a precursor to L-DOPA. It is an antiparkinsonian agent L-DOPA methyl ester that  elicits antitumor functionality in leukemia and melanoma.

Name: Melanin
Information: Melanin is a unique pigment with myriad functions. It is multifunctional, providing defense against environmental stresses such as ultraviolet (UV) light, oxidizing agents and ionizing radiation.

Name: Calcium chloride dihydrate
Information: Calcium chloride dihydrate is a moisture-resistant, cheap, and commonly available calcium salt. It is used as a calcium supplement in the DMEM (Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium) for use in cell culture studies and to prepare the synthetic brine solution.

Name: Dobutamine HCl
Indication:
Cardiac decompensation 
Diagnostic agent Coronary artery disease
Information: Dobutamine(Dobutrex) hydrochloride is a selective potent agonist of β1-AR (β-1 adrenergic receptor) and exhibits weak activity at α1-AR and β2-AR. Dobutamine is a sympathomimetic compound that effectively restores blood pressure in hypotensive dogs and human patients by improving myocardial contractility and increasing cardiac output (CO).

Name: CB-5339
Information: CB-5339 is a potent p97/Valosin Containing Protein (VCP) inhibitor with an IC50 of 9 nM.

Name: Fezolinetant
Information: Fezolinetant (ESN-364) is a potential antagonist of the neurokinin 3 receptor (NK3R). It interrupts pulsatile lh secretion and moderates levels of ovarian hormones throughout the menstrual cycle.

Name: Propiolactone
Information: Propiolactone(β-Propiolactone), a sterilizing and sporicidal agent, is used to sterilize blood plasma, vaccines, tissue grafts, surgical instruments and enzymes.

Name: Saquinavir Mesylate
Indication: treatment of HIV-1 with advanced immunodeficiency.
Information: Saquinavir mesylate (Ro 31-8959/003) is a potent inhibitor of HIV Protease used in antiretroviral therapy. It blocks proteolysis of polyproteins containing either wild-type or single-chain dimer retroviral proteinase (PR).

Name: Temozolomide Acid
Indication: Cancer(glioblastoma multiforme and refractory anaplastic astrocytoma.)
Information: Temozolomide acid is a carboxylic acid derivative of Temozolomide. It has an anticancer activity by causing breaks in DNA double strand, cell cycle arrest, and eventually cell death.

Name: Clavulanic acid
Information: Clavulanic acid is a naturally occurring, powerful bacterial β-lactamase inhibitor. The beta-lactam ring found in clavulanic acid binds to the active site of beta-lactamase, resulting in enzyme inactivation and enhancing the antibacterial activity of beta-lactam antibiotics like amoxicillin.

Name: Infigratinib Phosphate
Information: Infigratinib Phosphate (NVP-BGJ398 phosphate) is the phosphate salt form of infigratinib, an orally bioavailable pan-inhibitor of human  fibroblast growth factor receptors (FGFRs)  with IC50 of 0.9 nM, 1.4 nM, 1 nM, and 60 nM for  FGFR1, FGFR2, FGFR3, and FGFR4 respectively. It also has potential antiangiogenic, antineoplastic and antitumor activities.

Name: Lumateperone
Information: Lumateperone (ITI-007) is an antagonist of 5-HT2A receptor with Ki of 0.54 nM. It has anticancer activity and can also be used in studies of psychiatric disorders such as schizophrenia.

Name: Acetrizoic acid
Information: Acetrizoic acid is a first monomeric, water-soluble, iodinated ionic compound used as an X-ray contrast agent having nephrotropic property that can be intravenously administered for clinical applications.

Name: Cariprazine hydrochloride
Indication: schizophrenia and acute manic or mixed episodes due to bipolar I disorder.
Information: Cariprazine hydrochloride(RGH188 hydrochloride) is a novel antipsychotic agent and is a highly selective partial agonist of dopamineD2 and D3 and 5HT1A receptors, with preferential binding to the D3 receptor. It exhibits high selectivity and affinity to dopamine D3 (Ki = 0.085 nM) and D2 (Ki = 0.49 nM) receptors and has moderate affinity for the 5-HT1A receptor (Ki = 2.6 nM).

Name: Ubrogepant
Information: Ubrogepant (MK-1602) is an antagonist of human calcitonin gene-related peptide receptor (CGRP). It potently blocks human α–CGRP–stimulated cAMP responses with an IC50 of 0.081 nM in human CGRP receptor-expressing HEK293 cells.

Name: Palovarotene
Indication: heterotopic ossification in patients with Fibrodysplasia Ossificans Progressiva (FOP)
Information: Palovarotene (R 667; Ro 3300074) is a nuclear retinoic acid receptor γ (RAR-γ) agonist. It reduces heterotopic ossification (HO) in cultures and in murine and rat fibrodysplasia ossificans progressiva (FOP) models.

Name: Pasireotide
Information: Pasireotide (SOM230) is a multi-receptor ligand somatostatin analogue with high binding affinity for somatostatin receptor (SSTR) subtypes sst1,2,3 and sst5. It potently suppresses GH, IGF-I and ACTH secretion, indicating potential efficacy in acromegaly and Cushing’s disease.

Name: Deuterium oxide
Information: Deuterium oxide (D2O, heavy water), also known as heavy water, is a stable and non-radioactive isotopic form of water widely used in high-resolution NMR studies. It also serves as a safe and inexpensive source of deuterium (D) for D/H exchange reactions.

Name: Perifosine (KRX-0401)
Information: Perifosine (KRX-0401) is a novel Akt inhibitor with IC50 of 4.7 μM in MM.1S cells, targets pleckstrin homology domain of Akt. Phase 3.

Name: Palbociclib (PD-0332991) HCl
Information: Palbociclib (PD-0332991) HCl is a highly selective inhibitor of CDK4/6 with IC50 of 11 nM/16 nM in cell-free assays, respectively. It shows no activity against CDK1/2/5, EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, InsR, etc. Phase 3.

Name: Pemetrexed (LY-231514) disodium
Information: Pemetrexed is a novel antifolate and antimetabolite for TS, DHFR and GARFT with Ki of 1.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 65 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Gemcitabine HCl
Information: Gemcitabine HCl is a DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 50 nM, 40 nM, 18 nM and 12 nM in PANC1, MIAPaCa2, BxPC3 and Capan2 cells, respectively.

Name: Leucovorin Calcium Pentahydrate
Information: Leucovorin is a derivative of folic acid, which can be used to increase levels of folic acid under conditions favoring folic acid inhibition.

Name: Pamidronate Disodium
Information: Pamidronate Disodium is a nitrogen containing bisphosphonate, used to prevent osteoporosis.

Name: Gabapentin HCl
Information: Gabapentin HCl is a GABA analogue, used to treat seizures and neuropathic pain.

Name: Galanthamine HBr
Information: Galanthamine is an AChE inhibitor with IC50 of 0.35 μM, exhibits 50-fold selectivity against butyryl-cholinesterase.

Name: Granisetron HCl
Information: Granisetron is a serotonin 5-HT3 receptor antagonist,used to treat chemotherapy-induced nausea and vomiting.

Name: Biapenem
Information: Biapenem is a carbapenem antibiotic with activity against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacterial strains.

Name: Dorzolamide HCl
Information: Dorzolamide HCl is a water-soluble, potent inhibitor of human carbonic anhydrase II and IV with Ki of 1.9 nM and 31 nM, respectively, used as anti-glaucoma agent.

Name: Mizoribine
Information: Mizoribine is an imidazole nucleoside, selectively inhibits inosine monophosphate synthetase and guanosine monophosphate synthetase.

Name: Polymyxin B sulphate
Information: Polymyxin B is an antibiotic primarily used for resistant gram-negative infections.

Name: Teicoplanin
Information: Teicoplanin is a glycopeptide antibiotic, used to treat serious infections caused by Gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Varenicline Tartrate
Information: Varenicline Tartrate is a nicotinic AChR partial agonist, used to treat nicotine addiction.

Name: Perindopril Erbumine
Information: Perindopril Erbumine is a potent ACE inhibitor with IC50 of 1.05 nM.

Name: Cidofovir
Information: Cidofovir suppresses virus replication by selective inhibition of viral DNA synthesis.

Name: Ibuprofen Lysine
Information: Ibuprofen Lysine is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug.

Name: Palbociclib (PD0332991) Isethionate
Information: Palbociclib (PD0332991) Isethionate is a highly selective inhibitor of CDK4/6 with IC50 of 11 nM/16 nM in cell-free assays. It shows no activity against CDK1/2/5, EGFR, FGFR, PDGFR, InsR, etc. Phase 3.

Name: Alendronate sodium trihydrate
Information: Alendronate sodium trihydrate, a nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate, is a potent inhibitor of bone resorption used for the treatment and prevention of osteoporosis.

Name: Cytarabine
Information: Cytarabine is an antimetabolic agent and DNA synthesis inhibitor with IC50 of 16 nM in wild-type CCRF-CEM cells.

Name: L-Glutamine
Information: L-Glutamine (Gln) is one of the 20 amino acids encoded by the standard genetic code and also a major respiratory fuel and substrate for nucleic acid synthesis in mammalian intestinal cells.

Name: Gadodiamide Hydrate
Information: Gadodiamide Hydrate, a nonionic Gd3+ chelate, is frequently injected i.v. into magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) to enhance contrast.

Name: Penicillamine
Information: Penicillamine is used as an antirheumatic and as a chelating agent in Wilson’s disease.

Name: Etidronate
Information: Etidronate is a non-aminobisphosphonate, show protein tyrosine phosphatase (PTP) inhibitory activity, used for the treatment of Paget's disease and the prevention of heterotopic ossification.

Name: Tranexamic Acid
Information: Tranexamic Acid is an antifibrinolytic for blocking lysine-binding sites of plasmin and elastase-derived plasminogen fragments with IC50 of 5 mM.

Name: Levamisole hydrochloride
Information: (-)-Tetramisole is an inhibitor of alkaline phosphatase, used as an anthelmintic.

Name: Ticlopidine HCl
Information: Ticlopidine HCl is an P2 receptor inhibitor against ADP-induced platelet aggregation with IC50 of ~2 μM.

Name: ATP disodium
Information: ATP Disodium is a disodium salt form of adenosine-triphosphate that is used in cells as a coenzyme.

Name: Procarbazine HCl
Information: Procarbazine HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of procarbazine which is a polyfunctional alkylating compound, used for the treatment of Hodgkin's lymphoma.

Name: D-Cycloserine
Information: D-cycloserine is an analog of the amino acid D-alanine, used as an antibiotic in the treatment of tuberculosis.

Name: Sodium butyrate
Information: Sodium butyrate, sodium salt of butyric acid, is a histone deacetylase inhibitor and competitively binds to the zinc sites of class I and II histone deacetylases (HDACs).

Name: Taurine
Information: Taurine is an organic acid widely distributed in animal tissues.

Name: Clindamycin Phosphate
Information: Clindamycin Phosphate is a lincosamide antibiotic for Plasmodium falciparum with IC50 of 12 nM.

Name: Lisinopril dihydrate
Information: Lisinopril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used in treatment of hypertension, congestive heart failure, and heart attacks, and also in preventing renal and retinal complications of diabetes.

Name: Fudosteine
Information: Fudosteine is a cysteine derivative and a MUC5AC mucin hypersecretion inhibitor, used as a muco-active agent with indications for chronic respiratory diseases.

Name: Gabapentin
Information: Gabapentin is a GABA analogue, used to treat seizures and neuropathic pain.

Name: Kanamycin sulfate
Information: Kanamycin sulfate(Kanamycin monosulfate) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, available in oral, intravenous, and intramuscular forms, and used to treat a wide variety of infections.

Name: Chondroitin sulfate
Information: Chondroitin sulfate (CS) is a major component of the extracellular matrix (ECM) of many connective tissues, including cartilage, bone, skin, ligaments and tendons. It reduces the IL-1β-induced nuclear factor-kB (NF-κB) translocation in chondrocytes in vitro.

Name: Donepezil HCl
Information: Donepezil is a specific and potent AChE inhibitor for bAChE and hAChE with IC50 of 8.12 nM and 11.6 nM , respectively.

Name: Neostigmine Bromide
Information: Neostigmine Bromide is a reversible acetylcholinesterase inhibitor.

Name: Salbutamol Sulfate
Information: Salbutamol Sulfate is a short-acting β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with an IC50 of 8.93 ?M.

Name: Tobramycin
Information: Tobramycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic with an IC50 of 9.7 μM.

Name: NAD+
Information: NAD+ is a coenzyme composed of ribosylnicotinamide 5'-diphosphate coupled to adenosine 5'-phosphate by pyrophosphate linkage.

Name: Methacycline HCl
Information: Methacycline HCl is a tetracycline antibiotic, and also an inhibitor of epithelial–mesenchymal transition (EMT) with IC50 of roughly 5 μM, used to treat various infections.

Name: Lomefloxacin HCl
Information: Lomefloxacin HCl is a hydrochloride salt of lomefloxacin and is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Amiloride HCl dihydrate
Information: Amiloride HCl dihydrate is a potent epithelial sodium channel (ENaC) blocker, used in the management of hypertension and congestive heart failure.

Name: Oxacillin sodium monohydrate
Information: Oxacillin sodium monohydrate is an antibacterial agent and is a narrow spectrum beta-lactam antibiotic of the penicillin class.

Name: Neomycin sulfate
Information: Neomycin sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, used to treat bacteria infections.

Name: Streptomycin sulfate
Information: Streptomycin sulfate is a sulfate salt of streptomycin that is a protein synthesis inhibitor.

Name: Vancomycin HCl
Information: Vancomycin HCl is a hydrochloride of vancomycin that is a narrow-spectrum glycopeptide antibacterial agent.

Name: Hygromycin B
Information: Hygromycin B, a selective antibiotic that is effective on most bacteria, fungi and higher eukaryotes, inhibits protein synthesis by interfering with translocation and causing mistranslation at the 70S ribosome.

Name: Zanamivir
Information: Zanamivir is a neuraminidase inhibitor used in the treatment and prophylaxis of influenza caused by influenza A virus and influenza B virus.

Name: Plerixafor 8HCl (AMD3100 8HCl)
Information: Plerixafor 8HCl (AMD3100 8HCl) is the hydrochloride of Plerixafor, a chemokine receptor antagonist for CXCR4 and CXCL12-mediated chemotaxis with IC50 of 44 nM and 5.7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Geneticin (G418 Sulfate)
Information: Geneticin (G418 Sulfate), an aminoglycoside antibiotic, is an elongation inhibitor of 80 S ribosomes that blocks polypeptide synthesis by inhibiting the elongation step in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells.

Name: Solifenacin succinate
Information: Solifenacin succinate is a urinary antispasmodic of the antimuscarinic class.

Name: Palonosetron HCl
Information: Palonosetron HCl is a 5-HT3 antagonist used in the prevention and treatment of chemotherapy-induced nausea and vomiting.

Name: Miltefosine
Information: Miltefosine inhibits PI3K/Akt activity with ED50 of 17.2 μM and 8.1 μM in carcinoma cell lines A431 and HeLa, first oral drug for Visceral leishmaniasis, effective against both promastigotes and amastigotes.

Name: Danofloxacin Mesylate
Information: Danofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibacterial for veterinary use, with MIC90 of 0.28 μM.

Name: Amikacin disulfate
Information: Amikacin sulfate binds to 16S rRNA (bacterial 30S ribosome), causing misreading of mRNA and supressing proteins synthesis.

Name: (R)-baclofen
Information: (R)-baclofen is a derivative of gamma-aminobutyric acid primarily used to treat spasticity.

Name: Caspofungin Acetate
Information: Caspofungin acetate is an lipopeptide antifungal β-1,3-glucan synthase inhibitor.

Name: Creatinine
Information: Creatinine is a break-down product of creatine phosphate in muscle, and is usually produced at a fairly constant rate by the body.

Name: Amikacin hydrate
Information: Amikacin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic used to treat different types of bacterial infections.

Name: Tripelennamine HCl
Information: Tripelennamine is a widely used H1 antagonist, inhibiting PhIP glucuronidation with IC50 of 30 μM.

Name: Ibandronate sodium
Information: Ibandronate is a highly potent nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate used for the treatment of osteoporosis.

Name: Abacavir sulfate
Information: Abacavir is a commonly used nucleoside analogue with potent antiviral activity against HIV-1.

Name: L-Arginine HCl (L-Arg)
Information: L-Arginine is the nitrogen donor for synthesis of nitric oxide, a potent vasodilator that is deficient during times of sickle cell crisis.

Name: Thiamine HCl (Vitamin B1)
Information: Thiamine or vitamin B1 is a water-soluble vitamin of the B complex, its phosphate derivatives are involved in many cellular processes.

Name: Cesium chloride
Information: Cesium chloride is the inorganic compound. It is widely used medicine structure in isopycnic centrifugation for separating various types of DNA and is a reagent in analytical chemistry.

Name: Ceftazidime
Information: Ceftazidime is a third-generation cephalosporin that has activity against Gram-negative bacilli, including Pseudomonas aeruginosa.

Name: Penicillin V potassium salt
Information: Phenoxymethylpenicillin, also known as penicillin V, is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections. It acts by inhibiting the biosynthesis of cell-wall peptidoglycan.

Name: Pirenzepine dihydrochloride
Information: Pirenzepine is an antimuscarinic agent which inhibits gastric acid secretion at lower doses than are required to affect gastrointestinal motility, salivary, central nervous system, cardiovascular, ocular and urinary functions.

Name: Imipenem
Pharmacopoeia: Martindale:The Extra Pharmacopoeia,USP42-NF37,KP Ⅹ,EP7.5,JP17,印度药典
Information: Imipenem acts as an inhibitor of AmpC β-lactamase and is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Cangrelor Tetrasodium
Information: Cangrelor is a potent, competitive P2Y12 receptor inhibitor that is administered by intravenous infusion and rapidly achieves near complete inhibition of ADP-induced platelet aggregation.

Name: Acamprosate Calcium
Information: Acamprosate, calcium acetylhomotaurinate, is a synthetic compound with a chemical structure similar to the amino acid neurotransmitter gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) and the amino acid neuromodulator taurine.

Name: isoleucine
Information: Isoleucine is a non-polar, uncharged (at physiological pH), aliphatic amino acid that is used in the biosynthesis of proteins.

Name: L-Leucine
Information: Leucine is one of nine essential amino acids in humans which is important for protein synthesis and many metabolic functions. It contributes to regulation of blood-sugar levels growth and repair of muscle and bone tissue growth hormone production and wound healing.

Name: L-Citrulline
Information: L-citrulline is a substance called a non-essential amino acid that is used as a sports performance and cardiovascular health supplement.

Name: L-Theanine
Information: L-Theanine is a relaxing and nondietary amino acid found pretty much exclusively in teas from Camellia sinensis and is known to promote relaxation without sedation.

Name: Sodium Demethylcantharidate
Information: Demethylcantharidin (norcantharidin) is a synthetic analogue of cantharidin and has potent antitumor activity.

Name: L-Lysine hydrochloride
Information: L-Lysine hydrochloride is an essential amino acid. It is often added to animal feed used as a dietary supplement and plays a major role in calcium absorption, building muscle protein, recovering from surgery or sports injuries, and the body's production of hormones, enzymes, and antibodies.

Name: DL-Glutamine
Information: Glutamine is a non-essential amino acid present abundantly throughout the body and is involved in many metabolic processes.

Name: L-SelenoMethionine
Information: L-SelenoMethionine (SeMet), a naturally occurring amino acid, is a major food-form of selenium. It has been used as a supplement, and exhibits some important functions like cancer prevention and antioxidative defense.

Name: Pemirolast potassium
Information: Pemirolast potassium (BMY 26517) is a histamine H1 antagonist and mast cell stabilizer that acts as an antiallergic agent.

Name: Sodium Monofluorophosphate
Information: Sodium Monofluorophosphate  is a competitive inhibitor of pyruvate kinase and alkaline phosphatase with Ki of 3.4 mM and 69 μM, respectively, which also irreversibly inhibits phosphorylase phosphatase with Ki of 0.5 mM.

Name: Flavoxate HCl
Information: Flavoxate is a muscarinic AChR antagonist with IC50 of 12.2 μM.

Name: Dexamethasone Sodium Phosphate
Information: Dexamethasone is a potent synthetic member of the glucocorticoid class of steroid drugs, and an interleukin receptor modulator  that has anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant effects.

Name: Colistin Sulfate
Information: Colistin is a cyclic cationic decapeptide linked to a fatty acid side chain, it belongs to a group of similarly structured bacterial antimicrobial peptides.

Name: Gentamicin Sulfate
Information: Gentamycin Sulfate is a broad-spectrum, aminoglycoside antibiotic used for cell culture which inhibits protein synthesis in sensitive organisms.

Name: Netilmicin Sulfate
Information: Netilmicin Sulfate is a member of the aminoglycoside family of antibiotics.

Name: Bismuth Subcitrate Potassium
Information: Bismuth Subcitrate is an antibiotic used to treat stomach ulcers associated with Helicobacter pylori, a bacterial infection.

Name: Tetramisole HCl
Information: Tetramisole is a mixture of dextro- and levo isomers used as an anthelmintic.

Name: Clodronate Disodium
Information: Clodronate Disodium, a bisphosphonate, is a potent antiosteolytic agent which inhibits bone resorption.

Name: Histamine Phosphate
Information: Histamine acts directly on the blood vessels to dilate arteries and capillaries mediated by both H 1- and H 2-receptors.

Name: Succinylcholine Chloride Dihydrate
Information: Succinylcholine Chloride Dihydrate is a nicotinic AChR agonist and also acts as a depolarizing neuromuscular blocker.

Name: Terbutaline Sulfate
Information: Terbutaline Sulfate is a selective β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with IC50 of 53 nM.

Name: Mildronate
Information: Mildronate is an inhibitor of biosynthesis of L-carnitine by gamma-butyrobetaine (GBB) hydroxylase and as a competitive inhibitor of renal carnitine reabsorption.

Name: Eprazinone 2HCl
Information: Eprazinone is a mucolytic.

Name: Amprolium HCl
Information: Amprolium chloride is a thiamin antagonist, which prevents carbohydrate synthesis by blocking thiamine uptake.

Name: Bacitracin
Information: Bacitracin is a mixture of related cyclic polypeptides produced by organisms of the licheniformis group of Bacillus subtilis var Tracy, which disrupts both gram positive and gram negative bacteria by interfering with cell wall and peptidoglycan synthesis.

Name: Chloroquine Phosphate
Information: Chloroquine phosphate is a 4-aminoquinoline anti-malarial and anti-rheumatoid agent, also acting as an ATM activator.

Name: Ceftriaxone Sodium Trihydrate
Information: Ceftriaxone sodium trihydrate is a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Sodium Gluconate
Information: Sodium gluconate is the sodium salt of gluconic acid widely used in food and pharmaceutical industry.

Name: Nefopam HCl
Information: Nefopam HCl is a centrally-acting but non-opioid analgesic drug by blocking voltage-gated sodium channel and inhibition of serotonin, dopamine and noradrenaline reuptake.

Name: Paromomycin Sulfate
Information: Paromomycin Sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotics inhibiting protein synthesis in non-resistant cells by binding to 16S ribosomal RNA.

Name: Ribostamycin Sulfate
Information: Ribostamycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, containing a neutral sugar moiety, and is produced by Streptomyces ribosidi?cus.

Name: Capreomycin Sulfate
Information: Capreomycin Sulfate is a cyclic peptide antibiotic and thought to inhibit protein synthesis by binding to the 70S ribosomal unit.

Name: Proflavine Hemisulfate
Information: Proflavine Hemisulfate is a topical antiseptic by interchelating DNA, thereby disrupting DNA synthesis and leading to high levels of mutation in the copied DNA strands.

Name: Sodium ascorbate
Information: Sodium Ascorbate is a more bioavailable form of vitamin C that is an alternative to taking ascorbic acid as a supplement.

Name: Apramycin Sulfate
Information: Apramycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, which binds to the deep groove of the RNA.

Name: Isepamicin Sulphate
Information: Isepamicin Sulphate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, which inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by targeting the bacterial 30S ribosomal subunit.

Name: Micafungin Sodium
Information: Micafungin Sodium is an inhibitor of 1, 3-beta-D-glucan synthesis, used as an antifungal drug.

Name: Amifostine
Information: Amifostine is the first approved radioprotective drug, used to decrease the risk of kidney problems caused by treatment with cisplatin.

Name: Calcium Gluceptate
Information: Calcium gluceptate is a calcium salt used in the treatment and prophylaxis of hypocalcemia and as an electrolyte replenisher.

Name: Ceftazidime Pentahydrate
Information: Ceftazidime is a β-lactam antibacterial agent which has demonstrated a broad spectrum of activity against Gram-positive and Gram-negative aerobic bacteria.

Name: Guanethidine Sulfate
Information: Guanethidine is an antihypertensive drug that reduces the release of catecholamines, such as norepinephrine.

Name: Tolmetin Sodium
Information: Tolmetin is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug of the arylalkanoic acids.

Name: Hydroxychloroquine Sulfate
Information: Hydroxychloroquine Sulfate is an antimalarial agent used for the treatment of systemic lupus erythematosus, rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune, inflammatory and dermatologic conditions. Also acts as an inhibitor of autophagy and toll-like receptor (TLR) 7/9.

Name: Dihydrostreptomycin sulfate
Information: Dihydrostreptomycin sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, used to treat bacterial diseases in cattle, pigs and sheep. Dihydrostreptomycin is a derivative of streptomycin.

Name: Sisomicin sulfate
Information: Sisomicin sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, isolated from the fermentation broth of a new species of the genus Micromonospora.

Name: Eprodisate disodium
Information: Eprodisate Disodium is the orally available disodium salt form of Eprodisate, a small-molecule, orally bioavailable, inhibitor of AA-amyloid fibrillogenesis.

Name: Pralidoxime chloride
Information: Pralidoxime is an antidote to organophosphate pesticides and chemicals An acetylcholinesterase (AChE) reactivator.

Name: Eflornithine hydrochloride hydrate
Information: Eflornithine(Difluoromethylornithine) inhibits polyamine biosynthesis by the selective, irreversible inhibition of ornithine decarboxylase (ODC). A chemoprotective agent that blocks angiogenesis. Its biological half-life is 8 hours.

Name: Captisol (SBE-β-CD)
Information: Captisol (SBE-β-CD) is a novel, chemically modified cyclodextrin with a structure designed to optimize the solubility and stability of drugs.

Name: Glutathione
Information: Glutathione acts as an antioxidant, a free radical scavenger and a detoxifying agent. It is a tripeptide comprised of three amino acids (cysteine, glutamic acid, and glycine) present in most mammalian tissue.

Name: L-Ornithine hydrochloride
Information: L-ornithine hydrochloride ((S)-2,5-Diaminopentanoic acid) has an antifatigue effect by increasing the efficiency of energy consumption and promoting the excretion of ammonia. It is one of the key reactants in the urea cycle.

Name: Cefradine
Information: Cephradine is a semi-synthetic cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Sildenafil
Information: Sildenafil is a Phosphodiesterase 5 Inhibitor with IC50 of 5.22 nM.

Name: 4-Aminobutyric acid
Information: Gamma-Aminobutyric Acid is a naturally occurring neurotransmitter with central nervous system (CNS) inhibitory activity.
Synonyms: 4-Aminobutanoic acid, GABA, Gamma-aminobutyric acid, Piperidic acid

Name: Choline bitartrate
Information: Choline bitartrate is a form of the nutrient choline which is found in foods. Choline is necessary for normal liver and kidney function and a component of the neurotransmitter acetylcholine, a chemical that facilitates communication between the nerves and muscles.

Name: D-(+)-Cellobiose
Information: D-(+)-Cellobiose is a substrate of β-glucosidase.

Name: L-Glutamic acid monosodium salt
Information: L-Glutamic acid monosodium salt is the sodium salt of glutamic acid, found naturally in tomatoes, cheese and other foods.

Name: Sodium ferulate
Information: Sodium ferulate (SF), the sodium salt of ferulic acid, is a drug used in traditional Chinese medicine for treatment of cardiovascular and cerebrovascular diseases and to prevent thrombosis.

Name: Danshensu
Information: Danshensu, a herbal preparation used in traditional Chinese medicine, possesses potential antitumor and anti?angiogenesis effects.

Name: Creatine phosphate disodium salt
Information: Phosphocreatine, also known as creatine phosphate (CP) or PCr (Pcr), is a phosphorylated creatine molecule that serves as a rapidly mobilizable reserve of high-energy phosphates in skeletal muscle and the brain to recycle adenosine triphosphate, the energy currency of the cell.

Name: Glycylglycine
Information: Glycylglycine, the simplest peptide made of two glycine molecules, is usually used in the synthesis of more complicated peptides.

Name: VitaMin U
Information: Vitamin U (Methylmethionine chloride) is a vitamin found in green vegetables. It is used in the treatment of peptic ulcers, colitis, and gastritis and has an effect on secretory, acid-forming, and enzymatic functions of the intestinal tract.

Name: Glycine
Information: Glycine is a non-essential, non-polar, non-optical, glucogenic amino acid that is primarily found in gelatin and silk fibroin. It is involved in the body's production of DNA, phospholipids and collagen, and in release of energy.

Name: Manganese chloride
Information: Manganese chloride occurs in nature as the mineral. It is used as a precursor for other manganese compounds.

Name: Sodium carbonate
Information: Sodium Carbonate is the disodium salt of carbonic acid with alkalinizing property.
Synonyms: Disodium carbonate, Soda Ash, Carbonic acid disodium salt

Name: L(+)-Asparagine monohydrate
Information: L-asparagine is a non-essential amino acid that is involved in the metabolic control of cell functions in nerve and brain tissue, being used for a variety of pharmaceutical applications.

Name: L-Threonine
Information: L-Threonine is an essential amino acid which is in its active form. It is important for the formation of collagen, elastin, and tooth enamel, and aids liver and lipotropic function when combined with aspartic acid and methionine.

Name: Choline Glycerophosphate
Information: Choline Glycerophosphate is a choline derivative and one of the two major forms of choline storage (along with phosphocholine) in the cytosol.

Name: Timonacic
Information: Timonacic is a cyclic sulfur amino acid derivative with potential antineoplastic and antioxidant activities.

Name: Fosfomycin Disodium
Information: Fosfomycin is a bactericidal, low-molecular weight, broad-spectrum antibiotic, with putative activity against several bacteria, including multidrug-resistant Gram-negative bacteria, by irreversibly inhibiting an early stage in cell wall synthesis.

Name: Pipemidic acid
Information: Pipemidic acid is a pyridopyrimidine antibiotic derivative of piromidic acid with activity against gram-negative and some gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Methotrexate disodium
Information: Methotrexate sodium, an inhibitor of tetrahydrofolate dehydrogenase, is an antineoplastic antimetabolite with immunosuppressant properties.

Name: DL-Citrulline
Information: L-Citrulline (Cit) is a naturally occurring nonessential amino acid which is the key intermediate in the urea cycle.

Name: Homotaurine
Information: Homotaurine is a synthetic organic compound that has GABAergic activity by mimicking GABA. It is a GABAA partial agonist as well as a GABAB receptor partial agonist with low efficacy.

Name: Calcium folinate
Information: Calcium folinate is a metabolically active, reduced form of folic acid that is rapidly absorbed and extensively metabolized in the liver to other folic acid derivatives.
Synonyms: Leucovorin calcium, Folinic acid calcium salt, Wellcovorin

Name: D-Pantethine
Information: Pantethine is a naturally occurring compound synthesized in the body from pantothenic acid (vitamin B5) via addition of cysteamine and used as a dietary supplement for lowering blood cholesterol and triglycerides.

Name: Ozagrel sodium
Information: Sodium ozagrel (ozagrel) is a thromboxane A2 synthase inhibitor with neuroprotective properties.

Name: Nylidrin Hydrochloride
Information: Nylidrin hydrochloride was an effective inhibitor of the IgG1-mediated release of histamine from passively sensitized guinea pig lung slices, and of the IgE-mediated release of histamine from passively sensitized rat peritoneal mast cells and human basophils.

Name: Cephradine monohydrate
Information: Cefradine is a beta-lactam, first-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Citicholine
Information: Citicholine is a naturally occurring compound that acts as nutrient with a broad spectrum of benefits for conditions associated with symptoms of neurological dysfunction. As an endogenous compound, it is also an essential intermediate in the synthesis of cell membrane phospholipids and its formation is the rate-limiting step in phosphatidylcholine synthesis.

Name: UTP, Trisodium Salt
Information: Uridine-5'-triphosphate (UTP) is a pyrimidine nucleoside triphosphate and a substrate for the synthesis of RNA during transcription.

Name: Loxoprofen Sodium
Information: Loxoprofen Sodium is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) in the propionic acid derivatives group

Name: Sodium succinate
Information: Sodium succinate is the sodium salt form of succinate, which is an important metabolite at the cross-road of several metabolic pathways and involved in the formation and elimination of reactive oxygen species.

Name: Guanethidine Monosulfate
Information: Guanethidine monosulfate is an antihypertensive agent that acts by inhibiting selectively transmission in post-ganglionic adrenergic nerves.

Name: Spermine Tetrahydrochloride
Information: Spermine is a polyamine involved in cellular metabolism found in all eukaryotic cells. It is a major natural intracellular compound capable of protecting DNA from free radical attack.
Synonyms: Gerontine tetrahydrochloride, Neuridine tetrahydrochloride, Musculamine tetrahydrochloride

Name: β-Alanine
Information: β-Alanine is a naturally occurring beta amino acid formed in vivo by the degradation of dihydrouracil and carnosine. It acts as a neurotransmitter by activating glycine and GABA receptors.

Name: Tobramycin sulfate
Information: ipid Storage Modulator

Name: DL-Serine
Information: Serine is a non-essential amino acid and a natural ligand and allosteric activator of pyruvate kinase M2.

Name: DL-Arginine
Information: Arginine is an α-amino acid that is used in the biosynthesis of proteins and plays an important role in cell division, wound healing, removing ammonia from the body, immune function, and the release of hormones.

Name: L-Asparagine
Information: L-Asparagine is a non-essential amino acid that is involved in the metabolic control of cell functions in nerve and brain tissue.

Name: Creatine
Information: Creatine is a nitrogenous organic acid that occurs naturally in vertebrates. It facilitates the recycling of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) primarily in muscle and brain tissue.

Name: L-Valine
Information: Valine is a branched-chain essential amino acid that has stimulant activity and promotes muscle growth and tissue repair. It is a precursor in the penicillin biosynthetic pathway.

Name: L-Proline
Information: L-Proline is one of non-essential amino acids and an essential component of collagen that is important for proper functioning of joints and tendons.

Name: L-lysine
Information: Lysine is an α-amino acid that is used in the biosynthesis of proteins and is required for growth and tissue repair.

Name: L-Alanine
Information: Alanine is a naturally occuring non-essential amino acid that is involved in sugar and acid metabolism, increases immunity, and provides energy for muscle tissue, brainR, and the CNS.

Name: L-aspartic Acid
Information: L-aspartic Acid is one of non-essential amino acids and may be a neurotransmitter.

Name: L-methionine
Information: L-Methionine is an essential sulfur-containing, free-form amino acid, acts as an antioxidant promoter, and contributes to the synthesis of S-adenosyl-L-methionine (SAMe).

Name: L-arginine
Information: Arginine is an important amino acid used in the biosynthesis of proteins. L-arginine plays an important role in immune regulation by affecting the immune response and inflammation. It is also implicated in cell division, wound healing and the release of hormones.

Name: L-cysteine
Information: Cysteine is a naturally occurring, sulfur-containing amino acid which is important for protein synthesis, detoxification, and also exerts diverse metabolic functions.

Name: Clodronate disodium tetrahydrate
Information: Clodronate is a non-nitrogenous bisphosphonate that can bind to bone to reduce the bone resorption. It is used as an anti-osteoporotic drug for the prevention of osteoporosis in post-menopausal women and men.

Name: Lodoxamide Tromethamine
Information: Lodoxamide Tromethamine is the tromethamide salt form of lodoxamide, a synthetic mast cell stabilizing compound with anti-inflammatory activity.

Name: Edetate Trisodium
Information: sequester metal ions such as Ca2+ and Fe3+

Name: edetate calcium disodium
Information: Edetate calcium disodium is a chelating agent that is primarily used for the management of severe lead poisoning.

Name: pentetate calcium trisodium hydrate
Information: pentetate calcium trisodium hydrate is an iron chelating agent.

Name: Ala-Gln
Information: Ala-Gln, a dipeptide composed of alanine and Gln, is an alternative supplement to L-glutamine in the production of biopharmaceuticals with better solubility and stability than glutamine (Gln).

Name: L-Hydroxyproline
Information: L-Hydroxyproline is a collagen-specific amino acid. It is used as a diagnostic marker of bone turnover and liver fibrosis.

Name: Gastrodenol
Information: Gastrodenol is used to treat certain conditions caused by too much acid being produced in the stomach, such as stomach ulcers and ulcers of the upper part of the intestine (duodenal ulcers)

Name: Bendazac L-lysine
Information: Bendazac L-lysine has a protective effect against lens protein denaturation both in vitro and in vivo. It is also a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used for joint and muscular pain.

Name: Creatine monohydrate
Information: Creatine is a key player in the phosphagen energy system, the primary source of ATP during short-term, high intensity activities.

Name: Thiamine pyrophosphate hydrochloride
Information: Thiamine pyrophosphate hydrochloride is a thiamine (vitamin B1) derivative which is produced by the enzyme thiamine diphosphokinase. It is a coenzyme of many enzymes, most of which occur in prokaryotes and is involved in the regulation of basic metabolism.

Name: Malachite green
Information: Malachite green is a synthetic dyestuff and antimicrobial with potential carcinogenicity.
Synonyms: Aniline green, Basic green 4, Diamond green B, Victoria green B

Name: (R)-Serine
Information: (R)-Serine is the R-enantiomer of serine, which is used in the biosynthesis of proteins.

Name: (S)-Glutamic acid
Information: (S)-Glutamic acid (L-Glutamic acid) is an endogenous, non-selective glutamate receptor agonist.

Name: Sodium phytate hydrate
Information: Phytate (Phytic acid) functions as a storage depot and precursor for other inositol phosphates and pyrophosphates. It can be used clinically as a hypocalcemic agent and a complexing agent for removal of traces of heavy metal ions.
