Synonyms: phytic acid sodium hydrate, Dodecasodium phytate, myo-inositol hexakis, Inositol hexakisphosphate

Name: Chlorophyllin (sodium copper salt)
Information: Chlorophyllin, the sodium and copper salt of chlorophyll, is an antioxidant and antimutagenic agent.

Name: Sugammadex (sodium)
Information: Sugammadex is a selective relaxant binding agent indicated for reversal of neuromuscular blockade induced by rocuronium bromide and vecuronium bromide during surgery in adults.

Name: Gadoxetate sodium
Information: Gadoxetate is a paramagnetic gadolinium-containing contrast agent in which its salt form, gadoxetate disodium, is used for intravenous injection.

Name: Diquafosol Tetrasodium
Information: Diquafosol Tetrasodium, a  P2Y2 receptor  agonist, is a pharmaceutical drug for the treatment of dry eye disease.

Name: Rilmenidine Phosphate
Status: marketed in Hungary, Poland and the Czech Republic
Information: Rilmenidine Phosphate is a selective I(1) imidazoline receptor agonist, used for the treatment of hypertension.

Name: Pemetrexed Disodium Hydrate
Information: Pemetrexed Disodium Hydrate is a novel antifolate and antimetabolite for TS, DHFR and GARFT with Ki of 1.3 nM, 7.2 nM and 65 nM, respectively.

Name: DL-Methionine
Information: qHTS for Inhibitors of binding or entry into cells for Marburg Virus

Name: L-serine
Information: Inhibitory activity against T3 binding to human TRbeta1 receptor

Name: Adenosine disodium triphosphate
Information: Adenosine triphosphate (ATP) is a nucleoside triphosphate used in cells as a coenzyme often called the "molecular unit of currency" of intracellular energy transfer.

Name: Gadoversetamide
Information: Gadoversetamide is a paramagnetic agent that develops a magnetic moment when placed in a magnetic field. It is used as a contrast agent in MRI tests of the brain, spine, and liver.

Name: Bivalirudin Trifluoroacetate
Information: Bivalirudin Trifluoroacetate is a synthetic 20 residue peptide (thrombin inhibitor) which reversibly inhibits thrombin.

Name: Eptifibatide Acetate
Information: Eptifibatide Acetate is a cyclic heptapeptide constructed from 6 amino acids and a mercaptopropionyl residue. A disulfide bridge forms between mercaptopropionyl and cysteine. Eptifibatide prevents platelet aggregation. One study shows the inhibition of platelet glycoprotein IIb/IIIa in acute coronary syndromes.

Name: Octreotide Acetate
Information: Octreotide Acetate is the acetate salt of a cyclic octapeptide. It is a long-acting octapeptide with pharmacologic properties mimicking those of the natural hormone somatostatin.

Name: Atosiban Acetate
Information: Atosiban Acetate is a competitive oxytocin and vasopressin antagonist by exhibiting high affinity for both receptors. It is used to treat preterm labors.

Name: Oxytocin (Syntocinon)
Information: Oxytocin(Syntocinon) is a nine amino acid peptide that is synthesized in hypothalamic neurons and transported down axons of the posterior pituitary for secretion into blood.

Name: Salmon Calcitonin Acetate
Information: Salmon Calcitonin Acetate, which is more potent and longer lasting than human CT, has been used widely for the treatment of osteoporosis, paget's disease, hypercalcemic shock and chronic pain in terminal cancer patients.

Name: Terlipressin Acetate
Information: Terlipressin Acetate is an analogue of vasopressin used as a vasoactive drug in the management of hypotension. It has been found to be effective when norepinephrine does not help.

Name: Somatostatin Acetate
Information: Somatostatin Acetate is a peptide hormone that regulates the endocrine system and affects neurotransmission and cell proliferation via interaction with G protein-coupled somatostatin receptors and inhibition of the release of numerous secondary hormones.

Name: GHRP-2
Information: GHRP-2 is a true hGH secretagogue. It is a synthetic agonist of ghrelin.

Name: Desmopressin Acetate
Information: Desmopressin is a synthetic octapeptide, and an analogue of human hormone arginine vasopressin with antidiuretic and coagulant activities. It is a selective agonist for the vasopressin V2 receptor (V2R).

Name: Angiotensin II human Acetate
Information: Angiotensin II (angII) is an octapeptide hormone which affects the activities of heart, kidney, vasculature and brain. It works via binding to specific receptors present on cell membranes.

Name: Carperitide Acetate
Information: a peptide hormone that promotes the loss of fluid and electrolytes and the reduction of vascular tone.

Name: （6-）ε-Aminocaproic acid
Information: （6-）ε-?Aminocaproic acid is a derivative and analogue of the amino acid lysine.

Name: Foscarnet Sodium
Information: Foscarnet Sodium inhibits viral RNA polymerases, reverse transcriptase, and DNA polymerases through noncompetitive inhibition with dNTPs.

Name: Citric acid trilithium salt tetrahydrate
Information: Citric acid trilithium salt tetrahydrate is a pharmaceutical and construction material. It is commonly used in HPLC gradient elution for quantification of amino acids.
Synonyms: Trilithium citrate tetrahydrate, Lithium citrate tribasic tetrahydrate

Name: Hyaluronic acid
Information: Hyaluronic acid (HA) is an anionic, nonsulfated glycosaminoglycan distributed widely throughout connective, epithelial, and neural tissues. It is widely used in skin care.

Name: Latamoxef sodium
Information: Latamoxef sodium is an antibiotic compound more effective against Escherichia coli and Pseudomonas aeruginosathan cephalosporins

Name: Estramustine phosphate sodium
Information: Estramustine phosphate sodium is an antitumour drug with a unique dual mode of action. Estrone and estradiol, products of the metabolism of estramustine phosphate sodium, have shown antigonadotrophic activity resulting in reduced testosterone levels. Estramustine(the cytotoxic metabolite produced by dephosphorylation of estramustine phosphate sodium) is an antiprostatic tumor drug with antimicrotubule effects.

Name: Spermine
Information: Spermine is a polyamine involved in cellular metabolism found in all eukaryotic cells. It is found in a wide variety of organisms and tissues and is an essential growth factor in some bacteria.

Name: Sodium stibogluconate
Pharmacopoeia: Martindale:The Extra Pharmacopoeia, BP2020, Ph.Int_6th , IP2010
Information: Sodium stibogluconate, a pentavalent antimony derivative, is a potent and selective inhibitor of protein tyrosine phosphatase (PTPase). Sodium stibogluconate inhibits 99% of Src homology 2 domain-containing phosphatase 1 (SHP-1) activity at 10 μg/ml and similar degrees of inhibition of SHP-2 and PTP1B requires 100 μg/ml. Sodium stibogluconate is a drug used in treatment of leishmaniasis.
Synonyms: SSG, Stibogluconate sodium, Stibogluconate trisodium nonahydrate, Lenocta, VQD-001

Name: HEPES
Information: HEPES is a zwitterionic sulfonic acid buffering agent, commonly used to uphold a neutral pH of basal medium within cell cultures.

Name: Lithium carbonate
Information: Used in treatment of manic depression.

Name: D-Alanine
Information: D-alanine (Ala, (R)-Alanine, Ba 2776, D-α-Alanine, NSC 158286) is an endogenous co-agonist at the glycine site of the N-methyl-d-aspartate (NMDA) receptor.

Name: Lanreotide acetate
Information: Lanreotide (Laromustine, Angiopeptin, BIM 23014, Dermopeptin, Ipstyl, ITM-014, Somatulina, Somatuline, Lanreotidum) acetate, an analog of the native somatostatin peptide, is a physiological inhibitor of growth hormone (GH). Lanreotide also has antitumoral effects.
Synonyms: Laromustine, Angiopeptin, BIM 23014, BIM 23014C, BM 23014, Dermopeptin, Ipstyl, ITM-014, ITM-014T, Somatulina, Somatuline, Lanreotidum

Name: Levoleucovorin calcium
Information: Calcium Levofolinate is a calcium salt of folinic acid that is an adjuvant used in cancer chemotherapy.

Name: L-Histidine monohydrochloride monohydrate
Information: L-Histidine monohydrochloride monohydrate (L-Histidine hydrochloride hydrate, H-His-OH.HCl.H2O), a structural analogue of the essential amino acid L-histidine, is a reversible inhibitor of protein biosynthesis which evokes disparate responses from non-tumorigenic and tumorigenic cells in culture.

Name: Potassium sorbate
Information: Potassium sorbate (Sorbic acid potassium) is a nonpoisonous food preservative isolated from Sorbus aucuparia. Potassium sorbate is an effective inhibitor of most molds and yeasts and some bacteria.

Name: Teriparatide Acetate
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Teriparatide Acetate is a recombinant form of parathyroid hormone, used in the treatment of some forms of osteoporosis

Name: Felypressin Acetate
Information: Felypressin-Acetate is a non-catecholamine vasoconstrictor that is chemically associated to vasopressin, the posterior pituitary hormone.

Name: Zoledronic Acid
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Zoledronic acid (ZOL 446, ZA, Zoledronate, CGP-4244, GP42446A, Zometa, Zomera, Aclasta, Reclast), a potent osteoclast inhibitor, induces apoptosis in osteoclasts by inhibiting enzymes of the mevalonate pathway and preventing the isoprenylation of small GTP-binding proteins such as Ras and Rho. Zoledronic acid (ZA) also induces autophagy.
Synonyms: Zoledronate, CGP-4244, GP42446A, Zometa, Zomera, Aclasta, Reclast

Name: Gadobutrol
Information: Gadobutrol (Gadovist, Gadavist) is a non-ionic macrocyclic gadolinium-based contrast agent (GBCA) that is usedfor tissue contrast enhancement in magnetic resonance imaging (MRI).

Name: Bekanamycin
Information: Bekanamycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic.

Name: Piperazine adipate
Pharmacopoeia: EP10.4, USP42-NF37, KP Ⅹ, Ph.Int_6th, JP16,IP2010
Information: Piperazine adipate is a broad spectrum anthelmintic agent that inhibits malate oxidation in Ascaridia galli and Heterakis gallinae.

Name: Methionine
Information: Methionine (MRX-1024, D-Methionine) is an activitor of GABAA receptor that modulates neuronal activity.

Name: L-Ornithine
Information: L-ornithine ((S)-2,5-Diaminopentanoic acid) has an antifatigue effect by increasing the efficiency of energy consumption and promoting the excretion of ammonia. It is one of the key reactants in the urea cycle.

Name: Tenofovir hydrate
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Tenofovir (GS-1278) hydrate blocks reverse transcriptase and hepatitis B virus infections.

Name: Gadodiamide
Information: Gadodiamide (GDD, Omniscan) is a widely used magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) contrast agent with a high renal toxicity.

Name: Varenicline Hydrochloride
Information: Varenicline (CP 526555) Hydrochloride is a potent and selective inhibitor of nicotine acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) with Ki of 0.12 nM and 0.14 nM for α6β2 nAChR and α4β2 nAChR, respectively.

Name: Sodium etidronate
Information: Sodium Etidronate (Didronel, EHDP, Etidronic acid) is a non-aminobisphosphonate that exhibits protein tyrosine phosphatase (PTP) inhibitory activity.

Name: ATP
Information: ATP (Adenosine-Triphosphate, Adenosine 5'-triphosphate) is a multifunctional nucleoside triphosphate and an important endogenous signaling molecule in immunity and inflammation.

Name: Amikacin Sulfate Salt
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Pharmacopoeia: EP10.5, USP43-NF38, KP Ⅹ, Ph.Int_6th, JP17, IP2010
Information: Amikacin (BAY 41-6551) sulfate, a semisynthetic analog of kanamycin, is an aminoglycoside antibiotic which is very active against most gram-negative bacteria including gentamicin- and tobramycin-resistant strains.

Name: Dexamethasone phosphate disodium
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, HMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Pharmacopoeia: USP42-NF37, KP Ⅹ, Ph.Int_6th, JP17, Ph.Int_5th, JP16, IP2010
Information: Dexamethasone phosphate disodium (DEX, Dexacort, Decadron, Dexair, Hexadrol, Maxidex) is a glucocorticoid receptor agonist with both anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidative effects.
Synonyms: DEX, Dexacort, Decadron, Dexair, Hexadrol, Maxidex, Dexamethasone 21-phosphate disodium salt

Name: Gatifloxacin hydrochloride
Information: Gatifloxacin (AM-1155, CG5501, BMS-206584, PD135432) hydrochloride is a potent fluoroquinolone antibiotic with broad-spectrum antibacterial activity. Gatifloxacin hydrochloride inhibits bacterial type II topoisomerases with IC50 of 13.8 μg/ml and 0.109 μg/ml for S. aureus topoisomerase IV and E. coli DNA gyrase, respectively.
Synonyms: AM-1155 hydrochloride, CG5501 hydrochloride, BMS-206584 hydrochloride, PD135432 hydrochloride

Name: Kasugamycin hydrochloride hydrate
Information: Kasugamycin (Ksg) hydrochloride hydrate, an antibiotic which binds both the 30S and 70S ribosome, specifically inhibits translation initiation of canonical but not of leaderless messenger RNAs.

Name: Sodium citrate dihydrate
Information: Sodium citrate dehydrate (Trisodium citrate dihydrate, Citric acid trisodium salt dihydrate) is the preferred anticoagulant.
Synonyms: Trisodium citrate dihydrate, Citric acid trisodium salt dihydrate

Name: Melittin
Information: Melittin (MLT, Forapin, Forapine) is an activator of phospholipase A2 (PLA2) that stimulates the activity of the low molecular weight PLA2, while it does not the increase the activity of the high molecular weight enzyme.

Name: DL-Penicillamine
Information: DL-Penicillamine (DL-beta-Mercaptovaline, 3,3-Dimethyl-DL-cysteine, 3-Sulfanylvaline, Cuprimine, Depen, DL-PenA, DL-P) induces alteration of elastic fibers of periosteum-perichondrium and associates growth inhibition.

Name: Sodium Acetate
Pharmacopoeia: USP–NF 2021(Issue 2), EP10.5, KP Ⅹ, JP17, IP2010
Information: Sodium acetate is an organic sodium salt. It contains an acetate.

Name: Calcium chloride
Pharmacopoeia: USP–NF 2021(Issue 2), EP10.5, KP Ⅹ, JP17, IP2010
Information: Calcium chloride is an odorless, white, crystalline solid compound that is highly soluble in water.

Name: Sodium citrate
Pharmacopoeia: USP–NF 2021(Issue 2), EP10.5, KP Ⅹ, Ph.Int_6th, JP17, IP2010
Information: Sodium citrate dehydrate (Trisodium citrate dihydrate, Citric acid trisodium salt dihydrate) is the preferred anticoagulant.

Name: Ammonium ferric citrate
Information: Ammonium ferric citrate (Ferric ammonium citrate, Ammonium iron(III) citrate, Iron ammonium citrate, FerriSeltz) induces ferroptosis in non-small-cell lung carcinoma through the inhibition of GPX4-GSS/GSR-GGT axis activity.
Synonyms: Ferric ammonium citrate, Ammonium iron(III) citrate, Iron ammonium citrate, FerriSeltz

Name: Glatiramer acetate
Information: Glatiramer acetate is a synthetic copolymer composed of a random mixture of four amino acids that modifies the immune response.

Name: Gentamicin
Information: Gentamicin, an aminoglycoside class of bactericidal antibiotic, is effective against gram-negative bacterial infections.

Name: Merbromin
Information: Merbromin (Mercury dibromofluorescein disodium salt, Mercurochrome, Merbromine, Mercurocol, Sodium mercurescein, Asceptichrome, Supercrome, Brocasept, Cinfacromin), a xanthene dye, is a topical antiseptic used for minor cuts and scrapes. Merbromin is an organomercuric disodium salt compound and a fluorescein. Merbromin is a selective inhibitor of 3CLpro and provides a scaffold to design effective inhibitors of SARS-CoV-2.
Synonyms: Mercurochrome, Merbromine, Mercurocol, Sodium mercurescein, Asceptichrome, Supercrome, Brocasept, Cinfacromin

Name: Cidofovir hydrate
Information: Cidofovir hydrate is a selective inhibitor of viral DNA synthesis through the selective inhibition of viral DNA polymerase.

Name: Colistin
Information: Colistin, a cyclic polypeptide antibiotic synthesized by Bacillus polymyxa subspecies colistinus Koyama, exerts antimicrobial activity by targeting at the bacterial cell membrane.

Name: Menotropin
Information: Menotropin (Human Menopausal Gonadotrophin) is a hormonally active medication for the treatment of fertility disturbances, which are extracted from the urine of postmenopausal women.

Name: Tricine
Information: Tricine (N-[Tris(hydroxymethyl)methyl]glycine) is a buffer component for separation of low molecular weight peptides.

Name: Fondaparinux Sodium (Org 31540)
Information: Fondaparinux Sodium (Org 31540, Natural heparin pentasaccharide, Fondaparin, SR-90107A) is a synthetic glucopyranoside with antithrombotic activity. It selectively binds to antithrombin III, thereby potentiating the innate neutralization of activated factor X (Factor Xa) by antithrombin; a synthetic inhibitor of Factor Xa.
Synonyms: Natural heparin pentasaccharide Sodium, Fondaparin sodium, SR-90107A

Name: Metyrosine
Information: Metyrosine (α-Methyltyrosine), an antihypertensive drug, is a tyrosine hydroxylase inhibitor.

Name: Cetrorelix Acetate
Information: Cetrorelix Acetate (NS 75A Acetate, SB 075 Acetate, SB 75 Acetate) is a man-made hormone that blocks the effects of Gonadotropin Releasing Hormone (GnRH) with an IC50 of 1.21 nM.

Name: Papain
Information: Papain (papaya proteinase I) is a sulfhydryl protease from the latex of the papaya fruit. Papain breaks down intercellular matrix of cartilage.

Name: Fosphenytoin (disodium)
Information: Fosphenytoin (disodium) is the sodium salt form of fosphenytoin, a prodrug that is hydrolyzed to the anticonvulsant phenytoin upon parental administration.

Name: Prednisolone disodium phosphate
Information: Prednisolone disodium phosphate (Hydeltrasol, Prednisolone 21-phosphate disodium) is a synthetic glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory and immunomodulating properties that exerts late mitogenic and biphasic effects on resistant acute lymphoblastic leukemia cells.

Name: Cysteamine bitartrate
Information: Cysteamine bitartrate (Mercaptamine bitartrate) is an FDA-approved cystine-depleting aminothiol agent for the treatment of nephropathic cystinosis to decrease accumulation of lysosomal cystine by engaging in disulfide exchange. In addition, cysteamine bitartrate has antioxidant properties.

Name: Ammonium sulfate
Information: Ammonium sulphate (Mascagnite) is an inorganic sulfate salt used for the purification of enzymes and antibodies.

Name: Sodium Bicarbonate
Indication: heartburn, acid indigestion, and upset stomach as well as the treatment of metabolic acidosis associated with conditions such as severe renal disease and circulatory insufficiency due to shock
Information: Sodium bicarbonate(Armex Blast Media Flow Formula XL, BI-CF 40E, BI-H 40E, Bakeshure 180, Sodium Hydrogen Carbonate, Sodium hydrogen carbonate) is a biochemical reagent used as a pH buffering agent, an electrolyte replenisher, systemic alkalizer and in topical cleansing solutions.
Synonyms: Armex Blast Media Flow Formula XL, BI-CF 40E, BI-H 40E, Bakeshure 180, Sodium Hydrogen Carbonate, Sodium hydrogen carbonate

Name: Potassium Chloride
Information: Potassium chloride is an inorganic salt commonly used in fertilizer industry. It is also extensively used as a potassium supplement.

Name: Erlotinib HCl (OSI-744)
Information: Erlotinib HCl (OSI-744) is an EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM in cell-free assays, >1000-fold more sensitive for EGFR than human c-Src or v-Abl.

Name: Vandetanib (ZD6474)
Information: Vandetanib (ZD6474) is a potent inhibitor of VEGFR2 with IC50 of 40 nM in a cell-free assay. It also inhibits VEGFR3 and EGFR with IC50 of 110 nM and 500 nM, respectively. Not sensitive to PDGFRβ, Flt1, Tie-2 and FGFR1 with IC50 of 1.1-3.6 μM. No activity against MEK, CDK2, c-Kit, erbB2, FAK, PDK1, Akt and IGF-1R with IC50 above 10 μM.

Name: Imiquimod
Information: Imiquimod is a novel synthetic agent with immune response modifying activity.

Name: Camptothecin
Information: Camptothecin is a specific inhibitor of DNA topoisomerase I (Topo I) with IC50 of 0.68 μM in a cell-free assay. Phase 2.

Name: Ketoconazole
Information: Ketoconazole inhibits cyclosporine oxidase and testosterone 6 beta-hydroxylase with IC50 of 0.19 mM and 0.22 mM, respectively.

Name: Cefoselis Sulfate
Information: Cefoselis is a widely used beta-lactam antibiotic.

Name: Prazosin HCl
Information: Prazosin HCl is a competitive alpha-1 adrenoceptor antagonist, used to treat high blood pressure or benign prostatic hyperplasia.

Name: Ofloxacin
Information: Ofloxacin is a synthetic broad-spectrum antimicrobial agent.

Name: Marbofloxacin
Information: Marbofloxacin is a potent antibiotic inhibiting bacterial DNA replication.

Name: Irbesartan
Information: Irbesartan (SR-47436, BMS-186295) is a highly potent and specific angiotensin II type 1 (AT1) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 1.3 nM.

Name: Norfloxacin
Information: Norfloxacin is a broad-spectrum antibiotic.

Name: Risperidone
Information: Risperidone is a mutil-targeted antagonist for dopamine, serotonin, adrenergic and histamine receptors, used to treat schizophrenia and bipolar disorder.

Name: Sulfapyridine
Information: Sulfapyridine  is a sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Methyldopa
Information: Methyldopa (Aldomet) is a DOPA decarboxylase competitive inhibitor with an ED50 of 21.8 mg/kg.

Name: Torsemide
Information: Torsemide is a pyridyl sulfonylurea with a chemical structure between that of traditional loop diuretics and Cl- channel blockers, used to treat hypertension.

Name: Eplerenone
Information: Eplerenone is a mineralocorticoid receptor antagonist, and blocks the action of aldosterone, used to control high blood pressure.

Name: Paliperidone
Information: Paliperidone, the main active metabolite of Risperidone, is a potent serotonin-2A and dopamine-2 receptor antagonist, used in the treatment of schizophrenia.

Name: Flubendazole
Information: Flubendazole is an autophagy inducer by targeting Atg4B, used to treat internal parasite and worm infection.

Name: Oxibendazole
Information: Oxibendazole is a benzimidazole drug that interferes with metabolic pathways, used to protect against roundworms, strongyles, threadworms, pinworms and lungworm infestations in horses and some domestic pets.

Name: Irsogladine
Information: Irsogladine is an anti-gastric ulcer agent that facilitates gap-junctional intercellular communication through M1 muscarininc acetylcholine receptor binding.

Name: Sarafloxacin HCl
Information: Sarafloxacin HCl is a hydrochloride salt form of sarafloxacin which is a quinolone antibiotic drug with IC50 of 0.96 μg/L.

Name: Meclizine 2HCl
Information: Meclizine is a histamine H1 receptor antagonist used to treat nausea and motion sickness, has anti-histamine, anti-muscarinic and anti-oxidative phosphorylation properties, also an agonist ligand for mCAR (constitutive androstane receptor) and an inverse agonist for hCAR.

Name: Epalrestat
Information: Epalrestat is an aldose reductase inhibitor with IC50 of 72 nM.

Name: Lornoxicam
Information: Lornoxicam is a non-steroidal COX-1/COX-2 inhibitor, used as an anti-inflammatory drug to treat pain, osteoarthritis, and rheumatoid arthritis.

Name: Vinpocetine
Information: Vinpocetine is a selective inhibitor of voltage-sensitive sodium channel for the treatment of stroke, vascular dementia  and Alzheimer's disease.

Name: Neratinib (HKI-272)
Information: Neratinib (HKI-272) is a highly selective HER2 and EGFR inhibitor with IC50 of 59 nM and 92 nM in cell-free assays weakly inhibits KDR and Src, no significant inhibition to Akt, CDK1/2/4, IKK-2, MK-2, PDK1, c-Raf and c-Met. Phase 3.

Name: Sitafloxacin Hydrate
Information: Sitafloxacin Hydrate is a new-generation, broad-spectrum oral fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: R788 (Fostamatinib) Disodium
Information: R788 (Fostamatinib) disodium, a prodrug of the active metabolite R406, is a Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 41 nM in a cell-free assay, strongly inhibits Syk but not Lyn, 5-fold less potent to Flt3. Phase 3.

Name: Ketanserin
Information: Ketanserin is a specific 5-HT2A serotonin receptor antagonist with Ki of 2.5 nM for rat and human 5-HT2A, used as an antihypertensive drug.

Name: (-)-Huperzine A (HupA)
Information: (-)-Huperzine A is a potent, highly specific and reversible inhibitor of acetylcholinesterase (AChE) with Ki of 7 nM, exhibiting 200-fold more selectivity for G4 AChE over G1 AChE. Also acts as an NMDA receptor antagonist. Phase 4.

Name: Diosmin
Information: Diosmin is a semisynthetic phlebotropic agent and a member of the flavonoid family.

Name: Hypoxanthine
Information: Hypoxanthine, a naturally occurring purine derivative, an intermediate product of uric acid synthesis, formed from adenylic acid and itself a precursor of xanthine.

Name: Itraconazole
Information: Itraconazole is a relatively potent inhibitor of CYP3A4 with IC50 of 6.1 nM, used as a triazole antifungal agent.

Name: 7-Aminocephalosporanic acid
Information: 7-Aminocephalosporanic acid is used for synthesis of cephalosporin antibiotics and intermediates.

Name: Trazodone HCl
Information: Trazodone HCl is an antidepressant belonging to the class of serotonin receptor antagonists and reuptake inhibitors for treatment of anxiety disorders.

Name: Oseltamivir Phosphate
Information: Oseltamivir Phosphate is a potent and selective inhibitor of the neuraminidase that is essential for replication of influenza A and B viruses, used to prevent influenza.

Name: Capmatinib (INCB28060)
Information: Capmatinib (INCB28060) is a novel, ATP-competitive inhibitor of c-MET with IC50 of 0.13 nM in a cell-free assay, inactive against RONβ, as well as EGFR and HER-3. Phase 1.

Name: Mozavaptan
Information: Mozavaptan is a novel competitive vasopressin receptor antagonist for both V1 and V2 receptors with IC50 of 1.2 μM and 14 nM, respectively.

Name: Droxidopa
Information: Droxidopa is a psychoactive drug and acts as a prodrug to the neurotransmitters norepinephrine (noradrenaline) and epinephrine (adrenaline).

Name: Enrofloxacin
Information: Enrofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Ambroxol HCl
Information: AmbroxolHCl is a potent inhibitor of the neuronal Na+ channels, inhibits TTX-resistant Na+ currents with IC50 of 35.2 μM and 22.5 μM for tonic and phasic block, inhibits TTX-sensitive Na+ currents with IC50 of 100 μM. Phase 3.

Name: Cefadroxil hydrate
Information: Cefadroxil is a broad-spectrum antibiotic of the cephalosporin type, effective in Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacterial infections.

Name: Bilastine
Information: Bilastine is a new, well-tolerated, nonsedating H1 receptor antihistamine and has a rapid onset and prolonged duration of action.

Name: Sodium Aescinate
Information: Sodium aescinate (SA) is a widely-applied triterpene saponin product derived from horse chestnut seeds, possessing vasoactive and organ-protective activities with oral or injection administration in the clinic.

Name: Sodium Houttuyfonate
Information: Sodium Houttuyfonate, the active compound of the Houttuynia plant, is mainly used for treating purulent skin infections, respiratory tract infections, including pneumonia in elderly patients, and chronic bronchitis.

Name: Nuciferine
Information: Nuciferine is a major active aporphine alkaloid from the leaves of N. nucifera Gaertn and possesses anti-hyperlipidemia, anti-hypotensive, anti-arrhythmic, and insulin secretagogue activities.

Name: Vincamine
Information: Vincamine, an indole alkaloid found in the leaves of V. minor and C. roseus, is a peripheral vasodilator that increases blood flow to the brain.
Synonyms: Angiopac, Devincan, Equipur, Minorin, Novicet, Oxybral, Perval, Sostenil, Tripervan

Name: Sennoside A
Information: Sennoside A, a kind of irritant laxative isolated from rhei rhizome, causes purgative actions in the intestine.

Name: Retinyl (Vitamin A) Palmitate
Information: Vitamin A palmitate is a more stable, synthetic version of the essential nutrient vitamin A joined to palmitic acid.

Name: Clopidol
Information: Clopidol is an antiprotozoal agent.

Name: Chlortetracycline HCl
Information: Chlortetracycline HCl is the first identified tetracycline antibiotic.

Name: Amoxapine
Information: Amoxapine is a tricyclic dibenzoxazepine (an N-aryl piperazine) which acts similarly to several other tricyclic antidepressants, amoxapine inhibits GLYT2a transport activity with IC50 of 92 μM.

Name: Ebastine
Information: Ebastine is a potent H1-histamine receptor antagonist, used for allergic disorders.

Name: Folic acid
Information: Folic acid, a B vitamin, plays an important role in cell division and in the synthesis of amino acids and nucleic acids like DNA.
Synonyms: Folacin, Vitamin B9, Vitamin M, Pteroylglutamic acid, Folate

Name: Dolutegravir Sodium
Information: Dolutegravir sodium is a HIV integrase inhibitor with IC50 of 2.7 nM.

Name: Netupitant
Information: Netupitant is a selective neurokinin 1 (NK1) receptor antagonist with potential antiemetic activity.

Name: Cetilistat
Information: Cetilistat is a novel highly lipophilic benzoxazinone that inhibits gastrointestinal and pancreatic lipases. It shows a good safety and tolerability profile in vivo

Name: Mebhydrolin napadisylate
Information: Mebhydrolin Napadisylate is classified as an antihistamine drug classes used to treat allergies.

Name: 6-Aminopenicillanic acid
Information: 6-Aminopenicillanic acid (6-APA) is the central component of penicillin β-lactam antibiotics which are generated by Penicillium. It is used as precursor for antibiotic compounds ampicillin and amoxicillin.

Name: Alectinib hydrochloride
Information: Alectinib is a second generation oral drug that selectively inhibits the activity of anaplastic lymphoma kinase (ALK) tyrosine kinase.

Name: Amantadine
Information: Amantadine is an antiviral that is used in the prophylactic or symptomatic treatment of influenza A. It is an M2 inhibitor which blocks the ion channel formed by the M2 protein that spans the viral membrane.

Name: Balofloxacin Dihydrate
Information: an agonist of the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor delta (PPARd) signaling pathway

Name: Xanthopterin Hydrate
Information: Xanthopterin, isolated from butterfly wings and found in many other sources, replace folic acid in the nutrition of many animal species.

Name: Zofenopril calcium
Information: Zofenopril calcium is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor that protects the heart and helps reduce high blood pressure.

Name: Garenoxacin
Information: Garenoxacin (T-3811ME, BMS-284756) is a novel des-F(6) quinolone that has been shown to be effective in vitro against a wide range of clinically important pathogens, including gram-positive and gram-negative aerobes and anaerobes.

Name: Mirogabalin
Information: Mirogabalin (DS-5565) is a novel, preferentially selective α2δ-1 ligand that has been used in trials studying the treatment of Post-herpetic Neuralgia, Pain Associated With Fibromyalgia, and Diabetic peripheral neuropathic pain.

Name: Tazemetostat (EPZ-6438)
Information: Tazemetostat (EPZ-6438) is a potent, and selective EZH2 inhibitor with Ki and IC50 of 2.5 nM and 11 nM in cell-free assays, exhibiting a 35-fold selectivity versus EZH1 and >4,500-fold selectivity relative to 14 other HMTs.

Name: Indoximod (NLG-8189）
Information: Indoximod (NLG-8189), a methylated tryptophan, acts as an IDO (indoleamine-(2,3)-dioxygenase) pathway inhibitor, and reverses IDO-mediated immune suppression. Phase 2.

Name: Brigatinib (AP26113)
Information: Brigatinib (AP26113) is a potent and selective ALK (IC50, 0.6 nM) and ROS1 (IC50, 0.9 nM) inhibitor. It also inhibits ROS1, FLT3, and mutant variants of FLT3 (D835Y) and EGFR with lower potentcy.

Name: Gefitinib hydrochloride
Information: Gefitinib is an EGFR inhibitor with IC50s of 15.5 nM and 823.3 nM for WT EGFR and EGFR (858R/T790M), respectively.

Name: Sulfaquinoxaline sodium
Information: Sulfaquinoxaline sodium (N'1-quinoxalin-2-ylsulphanilamide sodium, SQ-Na) is the sodium salt of sulfaquinoxaline, which is often used as a drug to prevent coccidiosis in poultry, swine, and sheep by inhibiting the synthesis of nucleic acids and proteins in microorganisms.

Name: Cephalexin
Information: Cephalexin is an antibiotic that can treat a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Palbociclib
Status: FDA, DMF, EMA, CFDA, NDC, PMDA
Information: Palbociclib (Ibrance, PD 0332991) is a highly specific inhibitor of cyclin-dependent kinase 4 (Cdk4) and Cdk6 with IC50 of 11 nM and 16 nM, respectively.

Name: Potassium guaiacolsulfonate hemihydrate
Information: Potassium guaiacolsulfonate hemihydrate (Potassium Hydroxymethoxybenzenesulfonate, Sulfogaiacol) is used as an expectorant for relieving symptoms of cough and mucus in the chest due to respiratory infections, asthma, colds, or hay fever.

Name: Bictegravir Sodium
Information: Bictegravir (GS-9883) Sodium is a novel and potent inhibitor of HIV-1 integrase, specifically targets IN strand transfer activity with an IC50 of 7.5 nM.

Name: Spinosad
Information: Spinosad, a mixture of spinosyns A and D known as fermentation products of a soil actinomycete, is a biological neurotoxic insecticide with a broader action spectrum, targeting the nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChRs) of the insect nervous system.

Name: Tranylcypromine Sulfate
Information: Tranylcypromine (Parnate) is an irreversible inhibitor of monoamine oxidase (MAO) with a rapid onset of activity.

Name: Cabotegravir Sodium
Information: Cabotegravir (GSK-1265744) sodium is a orally active and long-acting HIV integrase strand transfer inhibitor. It also inhibits organic anion transporter 1/3 (OAT1/OAT3) with IC50 of 0.41 μM and 0.81 μM for OAT3 and OAT1, respectively.

Name: Oxaliplatin
Information: Oxaliplatin inhibits DNA synthesis by conforming DNA adducts in RT4, TCCSUP, A2780, HT-29, U-373MG, U-87MG, SK-MEL-2, and HT-144 cells.

Name: Heparin sodium
Information: Heparin sodium, a sulfated polysaccharide belonging to the family of glycosaminoglycans, has numerous important biological activities associated with its interaction with diverse proteins, used as an anticoagulant.

Name: Risedronate Sodium
Information: Risedronate Sodium, a nitrogen-containing bisphosphonate, inhibits osteoclast-mediated bone resorption and modulates bone metabolism, used in the treatment of osteoporosis.

Name: Disodium Cromoglycate
Information: Disodium Cromoglycate is an antiallergic drug with IC50 of 39 μg/mL.

Name: Adenine sulfate
Information: Adenine sulfate is a sulfate salt form of adenine which is a purine derivative and a nucleobase with a variety of roles in biochemistry.

Name: Azasetron HCl
Information: Azasetron HCl is a selective 5-HT3 receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.33 nM used in the management of nausea and vomiting induced by cancer chemotherapy.

Name: Hydralazine HCl
Information: Hydralazine HCl is a hydrochloride salt of hydralazine, which is a direct-acting smooth muscle relaxant used to treat hypertension by acting as a vasodilator primarily in arteries and arterioles.

Name: Besifloxacin HCl
Information: Besifloxacin HCl is a fourth-generation fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Calcium gluconate
Information: Calcium gluconate is element or mineral necessary for normal nerve, muscle, and cardiac function. Calcium as the gluconate salt helps to maintain calcium balance and prevent bone loss when taken orally.
Synonyms: Calcarea gluconica, Calcium gluconate anhydrous, Calcium D-gluconate, Calciofon, Glucobiogen

Name: Deferiprone
Information: Deferiprone is a chelating agent with an affinity for ferric ion (iron III)，binds with ferric ions to form neutral 3:1 (deferiprone:iron) complexes that are stable over a wide range of pH values.

Name: D-Phenylalanine
Information: D-Phenylalanine, a carboxypeptidase A, endorphinase and enkephalinase inhibitor, enhances endorphin production and diminishes pain.

Name: Minocycline HCl
Information: Minocycline HCl is the most lipid soluble and most active tetracycline antibiotic, binds to the 30S ribosomal subunit, preventing the binding of tRNA to the mRNA-ribosome complex and interfering with protein synthesis.

Name: Alosetron Hydrochloride
Information: Alosetron Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of alosetron, a potent and selective 5-HT3 receptor antagonist.

Name: Piperaquine phosphate
Information: Piperaquine phosphate is an orally active bisquinolone antimalarial drug.

Name: Icatibant Acetate
Information: Icatibant Acetate acts as an antagonist of the bradykinin B2 receptor and is used in the treatment of hereditary angioedema.

Name: Plerixafor (AMD3100)
Information: Plerixafor (AMD3100) is a chemokine receptor antagonist for CXCR4 and CXCL12-mediated chemotaxis with IC50 of 44 nM and 5.7 nM in cell-free assays, respectively.

Name: Sodium Hyaluronate
Information: Sodium hyaluronate is similar to the fluid that surrounds the joints in your body. This fluid acts as a lubricant and shock absorber for the joints.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Fosinopril Sodium
Information: Fosinopril Sodium is the ester prodrug of an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor, used for the treatment of hypertension and some types of chronic heart failure.

Name: Strontium Ranelate
Information: Strontium Ranelate is a strontium(II) salt of ranelic acid for (-)-desmethoxyverapamil binding to calcium channel with IC50 of 0.5 mM.

Name: Aprotinin
Information: Aprotinin is a small protein serine protease inhibitor (Kd=0.06 pM for bovine β-trypsin), used to reduce perioperative blood loss and transfusion.
